acceptThisReceiver.description: The value of yes(1) indicates that trap generation for this manager is enabled. The value of no(2) indicates that trap generation for this manager is disabled

mconfigBOOTPEnabled.name: mconfigBOOTPEnabled
mconfigBOOTPEnabled.description: The value of yes(1) indicates the PowerNet Adapter is configured to obtain its IP configuration parameters from a BOOTP server. The value of no(2) indicates adapter will assume IP configuration parameters values saved in adapter's eeprom, which was originally configured at local console.

mconfigTFTPServerIP.name: mconfigTFTPServerIP
mconfigTFTPServerIP.description: The IP address of TFTP server. If mconfigBOOTPEnabled is yes(1), then this IP address is provided by BOOTP server and not allowed to be modified; otherwise, this IP address can be modified. Before using TFTP to load new code image, the image file should be placed in proper directory of the specified TFTP server. This OID is only supported by APC Network Management Cards.

newCodeAuthentViaTFTP.name: newCodeAuthentViaTFTP
newCodeAuthentViaTFTP.description: Once mcontrolRestartAgent is set to loadAndExecuteNewAgent (3), PowerNet adapter will start to load the remote image file, for authentication only, instead of saving the code into flash memory. Only if a validNewAgentCodeImage (1) is found will the agent reboot the PowerNet adapter and invoke the loader to load and save new code into the flash memory. Otherwise, the current agent code will continue to run. This OID shows the result of the above authentication process. validNewAgentCodeImage (1) means the code image on TFTP server is a valid APC agent code and is different version from the current agent. Once agent identifies this, loader will start to update flash memory with the new agent code. sameAgentCodeImage (2) means the code image on TFTP server is exactly the same as the currently running agent. Currently running agent will not invoke loader to load the same again. invalidAgentCodeImage (3) means the code image on TFTP server is NOT a valid APC agent code. Thus, current agent will not load it into the flash memory. The value of this OID will be associated with TRAP codeImageAuthentDone. This OID is only supported by APC Network Management Cards.

mconfigClockDate.name: mconfigClockDate
mconfigClockDate.description: The current date in the mm/dd/yyyy format. Example: 01/01/2000.

mconfigClockTime.name: mconfigClockTime
mconfigClockTime.description: The current time in the hh:mm:ss am/pm format. Example: 12:00:00 am.

mcontrolRestartAgent.name: mcontrolRestartAgent
mcontrolRestartAgent.description: Setting this OID to restartCurrentAgent (1) will restart the same SNMP agent code currently saved in flash memory. Setting this OID to loadAndExecuteNewAgent (3) will enable adapter to load a new agent code into the flash memory and start to execute this new agent code. Bootp/tftp is the default protocol. loadAndExecuteNewAgent is only supported by APC Network Management Cards. Setting this OID to restartWithoutAgent (4) will restart the system and not start the agent. The subsequent time the system restarts the agent will also automatically restart. Setting this OID to resetNetworkAndRestart (5) will set the Boot Mode, IP Address, Subnet Mask, and Default Gateway to defaults, expire any existing DHCP lease and then restart the system. Setting this OID to resetNetworkLeaveModeAndRestart (6) will leave the Boot Mode at the current setting, set the IP Address, Subnet Mask, and Default Gateway to defaults, expire any existing DHCP lease and then restart the system.

mfiletransferStatusLastTransferResult.name: mfiletransferStatusLastTransferResult
mfiletransferStatusLastTransferResult.description: This OID has been deprecated. Once mfiletransferControlInitiateFileTransfer is set to a value other than doNotInitiateFileTransfer a file transfer of mfiletransferConfigSettingsFilename will be attempted from either a TFTP or FTP server. This OID shows the last attempted file transfer result. lastFileTransferResultSuccessful (1) means the file transfer was successful. lastFileTransferResultNotAvailable (2) means that there have been no previous file transfers. lastFileTransferResultFailureUnknown (3) means that the last file transfer failed for an unknown reason. lastFileTransferResultFailureServerInaccessible (4) means that the TFTP or FTP server could not be found on the network. lastFileTransferResultFailureServerAccessDenied (5) means that the TFTP or FTP server denied access. lastFileTransferResultFailureFileNotFound (6) means that the file could not be located. lastFileTransferResultFailureFileTypeUnknown (7) means the file was examined, but the contents were unknown. lastFileTransferResultFailureFileCorrupt (8) means the transferred file was corrupt.

mfiletransferConfigSettingsFilename.name: mfiletransferConfigSettingsFilename
mfiletransferConfigSettingsFilename.description: This OID has been deprecated. The path and name of the file to transfer using the mfiletransferControlInitiateFileTransfer OID. If the file to transfer exists in the default server directory then the path may be omitted.

mfiletransferConfigTFTPServerAddress.name: mfiletransferConfigTFTPServerAddress
mfiletransferConfigTFTPServerAddress.description: This OID has been deprecated. The IP Address in dotted decimal notation of the TFTP server involved in the file transfer.

mfiletransferConfigFTPServerAddress.name: mfiletransferConfigFTPServerAddress
mfiletransferConfigFTPServerAddress.description: This OID has been deprecated. The IP Address in dotted decimal notation of the FTP server involved in the file transfer.

mfiletransferConfigFTPServerUser.name: mfiletransferConfigFTPServerUser
mfiletransferConfigFTPServerUser.description: This OID has been deprecated. The user identification for logging into the FTP server specified with mfiletransferConfigFTPServerAddress.

mfiletransferConfigFTPServerPassword.name: mfiletransferConfigFTPServerPassword
mfiletransferConfigFTPServerPassword.description: This OID has been deprecated. The password for logging into the FTP server specified with mfiletransferConfigFTPServerAddress.

mfiletransferControlInitiateFileTransfer.name: mfiletransferControlInitiateFileTransfer
mfiletransferControlInitiateFileTransfer.description: This OID has been deprecated. Setting this OID to doNotInitiateFileTransfer (1) will do nothing. Setting this OID to initiateFileTransferDownloadViaTFTP (2) will attempt to transfer the file named in mfiletransferConfigSettingsFilename from the TFTP Server identified in mfiletransferConfigTFTPAddress. Setting this OID to initiateFileTransferDownloadViaFTP (3) will attempt to transfer the file named in mfiletransferConfigSettingsFilename from the FTP Server identified in mfiletransferConfigFTPAddress using mfiletransferConfigFTPUser and mfiletransferConfigFTPPassword for the FTP Server login process.

xPDUDeviceNominalMainInputVoltage.description: The nominal main input voltage to the PDU. Measured in Volts, line-to-line for a 3-wire (delta) service or line-to-neutral for a 4-wire (wye) service.

xPDUDeviceServiceType.description: The type of utility input to the PDU. Either 3 wires (delta), or 4 wires (wye).

xPDUDevicePanelBreakerRating.description: The rating of the panel breaker measured in Amps.

xPDUDeviceLoadTieBreakerPresent.name: xPDUDeviceLoadTieBreakerPresent
xPDUDeviceLoadTieBreakerPresent.description: Indicates whether or not a load tie breaker is installed in the PDU.

xPDUDeviceInfraStruXureType.description: Indicates the configuration of this PDU system. Type-B PDU is in a distributed UPS system and has bypass capabilities. Type-C PDU receives power from a larger central UPS.

xPDUMainInputOverVoltThreshold.name: xPDUMainInputOverVoltThreshold
xPDUMainInputOverVoltThreshold.description: Threshold above which an input over voltage condition will be generated. Specified as percent deviation from nominal.

xPDUMainInputUnderVoltThreshold.name: xPDUMainInputUnderVoltThreshold
xPDUMainInputUnderVoltThreshold.description: Threshold below which an input under voltage condition will be generated. Specified as percent deviation from nominal. A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

xPDUMainInputVoltageTableSize.name: xPDUMainInputVoltageTableSize
xPDUMainInputVoltageTableSize.description: The number of Main input voltage entries.

xPDUMainInputVoltagePhaseEntry.name: xPDUMainInputVoltagePhaseEntry
xPDUMainInputVoltagePhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular main input voltage phase.

xPDUMainInputVoltagePhaseIndex.name: xPDUMainInputVoltagePhaseIndex

xPDUMainInputVoltageLtoL.name: xPDUMainInputVoltageLtoL

xPDUMainInputVoltageLtoN.name: xPDUMainInputVoltageLtoN
xPDUMainInputVoltageLtoN.description: Line-to-neutral PDU input voltage when an isolation transformer is not present, or -1 if a transformer is present in this PDU. Measured in tenths of Volts.

xPDUBypassInputOverVoltThreshold.name: xPDUBypassInputOverVoltThreshold
xPDUBypassInputOverVoltThreshold.description: Threshold above which a bypass input over voltage condition will be generated. Specified as percent deviation from nominal.

xPDUBypassInputUnderVoltThreshold.name: xPDUBypassInputUnderVoltThreshold
xPDUBypassInputUnderVoltThreshold.description: Threshold below which an bypass input under voltage condition will be generated. Specified as percent deviation from nominal. A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

xPDUBypassInputVoltagePhaseEntry.name: xPDUBypassInputVoltagePhaseEntry

xPDUBranchBreakerRating.name: xPDUBranchBreakerRating
xPDUBranchBreakerRating.description: Indicates current rating of this breaker. 0=Breaker is not present. 1=Earth leakage connection. 2=Neutral connection. A value greater than 2 indicates breaker current rating in Amps. A value above 60 Amp will signify a remote feed. The xPDUBranchBreakerRDPFeed OID will indicate which breakers are configured as a remote drop. Note: When setting branch circuit thresholds/ratings for an entry, all positions tied (see the xPDUBranchBreakerTieIndicator OID) to this entry will inherit the new threshold/rating.

xPDUBranchBreakerRDPFeed.name: xPDUBranchBreakerRDPFeed
xPDUBranchBreakerRDPFeed.description: Indicates that a breaker position is feeding a remote distribution panel.

xPDUBranchBreakerTieIndicator.name: xPDUBranchBreakerTieIndicator
xPDUBranchBreakerTieIndicator.description: Indicates whether or not the breaker in this position is logically associated with the breaker immediately below it. This setting is used grouping the breakers feeding a multi-pole branch circuit. Note: When setting an entry's branch breaker tie indicator to breakerTied, all the positions that are tied to this breaker will take on the rating and thresholds for this entry of the table.

xPDUBranchBreakerCurrent.name: xPDUBranchBreakerCurrent
xPDUBranchBreakerCurrent.description: Indicates the branch current in tenths of Amps or -1 when not available.

xPDUBranchBreakerOverCurrentThreshold.name: xPDUBranchBreakerOverCurrentThreshold
xPDUBranchBreakerOverCurrentThreshold.description: Threshold above which a branch circuit high current condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the branch breaker rating. A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled. Note: When setting branch circuit thresholds/ratings for an entry, all positions tied (see the xPDUBranchBreakerTieIndicator OID) to this entry will inherit the new threshold/rating.

xPDUBranchBreakerUnderCurrentThreshold.name: xPDUBranchBreakerUnderCurrentThreshold
xPDUBranchBreakerUnderCurrentThreshold.description: Threshold below which a branch circuit low current condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the branch breaker rating. A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled. Note: When setting branch circuit thresholds/ratings for an entry, all positions tied (see the xPDUBranchBreakerTieIndicator OID) to this entry will inherit the new threshold/rating.

xPDUBranchBreakerMaxCurrentThreshold.name: xPDUBranchBreakerMaxCurrentThreshold

A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled. Note: When setting branch circuit thresholds/ratings for an entry, all positions tied (see the xPDUBranchBreakerTieIndicator OID) to this entry will inherit the new threshold/rating.

A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled. Note: When setting branch circuit thresholds/ratings for an entry, all positions tied (see the xPDUBranchBreakerTieIndicator OID) to this entry will inherit the new threshold/rating.

pmmBranchCircuitTotalApparentPower.description: Branch circuit total apparent power. Measured in tenths of kVA.

pmmBranchCircuitEnergyUsage.name: pmmBranchCircuitEnergyUsage
pmmBranchCircuitEnergyUsage.description: Indicates the energy usage in tenths of kWh or -1 when not available.

pmmBranchCircuitEnergyUsageResetDate.name: pmmBranchCircuitEnergyUsageResetDate
pmmBranchCircuitEnergyUsageResetDate.description: The date that the kWh usage was reset, in the format mm/dd/yyyy.

pmmBranchCircuitTotalPowerFactor.name: pmmBranchCircuitTotalPowerFactor
pmmBranchCircuitTotalPowerFactor.description: Indicates the total power factor of the branch circuit output. A value of 100 representing a unity power factor (1.00) Specified in hundredths.

pmmBranchCircuitBreakerState.name: pmmBranchCircuitBreakerState
pmmBranchCircuitBreakerState.description: This value indicates the current state of branch circuit breaker. 1 will indicate open, 2 will indicate closed, 3 will indicate unknown.

pmmBranchCircuitMinCurrentThreshold.name: pmmBranchCircuitMinCurrentThreshold
pmmBranchCircuitMinCurrentThreshold.description: Threshold below which a branch circuit minimum current condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the branch breaker rating represented in the OID pmmBranchCircuitBreakerRating A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

pmmBranchCircuitLowCurrentThreshold.name: pmmBranchCircuitLowCurrentThreshold
pmmBranchCircuitLowCurrentThreshold.description: Threshold below which a branch circuit low current condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the branch breaker rating represented in the OID pmmBranchCircuitBreakerRating A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

pmmBranchCircuitHighCurrentThreshold.name: pmmBranchCircuitHighCurrentThreshold
pmmBranchCircuitHighCurrentThreshold.description: Threshold below which a branch circuit high current condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the branch breaker rating represented in the OID pmmBranchCircuitBreakerRating A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

pmmBranchCircuitMaxCurrentThreshold.name: pmmBranchCircuitMaxCurrentThreshold
pmmBranchCircuitMaxCurrentThreshold.description: Threshold below which a branch circuit maximum current condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the branch breaker rating represented in the OID pmmBranchCircuitBreakerRating A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

pmmBranchCircuitMinApparentPowerThreshol.name: pmmBranchCircuitMinApparentPowerThreshold
pmmBranchCircuitMinApparentPowerThreshol.description: Threshold below which a branch circuit minimum apparent power condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the branch breaker apparent power rating. A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

pmmBranchCircuitMaxApparentPowerThreshol.name: pmmBranchCircuitMaxApparentPowerThreshold
pmmBranchCircuitMaxApparentPowerThreshol.description: Threshold below which a branch circuit maximum apparent power condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the branch breaker apparent power rating. A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

pmmBranchCircuitAlaramGeneration.name: pmmBranchCircuitAlaramGeneration
pmmBranchCircuitAlaramGeneration.description: Alarm generation status. 1 will indicate enabled, 2 will indicate disabled, 3 will indicate unknown.

pmmBranchCircuitBreakerOpenAlarm.name: pmmBranchCircuitBreakerOpenAlarm
pmmBranchCircuitBreakerOpenAlarm.description: Breaker open alarm status. 1 will indicate enabled, 2 will indicate disabled, 3 will indicate unknown.

xATSIdentProductName.name: xATSIdentProductName
xATSIdentProductName.description: The name of the transfer switch unit.

xATSIdentHardwareRev.name: xATSIdentHardwareRev
xATSIdentHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the transfer switch. This value is set at the factory.

xATSIdentFirmwareAppRev.name: xATSIdentFirmwareAppRev
xATSIdentFirmwareAppRev.description: An ID string identifying the application firmware revision of the transfer switch.

xATSIdentFirmwareAppOSRev.name: xATSIdentFirmwareAppOSRev
xATSIdentFirmwareAppOSRev.description: An ID string identifying the application operating system firmware revision of the transfer switch.

xATSIdentFirmwareControllerRev.name: xATSIdentFirmwareControllerRev
xATSIdentFirmwareControllerRev.description: An ID string identifying the transfer switch controller firmware revision.

xATSIdentDateOfManufacture.name: xATSIdentDateOfManufacture
xATSIdentDateOfManufacture.description: The date when the transfer switch was manufactured in mm/dd/yyyy format. This value is set at the factory.

xATSIdentModelNumber.name: xATSIdentModelNumber
xATSIdentModelNumber.description: A character string identifying the model number of the transfer switch. This value is set at the factory.

xATSIdentSerialNumber.name: xATSIdentSerialNumber
xATSIdentSerialNumber.description: A character string identifying the serial number of the transfer switch. This value is set at the factory.

xATSDeviceServiceType.name: xATSDeviceServiceType
xATSDeviceServiceType.description: The type of utility input to the transfer switch. Either 3 wires (delta), or 4 wires (wye).

xATSDeviceNominalVoltage.name: xATSDeviceNominalVoltage
xATSDeviceNominalVoltage.description: The nominal line-to-neutral system voltage. Measured in Volts, line-to-line for a 3-wire service or line-to-neutral for a 4-wire service. -1 if not available.

xATSDeviceNominalFrequency.name: xATSDeviceNominalFrequency
xATSDeviceNominalFrequency.description: The nominal system frequency. Measured in tenths of Hertz. -1 if not available.

xATSDeviceTransferSwitchRating.name: xATSDeviceTransferSwitchRating
xATSDeviceTransferSwitchRating.description: The rating of the transfer switch. Measured in Amps.

xATSDeviceDCBackUpPresent.name: xATSDeviceDCBackUpPresent
xATSDeviceDCBackUpPresent.description: Indicates if a DC backup is present or not.

xATSSwitchStatusSelectedSource.name: xATSSwitchStatusSelectedSource
xATSSwitchStatusSelectedSource.description: The source which is currently selected, i.e. supplying power to the load.

xATSSwitchStatusOperationalMode.name: xATSSwitchStatusOperationalMode
xATSSwitchStatusOperationalMode.description: The current operating mode of the transfer switch. When the ATS is in automatic mode, generator starting and ATS transferring is all done automatically as needed based on the state of source 1. Automatic operation is halted when the ATS is in either of the notInAuto modes. A mode of notInAuto indicates that the automatic operation switch is in the disabled position, as indicated by the xATSSwitchStatusAutomaticOperationSwitch OID. The notInAutoAbnormal condition indicates that an abnormal condition has caused the transfer switch to halt automatic operation. In this case, traps can indicate the exact problem. In the case of notInAutoAbnormal, refer to the operation manual for details on how debug the condition and restore automatic operation.

xATSSwitchStatusAutomaticOperationSwitch.name: xATSSwitchStatusAutomaticOperationSwitch
xATSSwitchStatusAutomaticOperationSwitch.description: The position of the automatic operation switch on the front of the transfer switch.

xATSSwitchStatusEngineStartSignal.name: xATSSwitchStatusEngineStartSignal
xATSSwitchStatusEngineStartSignal.description: The position of the Start/Stop contact which signals the generator engine to start/run. When the ATS is in automatic mode, generator starting/stopping is under ATS control.

xATSSwitchSettingsLowVoltageTransferPoin.name: xATSSwitchSettingsLowVoltageTransferPoint
xATSSwitchSettingsLowVoltageTransferPoin.description: The lowest acceptable voltage condition at source 1. When any phase of source 1 is lower than this voltage, source quality is considered bad and the generator run signal is asserted to begin generator operation. Specified in volts, line-to-line for a 3-wire service or line-to-neutral for a 4-wire service. -1 if not available.

xATSSwitchSettingsHighVoltageTransferPoi.name: xATSSwitchSettingsHighVoltageTransferPoint
xATSSwitchSettingsHighVoltageTransferPoi.description: The highest acceptable voltage condition at source 1. When any phase of source 1 is greater than this voltage, source quality is considered bad and the generator run signal is asserted to begin generator operation. Specified in volts, line-to-line for a 3-wire service or line-to-neutral for a 4-wire service. -1 if not available.

xATSSwitchSettingsMaxFrequencyDeviation.name: xATSSwitchSettingsMaxFrequencyDeviation
xATSSwitchSettingsMaxFrequencyDeviation.description: The maximum acceptable frequency deviation condition from nominal at source 1. When source 1 frequency is outside the specified range, source quality is considered bad and the generator run signal is asserted to begin generator operation. Specified in tenths of Hertz above or below nominal. A value of zero indicates that frequency is ignored when determining source quality. -1 if not available.

xATSSwitchSettingsMinPhaseBalance.name: xATSSwitchSettingsMinPhaseBalance
xATSSwitchSettingsMinPhaseBalance.description: The minimum required phase balance at source 1. When the percentage difference between the minimum and maximum phase voltage measurements at source 1 is greater than this value, source quality is considered bad and the generator run signal is asserted to begin generator operation. Specified as a percentage. A value of zero indicates that phase balance is ignored when determining source quality. -1 if not available.

xATSSwitchSettingsNominalRotation.name: xATSSwitchSettingsNominalRotation
xATSSwitchSettingsNominalRotation.description: The nominal phase rotation (or phase sequence) required by the load. For certain types of equipment, such as rotating machinery, phase rotation is critical for proper operation as it determines the direction which motors will rotate (clockwise or counterclockwise). Source quality will be seen as bad if the rotation measured at that ATS input does not match this setting. If this setting is set to any, phase rotation is ignored.

xATSSwitchSettingsAllowClosedTransfer.name: xATSSwitchSettingsAllowClosedTransfer
xATSSwitchSettingsAllowClosedTransfer.description: This setting enables seamless (closed) transfers between sources. When possible, both source 1 and source 2 are closed to the output for a brief time. If closed transfer is not possible within the amount of time specified by the xATSSwitchSettingsMaxSyncTime OID, an open transfer will be executed.

xATSSwitchSettingsMaxSyncTime.name: xATSSwitchSettingsMaxSyncTime
xATSSwitchSettingsMaxSyncTime.description: When attempting/seeking to perform a closed transfer, this setting defines the maximum time allowed before the transfer switch will give up and perform an open transfer. Specified in seconds. -1 if not available.

xATSSwitchSettingsNeutralTransferTime.name: xATSSwitchSettingsNeutralTransferTime
xATSSwitchSettingsNeutralTransferTime.description: This setting defines how long both source 1 and source 2 will be disconnected from the output, during an open transfer. Specified in seconds. -1 if not available.

xATSSwitchSettingsSetToFactoryDefaults.name: xATSSwitchSettingsSetToFactoryDefaults
xATSSwitchSettingsSetToFactoryDefaults.description: Sets all transfer switch settings to factory default values.

xATSSwitchTimersTableSize.name: xATSSwitchTimersTableSize
xATSSwitchTimersTableSize.description: The number of transfer switch timer entries.

xATSSwitchTimersTable.name: xATSSwitchTimersTable
xATSSwitchTimersTable.description: A list of timers supported by ATS. The number of entries is contained in the xATSSwitchTimersTableSize OID.

xATSSwitchTimersEntry.name: xATSSwitchTimersEntry
xATSSwitchTimersEntry.description: An entry containing information about an individual ATS timer.

xATSSwitchTimersIndex.name: xATSSwitchTimersIndex
xATSSwitchTimersIndex.description: Index of timer entries in the table.

xATSSwitchTimersName.name: xATSSwitchTimersName
xATSSwitchTimersName.description: Name of the individual timer.Refer to ATS operation manual, or on-line help, for detailed descriptions of ATS timers.

xATSSwitchTimersStatus.name: xATSSwitchTimersStatus
xATSSwitchTimersStatus.description: The status of the individual timer. Designates whether this timer entry is currently running or inactive.

xATSSwitchTimersRemainingTime.name: xATSSwitchTimersRemainingTime
xATSSwitchTimersRemainingTime.description: The time remaining for this timer entry. Specified in seconds.

xATSSwitchTimersDelaySetting.name: xATSSwitchTimersDelaySetting
xATSSwitchTimersDelaySetting.description: The delay settings associated with this timer entry. When this timer entry is active, the timer value must exceed this setting before the ATS behavior associated with this timer is executed. Refer to ATS operation manual, or on-line help, for detailed descriptions of ATS timers.

xATSSwitchBlockMapTableSize.name: xATSSwitchBlockMapTableSize
xATSSwitchBlockMapTableSize.description: The number of blocking map entries, or how many ATS actions can be blocked.

xATSSwitchBlockMapTable.name: xATSSwitchBlockMapTable
xATSSwitchBlockMapTable.description: A list of blocking maps supported by the ATS. The number of entries is contained in the xATSSwitchBlockMapTableSize OID.

xATSSwitchBlockMapEntry.name: xATSSwitchBlockMapEntry
xATSSwitchBlockMapEntry.description: An entry containing information about a specific ATS blocking map.

xATSSwitchBlockMapIndex.name: xATSSwitchBlockMapIndex
xATSSwitchBlockMapIndex.description: Index of blocking map entries in the table.

xATSSwitchBlockMapName.name: xATSSwitchBlockMapName
xATSSwitchBlockMapName.description: A string describing the ATS action to be blocked.

xATSSwitchBlockMapStatus.name: xATSSwitchBlockMapStatus
xATSSwitchBlockMapStatus.description: Represents the status of this blocking map entry, in bit-mapped format. A non-zero value indicates that this entry's ATS action is currently being blocked. The bit(s) set indicate which input(s) are causing the blocking (bit0, bit1, etc). bit 0 - Contact 1 bit 1 - Contact 2 bit 2 - Contact 3 bit 3 - Contact 4.

xATSSwitchBlockMapSetting.name: xATSSwitchBlockMapSetting
xATSSwitchBlockMapSetting.description: This setting designates the inputs that block the ATS action The mapping is specified as a bit-field, where each bit set indicates the input that blocks the ATS action associated with the entry. bit 0 - Contact 1 bit 1 - Contact 2 bit 2 - Contact 3 bit 3 - Contact 4.

xATSSwitchStatisticsTableSize.name: xATSSwitchStatisticsTableSize
xATSSwitchStatisticsTableSize.description: The number of transfer switch statistics entries.

xATSSwitchStatisticsTable.name: xATSSwitchStatisticsTable
xATSSwitchStatisticsTable.description: A list of statistics supported by ATS. The number of entries is contained in the xATSSwitchStatisticsTableSize OID.

xATSSwitchStatisticsEntry.name: xATSSwitchStatisticsEntry
xATSSwitchStatisticsEntry.description: An entry containing information about an individual ATS statistic.

xATSSwitchStatisticsIndex.name: xATSSwitchStatisticsIndex
xATSSwitchStatisticsIndex.description: Index of ATS statistics entries in the table.

xATSSwitchStatisticsName.name: xATSSwitchStatisticsName
xATSSwitchStatisticsName.description: This is the name of the ATS statistic associated with this entry.

xATSSwitchStatisticsValue.name: xATSSwitchStatisticsValue
xATSSwitchStatisticsValue.description: This is the value of the ATS statistic associated with this entry.

xATSSwitchStatisticsReset.name: xATSSwitchStatisticsReset
xATSSwitchStatisticsReset.description: This will reset the individual ATS statistic associated with this entry.

xATSSource1Position.name: xATSSource1Position
xATSSource1Position.description: The current position of the switch at source 1.

xATSSource1Frequency.name: xATSSource1Frequency
xATSSource1Frequency.description: The frequency at source 1 in tenths of Hertz. -1 if unavailable.

xATSSource1Quality.name: xATSSource1Quality
xATSSource1Quality.description: The current line quality of source 1.

xATSSource1Rotation.name: xATSSource1Rotation
xATSSource1Rotation.description: The phase rotation measured at the source 1 input of the ATS. The sequence is a reference to the order in which the three phases pass the zero-crossing boundary in time.

xATSSource1TableSize.name: xATSSource1TableSize
xATSSource1TableSize.description: The number of input voltage entries at the source 1 input of the ATS.

xATSSource1PhaseTable.name: xATSSource1PhaseTable
xATSSource1PhaseTable.description: A list of voltage table entries for source 1. The number of entries are the phase entries. The number of entries is contained in the xATSSource1TableSize OID.

xATSSource1PhaseEntry.name: xATSSource1PhaseEntry
xATSSource1PhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular input voltage phase at the source 1 input of the ATS.

xATSSource1Index.name: xATSSource1Index
xATSSource1Index.description: Description of each phase utilized at source 1.

xATSSource1VoltageLtoL.name: xATSSource1VoltageLtoL
xATSSource1VoltageLtoL.description: Source 1 line-to-line input voltage. Measured in tenths of Volts.

xATSSource1VoltageLtoN.name: xATSSource1VoltageLtoN
xATSSource1VoltageLtoN.description: Source 1 line-to-neutral input voltage. Measured in tenths of Volts. -1 for a 3-wire service type.

xATSSource2Position.name: xATSSource2Position
xATSSource2Position.description: The current position of the switch at source 2.

xATSSource2Frequency.name: xATSSource2Frequency
xATSSource2Frequency.description: The frequency at source 2 in tenths of Hertz. -1 if not available.

xATSSource2Quality.name: xATSSource2Quality
xATSSource2Quality.description: The current line quality of source 2.

xATSSource2Rotation.name: xATSSource2Rotation
xATSSource2Rotation.description: The phase rotation measured at the source 2 input of the ATS. -1 if not available.

xATSSource2TableSize.name: xATSSource2TableSize
xATSSource2TableSize.description: The number of input voltage entries at the source 2 input of the ATS.

xATSSource2PhaseTable.name: xATSSource2PhaseTable
xATSSource2PhaseTable.description: A list of voltage table entries for the source 2. The number of entries are the phase entries. The number of entries is contained in the xATSSource2TableSize OID.

xATSSource2PhaseEntry.name: xATSSource2PhaseEntry
xATSSource2PhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular input voltage phase at the source 2 input of the ATS.

xATSSource2Index.name: xATSSource2Index
xATSSource2Index.description: Description of each phase utilized at the source 2.

xATSSource2VoltageLtoL.name: xATSSource2VoltageLtoL
xATSSource2VoltageLtoL.description: Source 2 line-to-line input voltage. Measured in tenths of Volts.

xATSSource2VoltageLtoN.name: xATSSource2VoltageLtoN
xATSSource2VoltageLtoN.description: Source 2 line-to-neutral input voltage. Measured in tenths of Volts. -1 for a 3-wire service type.

xATSSystemOutputFrequency.name: xATSSystemOutputFrequency
xATSSystemOutputFrequency.description: The system output frequency in tenths of Hertz.

xATSSystemOutputTotalPower.name: xATSSystemOutputTotalPower
xATSSystemOutputTotalPower.description: Shows the total system output power in tenths of kW.

xATSSystemOutputTotalApparentPower.name: xATSSystemOutputTotalApparentPower
xATSSystemOutputTotalApparentPower.description: Shows the total system output power in tenths of kVA.

xATSSystemOutputTotalPowerFactor.name: xATSSystemOutputTotalPowerFactor
xATSSystemOutputTotalPowerFactor.description: Indicates the total power factor of the system output. A value of 100 representing a unity power factor (1.00) Specified in hundredths.

xATSSystemOutputFrequencyTolerance.name: xATSSystemOutputFrequencyTolerance
xATSSystemOutputFrequencyTolerance.description: Shows the panel output frequency tolerance in +/- Hertz.

xATSSystemOutputOverVoltThreshold.name: xATSSystemOutputOverVoltThreshold
xATSSystemOutputOverVoltThreshold.description: Threshold above which an output over voltage condition will be generated. Specified as tenths of percent deviation from nominal. A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

xATSSystemOutputUnderVoltThreshold.name: xATSSystemOutputUnderVoltThreshold
xATSSystemOutputUnderVoltThreshold.description: Threshold below which an output under voltage condition will be generated. Specified as tenths of percent deviation from nominal. A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

xATSSystemOutputOverCurrentThreshold.name: xATSSystemOutputOverCurrentThreshold
xATSSystemOutputOverCurrentThreshold.description: Threshold above which an over current condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the transfer switch rating (xATSDeviceTransferSwitchRating OID). A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

xATSSystemOutputUnderCurrentThreshold.name: xATSSystemOutputUnderCurrentThreshold
xATSSystemOutputUnderCurrentThreshold.description: Threshold below which an under current condition will be generated. Specified as a percent of the transfer switch rating (xATSDeviceTransferSwitchRating OID). A value of zero indicates that the threshold is disabled.

xATSSystemOutputAlarmDelayThreshold.name: xATSSystemOutputAlarmDelayThreshold
xATSSystemOutputAlarmDelayThreshold.description: Delay the generation of an output alarm. Specified in seconds.

xATSSystemOutputTableSize.name: xATSSystemOutputTableSize
xATSSystemOutputTableSize.description: The number of system output phase entries.

xATSSystemOutputPhaseTable.name: xATSSystemOutputPhaseTable
xATSSystemOutputPhaseTable.description: A list of system output table entries. The number of entries is contained in the xATSSystemOutputTableSize OID.

xATSSystemOutputPhaseEntry.name: xATSSystemOutputPhaseEntry
xATSSystemOutputPhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular system output phase.

xATSSystemOutputPhaseIndex.name: xATSSystemOutputPhaseIndex
xATSSystemOutputPhaseIndex.description: Description of each system output phase utilized in this device.

xATSSystemOutputVoltageLtoL.name: xATSSystemOutputVoltageLtoL
xATSSystemOutputVoltageLtoL.description: Line-to-line system output voltage available at the circuit panel. Measured in tenths of Volts. -1 if not available.

xATSSystemOutputVoltageLtoN.name: xATSSystemOutputVoltageLtoN
xATSSystemOutputVoltageLtoN.description: Line-to-neutral system output voltage available at the circuit panel. Measured in tenths of Volts. -1 for a 3-wire service type or if not available.

xATSSystemOutputPhaseCurrent.name: xATSSystemOutputPhaseCurrent
xATSSystemOutputPhaseCurrent.description: System load current per phase. Measured in Amps. -1 if not available.

xATSSystemOutputPower.name: xATSSystemOutputPower
xATSSystemOutputPower.description: System output power per phase. Measured in tenths of kW.

xATSSystemOutputApparentPower.name: xATSSystemOutputApparentPower
xATSSystemOutputApparentPower.description: system output power per phase. Measured in tenths of kVA.

xATSSystemOutputPowerFactor.name: xATSSystemOutputPowerFactor
xATSSystemOutputPowerFactor.description: indicates the power factor of the system output per phase. A value of 100 representing a unity power factor (1.00). Measured in hundredths.

xATSTestingStatusSelectTestProcess.name: xATSTestingStatusSelectTestProcess
xATSTestingStatusSelectTestProcess.description: Type of tests that can be selected when no test has been scheduled. engineStartTest and systemLoadTest may be selected when no tests are running. Tests that are selected may be canceled manually.

xATSTestingStatusProfileWarmupTime.name: xATSTestingStatusProfileWarmupTime
xATSTestingStatusProfileWarmupTime.description: The amount of time that the generator will warm up during a test. This is portion of the test when the xATSTestingStatusTestStatus OID returns the value engineWarmingUp. Specified in seconds.

xATSTestingStatusProfileLoadedTime.name: xATSTestingStatusProfileLoadedTime
xATSTestingStatusProfileLoadedTime.description: The amount of time that ATS will apply the system load to the generator during a system load test. This is portion of the test when the xATSTestingStatusTestStatus OID returns the value testingWithLoad. Specified in minutes.

xATSTestingStatusProfileUnloadedTime.name: xATSTestingStatusProfileUnloadedTime
xATSTestingStatusProfileUnloadedTime.description: The amount of time that the generator will run following the warm up portion of a start test, or the loaded portion of a load test. This is portion of the test when the xATSTestingStatusTestStatus OID returns the value testingWithoutLoad. Specified in seconds.

xATSTestingResultsLastDateOfTest.name: xATSTestingResultsLastDateOfTest
xATSTestingResultsLastDateOfTest.description: Date of the last test that was performed, either scheduled or manual. Test results are available in the xATSTestingResultsLastResult OID. Specified in the dd/mm/yyyy format, or 'none' if not available.

xATSTestingResultsLastResult.name: xATSTestingResultsLastResult
xATSTestingResultsLastResult.description: The result of the last ATS/generator system test.

xATSTestingResultsTestLastTestTime.name: xATSTestingResultsTestLastTestTime
xATSTestingResultsTestLastTestTime.description: Time of day at which the last test was performed, either scheduled or manual. Test results are available in the xATSTestingResultsLastResult OID. Specified in the hh:mm:ss format, or 'none' if not available.

xATSTestingResultsLastCrankDuration.name: xATSTestingResultsLastCrankDuration
xATSTestingResultsLastCrankDuration.description: The time spent cranking the generator before it started during the last test. Specified in seconds, or -1 if not available.

xATSTestingResultsLastWarmupDuration.name: xATSTestingResultsLastWarmupDuration
xATSTestingResultsLastWarmupDuration.description: The time spent in the engineWarmingUp state during the last system test. Specified in seconds, or -1 if not available.

xATSTestingResultsLastLoadedDuration.name: xATSTestingResultsLastLoadedDuration
xATSTestingResultsLastLoadedDuration.description: The time spent in the testingWithLoad state during the last system test. Specified in seconds, or -1 if not available.

xATSTestingResultsLastUnloadedDuration.name: xATSTestingResultsLastUnloadedDuration
xATSTestingResultsLastUnloadedDuration.description: The time spent in the testingWithoutLoad state during the last system test. Specified in seconds, or -1 if not available.

xATSTestingScheduleFrequency.name: xATSTestingScheduleFrequency
xATSTestingScheduleFrequency.description: The frequency of running scheduled tests.

xATSTestingScheduleTestDay.name: xATSTestingScheduleTestDay
xATSTestingScheduleTestDay.description: The desired day for the scheduled test. This object applies only when the xATSTestingScheduleFrequency OID is set to weekly or monthly. For weekly test frequency, the string is the day the test will be run. For monthly test frequency, the string indicates the day, and the instance within the month. For example, for monthly frequency: 2nd Sunday, 3rd Monday, 4th Tuesday, for weekly frequency: Sunday, Monday, Tuesday.

xATSTestingScheduleTestTime.name: xATSTestingScheduleTestTime
xATSTestingScheduleTestTime.description: The time of day that the scheduled test will occur. Specified in the format hh:mm.

xATSTestingScheduleTestWithLoadInterval.name: xATSTestingScheduleTestWithLoadInterval
xATSTestingScheduleTestWithLoadInterval.description: This setting specifies which system tests should include applying the load to the generator. The applyLoadMonthlyDetailed entry in the list will apply load once, for each month represented in the xATSTestingScheduleTestWithLoadSelectMonth OID.

xATSTestingScheduleTestWithLoadSelectMon.name: xATSTestingScheduleTestWithLoadSelectMonth
xATSTestingScheduleTestWithLoadSelectMon.description: The detailed selection for testing with load on a month-by-month basis. This object is applicable when the xATSTestingScheduleTestWithLoadInterval is set to applyLoadMonthlyDetailed. Otherwise this selection will be ignored. Format for this string is a comma-separated entry of months. For example: Jan,Mar,Dec. The string will return 'No Months Scheduled' if no months have been selected.

xATSTestingScheduleNextTestDate.name: xATSTestingScheduleNextTestDate
xATSTestingScheduleNextTestDate.description: The date of the next scheduled test, in the format dd-mmm-yyyy.

xATSTestingSimulatePowerFailTest.name: xATSTestingSimulatePowerFailTest
xATSTestingSimulatePowerFailTest.description: This object executes a simulated power failure for the duration indicated. Simulation can be aborted by selecting cancelSimulation.

xATSTestingSimulatePowerFailTimeRemainin.name: xATSTestingSimulatePowerFailTimeRemaining
xATSTestingSimulatePowerFailTimeRemainin.description: Indicates the time remaining in seconds, for a simulated power failure. a value of zero indicates that simulated power failure is not active.

xATSInputContactNumContacts.name: xATSInputContactNumContacts
xATSInputContactNumContacts.description: The number of contacts supported by the ATS.

xATSInputContactTableSize.name: xATSInputContactTableSize
xATSInputContactTableSize.description: The number of input contact entries.

xATSInputContactTable.name: xATSInputContactTable
xATSInputContactTable.description: A list of contacts supported by the ATS. The number of entries is contained in the xATSInputContactTableSize OID.

xATSInputContactEntry.name: xATSInputContactEntry
xATSInputContactEntry.description: A contact entry containing information for a given contact.

xATSInputContactNumber.name: xATSInputContactNumber
xATSInputContactNumber.description: An index identifying the contact on the ATS.

xATSInputContactName.name: xATSInputContactName
xATSInputContactName.description: The description of the purpose/use of the contact.

xATSInputContactNormalState.name: xATSInputContactNormalState
xATSInputContactNormalState.description: The normal operating position of the contact.

xATSInputContactCurrentState.name: xATSInputContactCurrentState
xATSInputContactCurrentState.description: This value indicates the current state of the contact.

xATSOutputRelayNumRelays.name: xATSOutputRelayNumRelays
xATSOutputRelayNumRelays.description: The number of output relays supported by the ATS.

xATSOutputRelayTableSize.name: xATSOutputRelayTableSize
xATSOutputRelayTableSize.description: The number of output relay entries.

xATSOutputRelayTable.name: xATSOutputRelayTable
xATSOutputRelayTable.description: A list of output relays supported by the ATS. The number of entries is contained in the xATSOutputRelayTableSize OID.

xATSOutputRelayEntry.name: xATSOutputRelayEntry
xATSOutputRelayEntry.description: A output relay entry containing information for a given contact.

xATSOutputRelayNumber.name: xATSOutputRelayNumber
xATSOutputRelayNumber.description: An index identifying the output relay on the ATS.

xATSOutputRelayName.name: xATSOutputRelayName
xATSOutputRelayName.description: The description of the purpose/use of the output relay.

xATSOutputRelayNormalState.name: xATSOutputRelayNormalState
xATSOutputRelayNormalState.description: The normal operating position of the output relay.

xATSOutputRelayCurrentState.name: xATSOutputRelayCurrentState
xATSOutputRelayCurrentState.description: This value indicates the current state of the output relay.

xATSGeneratorIdentModelNumber.name: xATSGeneratorIdentModelNumber
xATSGeneratorIdentModelNumber.description: A character string identifying the model number of the generator. This value is set at the factory.

xATSGeneratorIdentSerialNumber.name: xATSGeneratorIdentSerialNumber
xATSGeneratorIdentSerialNumber.description: A character string identifying the serial number of the generator. This value is set at the factory.

xATSGeneratorIdentDateofManufacture.name: xATSGeneratorIdentDateofManufacture
xATSGeneratorIdentDateofManufacture.description: A character string identifying when the generator was manufactured in mm/dd/yyyy format. This value is set at the factory.

xATSGeneratorIdentVoltageConfiguration.name: xATSGeneratorIdentVoltageConfiguration
xATSGeneratorIdentVoltageConfiguration.description: The voltage for which the generator's alternator is designed. Specified in Volts line-to-line.

xATSGeneratorIdentMaxPowerRating.name: xATSGeneratorIdentMaxPowerRating
xATSGeneratorIdentMaxPowerRating.description: The max power rating of the generator. Specified in kW.

xATSGeneratorIdentAlternatorFrequency.name: xATSGeneratorIdentAlternatorFrequency
xATSGeneratorIdentAlternatorFrequency.description: The frequency for which the generator's alternator is designed. Specified in Hertz.

xATSGeneratorStatusGeneratorName.name: xATSGeneratorStatusGeneratorName
xATSGeneratorStatusGeneratorName.description: The name or label for the generator connected to the source 2 of the ATS.

xATSGeneratorStatusOperational.name: xATSGeneratorStatusOperational
xATSGeneratorStatusOperational.description: The operational status of the generator. unavailable when unrecognized status is received.

xATSGeneratorStatusModeSwitchPosition.name: xATSGeneratorStatusModeSwitchPosition
xATSGeneratorStatusModeSwitchPosition.description: The position of the generator's auto-mode switch. In automatic mode, the generator is started and stopped via the remote start contact, which has state indicated in the xATSGeneratorStatusRemoteStart OID. In manual mode generator start/stop control is via local command only. Off prevents the generator from running.

xATSGeneratorStatusRemoteStart.name: xATSGeneratorStatusRemoteStart
xATSGeneratorStatusRemoteStart.description: The status of the generator's remote start contact, which is provided as an output from the transfer switch to start/stop the generator when in automatic mode.

xATSGeneratorAdvStatusBatteryVoltage.name: xATSGeneratorAdvStatusBatteryVoltage
xATSGeneratorAdvStatusBatteryVoltage.description: The voltage of the generator's starting battery. Measured in tenths of VDC, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorAdvStatusOilPressure.name: xATSGeneratorAdvStatusOilPressure
xATSGeneratorAdvStatusOilPressure.description: The generator's engine oil pressure. Measured in tenths of Psi or kPa, based on the value of the xATSGeneratorSettingsMetricUnit OID, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorAdvStatusCoolantTemperature.name: xATSGeneratorAdvStatusCoolantTemperature
xATSGeneratorAdvStatusCoolantTemperature.description: Current coolant temperature in the generator. Measured in degrees Celsius or Fahrenheit, based on the value of the xATSGeneratorSettingsMetricUnit OID, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorAdvStatusEngineRPM.name: xATSGeneratorAdvStatusEngineRPM
xATSGeneratorAdvStatusEngineRPM.description: Current engine speed of the generator. Measured in RPM, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorAdvStatusOilLevel.name: xATSGeneratorAdvStatusOilLevel
xATSGeneratorAdvStatusOilLevel.description: Indicates adequate oil level in the generator.

xATSGeneratorAdvStatusCoolantLevel.name: xATSGeneratorAdvStatusCoolantLevel
xATSGeneratorAdvStatusCoolantLevel.description: Indicates adequate coolant level in the generator.

xATSGeneratorOutputFrequency.name: xATSGeneratorOutputFrequency
xATSGeneratorOutputFrequency.description: The output frequency of the generator. Measured in tenths of Hertz, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputTotalPower.name: xATSGeneratorOutputTotalPower
xATSGeneratorOutputTotalPower.description: The total output power of the generator. Measured in tenths of tenths of kW, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputTotalApparentPower.name: xATSGeneratorOutputTotalApparentPower
xATSGeneratorOutputTotalApparentPower.description: The total output power of the generator. Measured in tenths of kVA, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputTotalPowerFactor.name: xATSGeneratorOutputTotalPowerFactor
xATSGeneratorOutputTotalPowerFactor.description: Indicates the total load power factor of the generator. A value of 100 representing a unity power factor (1.00), or -1 when if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputTableSize.name: xATSGeneratorOutputTableSize
xATSGeneratorOutputTableSize.description: The number of generator output phase entries.

xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseTable.name: xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseTable
xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseTable.description: A list of generator output table entries. The number of entries is contained in the xATSGeneratorOutputTableSize OID.

xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseEntry.name: xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseEntry
xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular generator output phase.

xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseIndex.name: xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseIndex
xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseIndex.description: Description of each generator output phase utilized in this device.

xATSGeneratorOutputVoltageLtoL.name: xATSGeneratorOutputVoltageLtoL
xATSGeneratorOutputVoltageLtoL.description: Line-to-line generator output voltage. Measured in Volts, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputVoltageLtoN.name: xATSGeneratorOutputVoltageLtoN
xATSGeneratorOutputVoltageLtoN.description: Line-to-neutral generator output voltage. Measured in volts, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseCurrent.name: xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseCurrent
xATSGeneratorOutputPhaseCurrent.description: Generator load current per phase. Measured in Amps, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputPower.name: xATSGeneratorOutputPower
xATSGeneratorOutputPower.description: Generator output power per phase. Measured in tenths of kW, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputApparentPower.name: xATSGeneratorOutputApparentPower
xATSGeneratorOutputApparentPower.description: Generator output power per phase. Measured in tenths of kVA, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorOutputPowerFactor.name: xATSGeneratorOutputPowerFactor
xATSGeneratorOutputPowerFactor.description: Indicates the load power factor of the generator output per phase. A value of 100 representing a unity power factor (1.00), or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorSettingsVoltageAdjust.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsVoltageAdjust
xATSGeneratorSettingsVoltageAdjust.description: The voltage adjust of the generator. Specified in volts line-to-line, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorSettingsFrequencyAdjust.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsFrequencyAdjust
xATSGeneratorSettingsFrequencyAdjust.description: The frequency adjust of the generator. Specified in tenths of Hertz.

xATSGeneratorSettingsStartDelay.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsStartDelay
xATSGeneratorSettingsStartDelay.description: The delay, in seconds, after the remote run signal is activated before the generator's engine will be cranked to start, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorSettingsStopDelay.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsStopDelay
xATSGeneratorSettingsStopDelay.description: The delay, in seconds, before the generator will stop after the remote run signal is deactivated, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankCycleEnable.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankCycleEnable
xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankCycleEnable.description: When Crank Cycle is enabled, the engine will be cranked up to the time specified by the xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankTime OID. If the generator's engine does not start, there will be a pause as specified by the xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankRestTime OID before the engine will be cranked again. This cycle is repeated as specified by the xATSGeneratorSettingsNumberCrank OID. When crank cycle is disabled, the generator's engine will be cranked continuously until it starts.

xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankTime.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankTime
xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankTime.description: The duration of engine cranking, in seconds, when starting the generator. Applicable when the xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankCycleEnable OID is enabled. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankRestTime.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankRestTime
xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankRestTime.description: The pause duration, in seconds, following an unsuccessful attempt to start the generator. Applicable when the xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankCycleEnable OID is enabled. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorSettingsNumberCrank.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsNumberCrank
xATSGeneratorSettingsNumberCrank.description: The number of failed crank attempts before giving up on starting the generator. Applicable when the xATSGeneratorSettingsCrankCycleEnable OID is enabled. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorSettingsMetricUnit.name: xATSGeneratorSettingsMetricUnit
xATSGeneratorSettingsMetricUnit.description: Specifies the use of metric units in generator related OIDs, as well as on all other interfaces including the generator's local interface.

xATSGeneratorServiceTotalRunHoursLifetim.name: xATSGeneratorServiceTotalRunHoursLifetime
xATSGeneratorServiceTotalRunHoursLifetim.description: Total time that the generator engine has been run, over the life of the generator. Measured in hours. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorServiceEngineStartsLifetime.name: xATSGeneratorServiceEngineStartsLifetime
xATSGeneratorServiceEngineStartsLifetime.description: Number of engine starts over the life of the generator. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorServiceTotalkWhLifetime.name: xATSGeneratorServiceTotalkWhLifetime
xATSGeneratorServiceTotalkWhLifetime.description: Total kWh of operation over the life of the generator. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorServiceTotalRunHoursSinceMa.name: xATSGeneratorServiceTotalRunHoursSinceMaintenance
xATSGeneratorServiceTotalRunHoursSinceMa.description: Total time that the generator engine has been run, since last service maintenance. Measured in tenths of hours. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorServiceEngineStartsSinceMai.name: xATSGeneratorServiceEngineStartsSinceMaintenance
xATSGeneratorServiceEngineStartsSinceMai.description: Number of engine starts since last service maintenance. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorServiceTotalkWhMaintenance.name: xATSGeneratorServiceTotalkWhMaintenance
xATSGeneratorServiceTotalkWhMaintenance.description: Total kWh of operation since last service maintenance. -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorServiceResetRecord.name: xATSGeneratorServiceResetRecord
xATSGeneratorServiceResetRecord.description: Resets the engine start counter, engine run-hours, and kWh values that have accumulated in the generator since last maintenance. Also, the last service date will be reset to the current system date, and any service alarms will be cleared.

xATSGeneratorServiceRecordResetDate.name: xATSGeneratorServiceRecordResetDate
xATSGeneratorServiceRecordResetDate.description: Date at which the generator's service record was reset, in dd-mmm-yyyy format.

xATSGeneratorServiceNextServiceDate.name: xATSGeneratorServiceNextServiceDate
xATSGeneratorServiceNextServiceDate.description: Date at which the next generator service is due in dd-mmm-yyyy format. Based on the xATSGeneratorServiceCalendarIntervalThreshold OID or '' if the calendar-based threshold is set to off.

xATSGeneratorServiceRunHoursUntilService.name: xATSGeneratorServiceRunHoursUntilServiceDate
xATSGeneratorServiceRunHoursUntilService.description: Run hours until the next generator service is due, in hours. Based on the xATSGeneratorServiceRunHoursThreshold OID or -1 if the run hour-based threshold is set to off.

xATSGeneratorServiceRunHoursThreshold.name: xATSGeneratorServiceRunHoursThreshold
xATSGeneratorServiceRunHoursThreshold.description: Run hour-based service interval. When the run-hours since service surpasses this threshold, generator service is due.

xATSGeneratorServiceCalendarIntervalThre.name: xATSGeneratorServiceCalendarIntervalThreshold
xATSGeneratorServiceCalendarIntervalThre.description: Calendar-based service interval. When the next service date, as indicated by the xATSGeneratorServiceNextServiceDate OID is in the past, generator is due for service.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemType.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemType
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemType.description: The type of fuel used by the generator.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemTankSize.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemTankSize
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemTankSize.description: Size of the generator's fuel tank. Specified in gallons or liters, based on the value of the xATSGeneratorSettingsMetricUnit OID, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemFuelLevel.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemFuelLevel
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemFuelLevel.description: Fuel remaining in the generator tank. Measured in percent of tank fill, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemRuntimePower.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemRuntimePower
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemRuntimePower.description: The power value used in the runtime remaining calculation. Measured in tenths of kW, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemEstimatedRunTime.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemEstimatedRunTime
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemEstimatedRunTime.description: An estimate of available runtime for the generator, based on available fuel as specified in the xATSGeneratorFuelSystemFuelLevel OID and kW load as specified in the xATSGeneratorFuelSystemRuntimePower OID. Measured in tenths of hours, or -1 if not available.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemLowRunTimeThresho.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemLowRunTimeThreshold
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemLowRunTimeThresho.description: Threshold below which a low runtime alarm will exist.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemVeryLowRunTimeThr.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemVeryLowRunTimeThreshold
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemVeryLowRunTimeThr.description: Threshold below which a very low runtime alarm will exist.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemLowFuelLevelThres.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemLowFuelLevelThreshold
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemLowFuelLevelThres.description: Threshold below which a low fuel alarm will exist, with a value of 0 indicating disabled. Specified as percent of tank fill.

xATSGeneratorFuelSystemVeryLowFuelLevelT.name: xATSGeneratorFuelSystemVeryLowFuelLevelThreshold
xATSGeneratorFuelSystemVeryLowFuelLevelT.description: Threshold below which a very low fuel alarm will exist, with a value of 0 indicating disabled. Specified as percent of tank fill.

apCPSPwNum.name: apCPSPwNum
apCPSPwNum.description: The number of the power supplies.

apCPSPw1.name: apCPSPw1
apCPSPw1.description: State of the first power supply. 0 will indicate not installed, 1 will indicate power ON, 2 will indicate power OFF.

apCPSPw2.name: apCPSPw2
apCPSPw2.description: State of the second power supply. 0 will indicate not installed, 1 will indicate power ON, 2 will indicate power OFF.

cpsCardIdentTable.name: cpsCardIdentTable
cpsCardIdentTable.description: A table of PCMCIA card identifications.

cpsCardIdentEntry.name: cpsCardIdentEntry
cpsCardIdentEntry.description: Identification information for a PCMCIA card.

cpsCardIdentIndex.name: cpsCardIdentIndex
cpsCardIdentIndex.description: Number to identify the socket Card.

cpsCardConfTable.name: cpsCardConfTable
cpsCardConfTable.description: A table of socket configuration information.

cpsCardConfIndex.name: cpsCardConfIndex
cpsCardConfIndex.description: Number to identify the socket PCMCIA.

cpsCardStatusTable.name: cpsCardStatusTable
cpsCardStatusTable.description: A table of current socket status information.

cpsCardStatusEntry.name: cpsCardStatusEntry
cpsCardStatusEntry.description: Current status information for a socket.

cpsCardStatusIndex.name: cpsCardStatusIndex
cpsCardStatusIndex.description: Number to identify the socket PCMCIA.

apCPSFlashSize.name: apCPSFlashSize
apCPSFlashSize.description: Total amount of flash memory in Mbytes.

apCPSRAMSize.name: apCPSRAMSize
apCPSRAMSize.description: Total amount of RAM in Mbytes.

cpsEthDhcpc.name: cpsEthDhcpc
cpsEthDhcpc.description: 0 will indicate DHCP inactive, 1 will indicate DHCP active, 2 will indicate DHCP active and the last parameter is saved.

cpsEthIPaddr.name: cpsEthIPaddr
cpsEthIPaddr.description: This is the IP address of the Ethernet Interface.

cpsEthIPmask.name: cpsEthIPmask
cpsEthIPmask.description: The mask for the Ethernet network.

cpsEthMTU.name: cpsEthMTU
cpsEthMTU.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit size, which determines whether packets should be broken up.

cpsResolverOrder.name: cpsResolverOrder
cpsResolverOrder.description: Specifies how host lookups are to be performed. Valid values : empty, 'hosts', 'bind', 'hosts, bind', 'bind, hosts'

cpsMultipleIP.name: cpsMultipleIP
cpsMultipleIP.description: Valid values are ON or OFF. If set to ON, the resolve library will return all valid addresses for a host that appears in the /etc/hosts file, instead of only the first.

cpsDNSpriserv.name: cpsDNSpriserv
cpsDNSpriserv.description: Internet Address (in dot notation) of primary name server that the resolver should query.

cpsDNSsecserv.name: cpsDNSsecserv
cpsDNSsecserv.description: Internet Address (in dot notation) of secondary name server that the resolver should query.

cpsSerialNFS.name: cpsSerialNFS
cpsSerialNFS.description: Remote Network File System where data buffering will be written instead of the default directory '/var/run/DB'.

cpsSerialRlogin.name: cpsSerialRlogin
cpsSerialRlogin.description: Location of the rlogin binary that accepts the -i flag.

cpsSerialLocalLogins.name: cpsSerialLocalLogins
cpsSerialLocalLogins.description: This parameter is only necessary when authentication is being performed for a port. This is useful if the Radius authentication server is down. 0 indicates OFF, 1 indicates ON.

cpsSerialFacility.name: cpsSerialFacility
cpsSerialFacility.description: This value (0-7) is the Local facility sent to the syslog daemon.

cpsSerialDBFacility.name: cpsSerialDBFacility
cpsSerialDBFacility.description: This value (0-7) is the Local facility sent to the syslog daemon.

cpsSerialPortTable.name: cpsSerialPortTable
cpsSerialPortTable.description: This is the specific configuration per serial port.

cpsSerialPortNumber.name: cpsSerialPortNumber
cpsSerialPortNumber.description: Number to identify the serial port. Value 0 is ALL.

cpsSerialPortTty.name: cpsSerialPortTty
cpsSerialPortTty.description: The device name for the serial port.

cpsSerialPortName.name: cpsSerialPortName
cpsSerialPortName.description: Alias name given to the server connected to the serial port.

cpsSerialPortDataSize.name: cpsSerialPortDataSize
cpsSerialPortDataSize.description: The data size for the serial port.

cpsSerialPortStopBits.name: cpsSerialPortStopBits
cpsSerialPortStopBits.description: The number of stop bits for the serial port.

cpsSerialPortParity.name: cpsSerialPortParity
cpsSerialPortParity.description: The parity for the serial port.

cpsSerialPortFlowCtrl.name: cpsSerialPortFlowCtrl
cpsSerialPortFlowCtrl.description: The flow control for the serial port.

cpsSerialPortDTRdelay.name: cpsSerialPortDTRdelay
cpsSerialPortDTRdelay.description: This specifies how long (in milliseconds) a DTR signal will be turned off before it is turned on again.

cpsSerialPortDCDCtrl.name: cpsSerialPortDCDCtrl
cpsSerialPortDCDCtrl.description: DCD signal controls the connection request. 0 will indicate nocontrol, 1 will indicate control.

cpsSerialPortLogUtmp.name: cpsSerialPortLogUtmp
cpsSerialPortLogUtmp.description: Update the login records in /var/run/utmp file. 0 will indicate inactive, 1 will indicate active.

cpsSerialPortLogWtmp.name: cpsSerialPortLogWtmp
cpsSerialPortLogWtmp.description: Update the login records in /var/run/wtmp file. 0 will indicate inactive, 1 will indicate active.

cpsSerialPortLogform.name: cpsSerialPortLogform
cpsSerialPortLogform.description: This is the format to write the login record.

cpsSerialPortAuthSrv1.name: cpsSerialPortAuthSrv1
cpsSerialPortAuthSrv1.description: IP address of the primary authentication server.

cpsSerialPortAccSrv1.name: cpsSerialPortAccSrv1
cpsSerialPortAccSrv1.description: IP address of the primary accounting server.

cpsSerialPortAuthTmo.name: cpsSerialPortAuthTmo
cpsSerialPortAuthTmo.description: This is the timeout (in seconds) for the authentication query to be answered.

cpsSerialPortAuthRetr.name: cpsSerialPortAuthRetr
cpsSerialPortAuthRetr.description: This defines the number of times each server is tried before another is contacted.

cpsSerialPortAuthSrv2.name: cpsSerialPortAuthSrv2
cpsSerialPortAuthSrv2.description: IP address of the secondary authentication server.

cpsSerialPortAccSrv2.name: cpsSerialPortAccSrv2
cpsSerialPortAccSrv2.description: IP address of the secondary accounting server.

cpsSerialPortAuthSecret.name: cpsSerialPortAuthSecret
cpsSerialPortAuthSecret.description: This is the shared secret with authentication servers.

cpsSerialPortAuthRadP.name: cpsSerialPortAuthRadP
cpsSerialPortAuthRadP.description: Radius state. 0 will indicate inactive, 1 will indicate active.

cpsSerialPortRemoteIP.name: cpsSerialPortRemoteIP
cpsSerialPortRemoteIP.description: This is the default IP address of the serial port.

cpsSerialPortSocketPort.name: cpsSerialPortSocketPort
cpsSerialPortSocketPort.description: This defines an alternative labeling system for the serial port.

cpsSerialPortRemHost.name: cpsSerialPortRemHost
cpsSerialPortRemHost.description: The IP address of the host to which the serial port will connect.

cpsSerialPortPrompt.name: cpsSerialPortPrompt
cpsSerialPortPrompt.description: This defines the login prompt to the serial port.

cpsSerialPortNetMask.name: cpsSerialPortNetMask
cpsSerialPortNetMask.description: The network mask used in dial in connection.

cpsSerialPortPppMtu.name: cpsSerialPortPppMtu
cpsSerialPortPppMtu.description: The PPP MTU - dial in connection.

cpsSerialPortPppMru.name: cpsSerialPortPppMru
cpsSerialPortPppMru.description: The PPP MRU - dial in connection.

cpsSerialPortPppOptions.name: cpsSerialPortPppOptions
cpsSerialPortPppOptions.description: The PPP options when the PPP session is autodetected.

cpsSerialPortPppFoption.name: cpsSerialPortPppFoption
cpsSerialPortPppFoption.description: The PPP forced options when the user has already been authenticated.

cpsSerialPortModemChat.name: cpsSerialPortModemChat
cpsSerialPortModemChat.description: The initchat send to modem connected.

cpsSerialPortSttyCmd.name: cpsSerialPortSttyCmd
cpsSerialPortSttyCmd.description: The tty settings after socket connection is established.

cpsSerialPortSockTx.name: cpsSerialPortSockTx
cpsSerialPortSockTx.description: Defines the delay (in milliseconds) before transmission to the Ethernet of data received through a serial port.

cpsSerialPortSockPoll.name: cpsSerialPortSockPoll
cpsSerialPortSockPoll.description: Keep-alive timer (milliseconds) for the TCP connection.

cpsSerialPortDBsize.name: cpsSerialPortDBsize
cpsSerialPortDBsize.description: Maximum size of the data buffering file.

cpsSerialPortDBtime.name: cpsSerialPortDBtime
cpsSerialPortDBtime.description: Timestamp in data buffering. 0 will indicate inactive, 1 will indicate active.

cpsSerialPortDBmode.name: cpsSerialPortDBmode
cpsSerialPortDBmode.description: Data buffering mode : circ or line.

cpsSerialPortDBsyslog.name: cpsSerialPortDBsyslog
cpsSerialPortDBsyslog.description: Size of the data buffer sent to syslog.

cpsSerialPortDBmenu.name: cpsSerialPortDBmenu
cpsSerialPortDBmenu.description: Menu type for data buffering. 0 will indicate display Menu, 1 will indicate inactive, 2 will indicate DB, 3 will indicate Parc.

cpsSerialPortDBalarm.name: cpsSerialPortDBalarm
cpsSerialPortDBalarm.description: Alarm generation status. 0 will indicate inactive, 1 will indicate active.

cpsSerialPortSniffAdm.name: cpsSerialPortSniffAdm
cpsSerialPortSniffAdm.description: List of admin users allowed to sniff session.

cpsSerialPortSniffEsc.name: cpsSerialPortSniffEsc
cpsSerialPortSniffEsc.description: Escape sequence used in sniff session.

cpsSerialPortTelnetMode.name: cpsSerialPortTelnetMode
cpsSerialPortTelnetMode.description: Mode negotiated by client telnet with the server. 0 will indicate text, 1 will indicate binary.

cpsSerialPortSysBufSess.name: cpsSerialPortSysBufSess
cpsSerialPortSysBufSess.description: Syslog Buffering at all times. 0 will indicate yes, 1 will indicate no.

cpsSerialPortLFSuppress.name: cpsSerialPortLFSuppress
cpsSerialPortLFSuppress.description: LF suppression in socket_server session. 0 will indicate inactive, 1 will indicate active.

cpsSerialPortAutoInput.name: cpsSerialPortAutoInput
cpsSerialPortAutoInput.description: Input string used for auto answer.

cpsSerialPortAutoOutput.name: cpsSerialPortAutoOutput
cpsSerialPortAutoOutput.description: Output string used for auto answer.

cpsInfoSerialPortTable.name: cpsInfoSerialPortTable
cpsInfoSerialPortTable.description: This is the information of the specific serial port.

cpsInfoSerialPortNumber.name: cpsInfoSerialPortNumber
cpsInfoSerialPortNumber.description: Number to identify the serial port.

cpsInfoSerialPortTty.name: cpsInfoSerialPortTty
cpsInfoSerialPortTty.description: The device name for the serial port.

cpsInfoSerialPortName.name: cpsInfoSerialPortName
cpsInfoSerialPortName.description: Alias name given to the server connected to the serial port.

cpsInfoSerialPortTxBytes.name: cpsInfoSerialPortTxBytes
cpsInfoSerialPortTxBytes.description: The number of transmitted bytes by the serial port.

cpsInfoSerialPortRXBytes.name: cpsInfoSerialPortRXBytes
cpsInfoSerialPortRXBytes.description: The number of received bytes by the serial port.

cpsInfoSerialPortSigDTR.name: cpsInfoSerialPortSigDTR
cpsInfoSerialPortSigDTR.description: The state of the DTR signal. 0 will indicate down, 1 will indicate up.

cpsInfoSerialPortSigCD.name: cpsInfoSerialPortSigCD
cpsInfoSerialPortSigCD.description: The state of the DCD signal. 0 will indicate down, 1 will indicate up.

cpsInfoSerialPortSigDSR.name: cpsInfoSerialPortSigDSR
cpsInfoSerialPortSigDSR.description: The state of the DSR signal. 0 will indicate down, 1 will indicate up.

cpsInfoSerialPortSigRTS.name: cpsInfoSerialPortSigRTS
cpsInfoSerialPortSigRTS.description: The state of the RTS signal. 0 will indicate down, 1 will indicate up.

cpsInfoSerialPortSigCTS.name: cpsInfoSerialPortSigCTS
cpsInfoSerialPortSigCTS.description: The state of the CTS signal. 0 will indicate down, 1 will indicate up.

cpsInfoSerialPortSigRI.name: cpsInfoSerialPortSigRI
cpsInfoSerialPortSigRI.description: The state of the RI signal. 0 will indicate down, 1 will indicate up.

apCPSSave.name: apCPSSave
apCPSSave.description: Exec saveconf command. 0 will indicate don't save, 1 will indicate save.

apCPSSerialHUP.name: apCPSSerialHUP
apCPSSerialHUP.description: Exec signal_ras hup command. 0 will indicate no restart, 1 will indicate restart.

accessPXIdentAlarmStatus.name: accessPXIdentAlarmStatus
accessPXIdentAlarmStatus.description: Access PX alarm status 1 = Normal 2 = Warning 3 = Critical.

accessPXIdentProductNumber.name: accessPXIdentProductNumber
accessPXIdentProductNumber.description: The product number of the Access PX.

accessPXIdentHardwareRev.name: accessPXIdentHardwareRev
accessPXIdentHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision number of the Access PX.

accessPXIdentDateOfManufacture.name: accessPXIdentDateOfManufacture
accessPXIdentDateOfManufacture.description: The date of manufacture of the Access PX.

accessPXIdentSerialNumber.name: accessPXIdentSerialNumber
accessPXIdentSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the Access PX.

accessPXConfigCardReaderEnableDisableAct.name: accessPXConfigCardReaderEnableDisableAction
accessPXConfigCardReaderEnableDisableAct.description: Action to disable/enable the card reader.

accessPXConfigAutoRelockTime.name: accessPXConfigAutoRelockTime
accessPXConfigAutoRelockTime.description: Time (10 - 60) in seconds when the door will automatically relock after it has been unlocked and the handle has not been opened.

accessPXConfigCardFormat.name: accessPXConfigCardFormat
accessPXConfigCardFormat.description: Indicates and controls the various card format.

accessPXConfigFrontDoorLockControl.name: accessPXConfigFrontDoorLockControl
accessPXConfigFrontDoorLockControl.description: Control action (unlock, lock) for the front door. Setting this OID will unlock or lock the front door. Getting this OID will respond with the current state of the front door lock which could be 1 = unlocked, 2 = locked, 3 = not installed, 4 = disconnected.

accessPXConfigFrontDoorMaxOpenTime.name: accessPXConfigFrontDoorMaxOpenTime
accessPXConfigFrontDoorMaxOpenTime.description: Time in minutes, (1 - 120), that the front door can be allowed to remain open without generating an alarm condition.

accessPXStatusFrontDoorLock.name: accessPXStatusFrontDoorLock

serverStatus.name: serverStatus
serverStatus.description: The status of the StruxureWare Operations server: 1: The status of the application server is unknown. Check Webmin and if the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 2: Restart the StruxureWare DC Operation server. If the server was part of a cluster, see the StruxureWare DC Operation User Assistance about rejoining the cluster. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 3: No problem. 4: High availability is lost. The StruxureWare DC Operation Application server is running but one or more nodes are not available. If the StruxureWare DC Operation server is part of a cluster, ensure all nodes are running and there is a network connection between the nodes. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 5: Wait for the StruxureWare DC Operation Application server to initialize. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 6: Wait for the StruxureWare DC Operation Application server to finish starting. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 7: This node is running in Disaster Recovery mode. 8: The JBoss postoffice is currently inconsistent. This may be a temporary issue. If the problem persists for more than 10 minutes, contact Technical Support. 9: The JBoss is missing jgroups. This may be a temporary issue. If the problem persists for more than 10 minutes, contact Technical Support.

databaseStatus.name: databaseStatus
databaseStatus.description: The status of the StruxureWare Operations database: 1: The status of the database is unknown. Check Webmin and if the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 2: Restart the StruxureWare DC Operation server. If the server was part of a cluster, see the StruxureWare DC Operation User Assistance about rejoining the cluster. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 3: No problem. 4: High availability is lost. The database is detached from the cluster and does not receive updates. See the StruxureWare DC Operation User Assistance about reattaching the database node to the StruxureWare DC Operation cluster. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 5: The database is catching up with the cluster. Wait for the StruxureWare DC Operation database to retrieve all updates from the master node. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 6: The database is attaching to the cluster. Wait for the StruxureWare Operation database to attach to the cluster. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 7: The database is the master in a cluster. 8: The database is the primary slave in the cluster. All changes on master are synchronously replicated to this node. 9: The database is a secondary slave in the cluster. All changes on master are asynchronously replicated to this node. 10: The database does not replicate its changes to other nodes.

loadBalancerStatus.name: loadBalancerStatus
loadBalancerStatus.description: The status of the StruxureWare Operations load balancer: 1: Load Balancer status is unknown. Check Webmin and if the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 2: Load Balancer stopped. Restart the StruxureWare DC Operation server. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 3: Normal status 4: High availability is lost. The StruxureWare DC Operation Load Balancer is running but one or more nodes are not available. If the StruxureWare DC Operation server is part of a cluster, ensure all nodes are running and there is a network connection between the nodes. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support.

essentialServicesStatus.name: essentialServicesStatus
essentialServicesStatus.description: The status of the StruxureWare Operations essential services: 1: Unknown status. Check Webmin and if the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 2: Essential services are not running on the StruxureWare DC Operation server. Reboot the node and monitor the status page in Webmin. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 3: Normal status 4: The time difference between the StruxureWare DC Operation slave and the master node is too big. Correct the time on the slave to match the time on the master. Consider using an NTP server. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support. 5: The last backup that was attempted on the StruxureWare DC Operation server has failed. Make certain that the system can write to the location specified as backup location. This is particularly relevant for network attached storage. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support.

etlStatus.name: etlStatus
etlStatus.description: The status of the StruxureWare Operations ETL services: 1: Unknown status. Check the network configuration and the server network settings. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support (http://www.apc.com/go/direct/index.cfm?tag=support). 2: Normal status, 3: ETL Transformations have failed and are subsequently stopped. Investigate the cause of the failure. If the problem persists, contact Technical Support (http://www.apc.com/go/direct/index.cfm?tag=support). 4: ETL Transformations are currently paused. 5: ETL Transformations are currently stopped.

upsAdvInputLineFailCause.name: upsAdvInputLineFailCause
upsAdvInputLineFailCause.description: The reason for the occurrence of the last transfer to UPS battery power. The variable is set to: - noTransfer(1) -- if there is no transfer yet. - highLineVoltage(2) -- if the transfer to battery is caused by an over voltage greater than the high transfer voltage. - brownout(3) -- if the duration of the outage is greater than five seconds and the line voltage is between 40% of the rated output voltage and the low transfer voltage. - blackout(4) -- if the duration of the outage is greater than five seconds and the line voltage is between 40% of the rated output voltage and ground. - smallMomentarySag(5) -- if the duration of the outage is less than five seconds and the line voltage is between 40% of the rated output voltage and the low transfer voltage. - deepMomentarySag(6) -- if the duration of the outage is less than five seconds and the line voltage is between 40% of the rated output voltage and ground. The variable is set to - smallMomentarySpike(7) -- if the line failure is caused by a rate of change of input voltage less than ten volts per cycle. - largeMomentarySpike(8) -- if the line failure is caused by a rate of change of input voltage greater than ten volts per cycle. - selfTest(9) -- if the UPS was commanded to do a self test. - rateOfVoltageChange(10) -- if the failure is due to the rate of change of the line voltage.
