sPDUOutletConfigMSPmupsP2LowTemp.name: sPDUOutletConfigMSPmupsP2LowTemp
sPDUOutletConfigMSPmupsP2LowTemp.description: Setting this OID to disableAlarm (1) disables the Probe 2 low temperature alarm for this outlet. Setting this OID to enableAlarm (2) enables the Probe 2 low temperature alarm for this outlet.

sPDUOutletConfigMSPmupsP2HiTemp.name: sPDUOutletConfigMSPmupsP2HiTemp
sPDUOutletConfigMSPmupsP2HiTemp.description: Setting this OID to disableAlarm (1) disables the Probe 2 high temperature alarm for this outlet. Setting this OID to enableAlarm (2) enables the Probe 2 high temperature alarm for this outlet.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPTable.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPTable
sPDUOutletStatusMSPTable.description: Allows for getting of status of individual outlets. The number of entries is contained in the sPDUMasterStatusOutletCount OID.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPEntry.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPEntry
sPDUOutletStatusMSPEntry.description: The outlets to gather status from.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPIndex.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPIndex
sPDUOutletStatusMSPIndex.description: The index to the MasterSwitch MSP.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPName.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPName
sPDUOutletStatusMSPName.description: The name of the MasterSwitch plus. The maximum value is 23 characters. The name is set by using the sPDUMasterConfigMSPName OID.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletIndex.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletIndex
sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletName.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletName
sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum size is 23 characters. The name is set by using the sPDUOutletConfigMSPallOutletName OID. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletState.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletState
sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletState.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the outletStatusMSPOn (1) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the outletStatusMSPOff (2) value will be returned.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPCommandPending.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPCommandPending
sPDUOutletStatusMSPCommandPending.description: Getting this variable will return the command pending state of the outlet. If a command is pending on the outlet, the outletStatusMSPCommandPending (1) value will be returned. If there is not a command pending on the outlet, the outletStatusMSPNoCommandPending (2) will be returned.

sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletCtrlMode.name: sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletCtrlMode
sPDUOutletStatusMSPOutletCtrlMode.description: The Control Mode of the outlet. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

rPDUIdentName.name: rPDUIdentName
rPDUIdentName.description: The name of the Rack PDU. The maximum string size is device dependent.

rPDUIdentHardwareRev.name: rPDUIdentHardwareRev
rPDUIdentHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the Rack PDU. This value is set at the factory.

rPDUIdentFirmwareRev.name: rPDUIdentFirmwareRev
rPDUIdentFirmwareRev.description: An 8-byte ID string identifying the Rack PDU firmware revision. This value is set at the factory.

rPDUIdentDateOfManufacture.name: rPDUIdentDateOfManufacture
rPDUIdentDateOfManufacture.description: The date when the Rack PDU was manufactured in mm/dd/yyyy format. This value is set at the factory. The year 2000 will be represented by 00.

rPDUIdentModelNumber.name: rPDUIdentModelNumber
rPDUIdentModelNumber.description: A 10-character string identifying the model number of the Rack PDU. This value is set at the factory.

rPDUIdentSerialNumber.name: rPDUIdentSerialNumber
rPDUIdentSerialNumber.description: A 12-character string identifying the serial number of the Rack PDU. This value is set at the factory.

rPDUIdentDeviceRating.name: rPDUIdentDeviceRating
rPDUIdentDeviceRating.description: Getting this OID will return the electrical rating of the device in Amps.

rPDUIdentDeviceNumOutlets.name: rPDUIdentDeviceNumOutlets
rPDUIdentDeviceNumOutlets.description: Getting this OID will return the number of outlets contained in the device.

rPDUIdentDeviceNumPhases.name: rPDUIdentDeviceNumPhases
rPDUIdentDeviceNumPhases.description: Getting this OID will return the number of phases supported by the device.

rPDUIdentDeviceNumBreakers.name: rPDUIdentDeviceNumBreakers
rPDUIdentDeviceNumBreakers.description: Getting this OID will return the number of circuit breakers supported by the device. This is the same as the number of banks of outlets. 0 will be returned if the unit has no phase breakers.

rPDUIdentDeviceBreakerRating.name: rPDUIdentDeviceBreakerRating
rPDUIdentDeviceBreakerRating.description: Getting this OID will return rating of the circuit breakers on the device in Amps if it has any.

rPDUIdentDeviceOrientation.name: rPDUIdentDeviceOrientation
rPDUIdentDeviceOrientation.description: Getting this OID will return the intended physical orientation of the device. OrientHorizonatal(1) indicates Horizontal. OrientVertical(2) indicates Vertical.

rPDUIdentDeviceOutletLayout.name: rPDUIdentDeviceOutletLayout
rPDUIdentDeviceOutletLayout.description: Getting this OID will return outlet layout for the device. seqPhaseToNeutral(1) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-N,2:2-N,3:3-N,4:1-N,5:2-N,... seqPhaseToPhase(2) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-2,2:2-3,3:3-1,4:1-2,5:2-3,... seqPhToNeu21PhToPh(3) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-N,2:2-N...21:3-N,22:1-2,23:2-3,24:3-1,... seqPhToPhGrouped(4) indicates outlet layout as follows: For AP8xxx SKU's Group 1:1-2, Group 2:2-3, Group 3:3-1. For AP7xxx SKU's Group 1:3-1. Group 2:2-3, Group 3:1-2. seqPhToNGrouped(5) indicates outlet layout as follows: This unit has 3 outlet groups. Group 1:1-N, Group 2:2-N, Group 3:3-N. seqPToN1516PToPGrouped(6) indicates outlet layout as follows: This unit has 4 outlet groups. Group 1 (Outlets 1-14):1-2, Group 2 (Outlets 15-16):1-N, Group 3:2-3, Group 4:3-1. seqPhToPh2xGrouped(7) indicates outlet layout as follows: This unit has 6 outlet groups. Group 1:1-2, Group 2:1-2, Group 3:2-3, Group 4:2-3, Group 5:3-1, Group 6:3-1. seqPhToN2xGrouped(8) indicates outlet layout as follows: This unit has 6 outlet groups. Group 1:1-N, Group 2:1-N, Group 3:2-N, Group 4:2-N, Group 5:3-N, Group 6:3-N. seqNotApplicable(9): Outlet layout does not affect any of the user interfaces. These SKUs may report seqNotApplicable(9) if there is not an exact outlet layout match available.

rPDUIdentDeviceDisplayOrientation.name: rPDUIdentDeviceDisplayOrientation
rPDUIdentDeviceDisplayOrientation.description: Getting this OID will return the intended physical orientation of the Seven-Segment Display. Normal(1) indicates Normal. Reverse(2)indicates Upside-Down.

rPDUIdentDeviceLinetoLineVoltage.name: rPDUIdentDeviceLinetoLineVoltage
rPDUIdentDeviceLinetoLineVoltage.description: Getting/Setting this OID will return/set the Line to Line Voltage. This OID defaults to the nominal input line voltage in volts AC. This setting is used to calculate total power and must be configured for best accuracy. This OID does not apply to AP86XX, AP88XX, or AP89XX SKUs. The valid range is between 0V to 440V

rPDUIdentDevicePowerWatts.name: rPDUIdentDevicePowerWatts
rPDUIdentDevicePowerWatts.description: Getting this OID will return the Power in Watts.

rPDUIdentDevicePowerFactor.name: rPDUIdentDevicePowerFactor
rPDUIdentDevicePowerFactor.description: Getting/setting this OID will return/set the Power Factor in thousanths (1000 is power factor of 1). For AP8XXX SKUs, this OID is read-only Valid range is from 0 to 1000.

rPDUIdentDevicePowerVA.name: rPDUIdentDevicePowerVA
rPDUIdentDevicePowerVA.description: Getting this OID will return the Power in VA.

rPDUIdentDeviceLinetoNeutralVoltage.name: rPDUIdentDeviceLinetoNeutralVoltage
rPDUIdentDeviceLinetoNeutralVoltage.description: Getting/Setting this OID will return/set the Line to Neutral Voltage. This OID defaults to the nominal line to neutral voltage in volts AC. This setting is used to calculate total power and must be configured for best accuracy. This OID applies only to AP7823. For all other models, the OID is fixed at 0. The valid range is between 0V to 440V.

rPDULoadDevMaxPhaseLoad.name: rPDULoadDevMaxPhaseLoad
rPDULoadDevMaxPhaseLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the maximum rated power that each phase of the Rack PDU can provide. It is represented in Amps. 0 will be returned if the unit is banked.

rPDULoadDevNumPhases.name: rPDULoadDevNumPhases
rPDULoadDevNumPhases.description: The number of phases available with this Rack PDU.

rPDULoadDevMaxBankLoad.name: rPDULoadDevMaxBankLoad
rPDULoadDevMaxBankLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the maximum rated power that a bank of the Rack PDU can provide. It is represented in Amps. 0 will be returned if the device does not have any banks.

rPDULoadDevNumBanks.name: rPDULoadDevNumBanks
rPDULoadDevNumBanks.description: The number of banks of outlets available with this Rack PDU. A bank of outlets has a unique circuit breaker for a subset of the total number of outlets on the rPDU. 0 will be returned if the unit has no banks.

rPDULoadDevBankTableSize.name: rPDULoadDevBankTableSize
rPDULoadDevBankTableSize.description: The size of the Bank Table.

rPDULoadDevBankTable.name: rPDULoadDevBankTable
rPDULoadDevBankTable.description: Allows for getting the Bank Max Load in the Rack PDU.

rPDULoadDevBankIndex.name: rPDULoadDevBankIndex
rPDULoadDevBankIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU bank entry.

rPDULoadDevBankNumber.name: rPDULoadDevBankNumber
rPDULoadDevBankNumber.description: Getting this OID will return the bank number.

rPDULoadDevBankMaxLoad.name: rPDULoadDevBankMaxLoad
rPDULoadDevBankMaxLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the maximum rated power that each bank of the Rack PDU can provide. It is represented in Amps.

rPDULoadDevMaxOutletTableSize.name: rPDULoadDevMaxOutletTableSize
rPDULoadDevMaxOutletTableSize.description: The size of the Outlet Table.

rPDULoadDevMaxOutletTable.name: rPDULoadDevMaxOutletTable
rPDULoadDevMaxOutletTable.description: Allows for getting the Max Outlet Load in an Outlet Monitored Rack PDU.

rPDULoadDevMaxOutletEntry.name: rPDULoadDevMaxOutletEntry
rPDULoadDevMaxOutletEntry.description: This gives access to Max Outlet Load of an Outlet Monitored Rack PDU

rPDULoadDevOutletIndex.name: rPDULoadDevOutletIndex
rPDULoadDevOutletIndex.description: The index to the Outlet Monitored Rack PDU Max Outlet Load entry.

rPDULoadDevOutletNumber.name: rPDULoadDevOutletNumber
rPDULoadDevOutletNumber.description: Getting this OID will return the Outlet number.

rPDULoadDevMaxOutletLoad.name: rPDULoadDevMaxOutletLoad
rPDULoadDevMaxOutletLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the maximum rated power that each Outlet of an Outlet Monitored Rack PDU can provide. It is represented in Amps.

rPDULoadPhaseConfigTable.name: rPDULoadPhaseConfigTable
rPDULoadPhaseConfigTable.description: Allows for configuration of each Rack PDU phase. The number of entries is contained in the rPDULoadDevNumPhases OID.

rPDULoadPhaseConfigEntry.name: rPDULoadPhaseConfigEntry
rPDULoadPhaseConfigEntry.description: The Rack PDU phase to configure.

rPDULoadPhaseConfigIndex.name: rPDULoadPhaseConfigIndex
rPDULoadPhaseConfigIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU phase entry.

rPDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold.name: rPDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold
rPDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is less than the threshold value. A threshold value of 0 Amps effectively disables this warning. Maximum value must be less than the value returned by the rPDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID.

rPDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold.name: rPDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold
rPDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than the value returned by the rPDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the rPDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold OID.

rPDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold.name: rPDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold
rPDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load has entered an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than or equal to the value returned by the rPDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the rPDULoadDevMaxPhaseLoad OID.

rPDULoadPhaseConfigAlarm.name: rPDULoadPhaseConfigAlarm
rPDULoadPhaseConfigAlarm.description: Getting this OID will return the current Phase Alarm.

rPDULoadStatusTable.name: rPDULoadStatusTable
rPDULoadStatusTable.description: Allows for getting of status of each Rack PDU phase/bank. The number of entries is calculated by adding the number of phases (rPDULoadDevNumPhases OID) and the number of banks of outlets (rPDULoadDevNumBanks) Number of entries = #phases + #banks. NOTE: If a device has phase and bank information, all phase information shall precede the bank information. If a device has total information, it shall precede both the bank and the phase information.

rPDULoadStatusEntry.name: rPDULoadStatusEntry
rPDULoadStatusEntry.description: The Rack PDU phase/bank to gather status from.

rPDULoadStatusIndex.name: rPDULoadStatusIndex
rPDULoadStatusIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU phase/bank entry. All phase information will precede any bank information

rPDULoadStatusLoad.name: rPDULoadStatusLoad
rPDULoadStatusLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the phase/bank load measured in tenths of Amps.

rPDULoadStatusLoadState.name: rPDULoadStatusLoadState
rPDULoadStatusLoadState.description: Getting this OID will return the phase/bank load state. phaseLoadNormal(1) indicates that the phase/bank is operating properly within the rPDULoadConfigLowLoadThreshold and rPDULoadConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID values. phaseLoadLow(2) indicates that the phase/bank load has dropped below the rPDULoadConfigLowLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. phaseLoadNearOverload(3) indicates that the phase/bank load is greater than or equal to the rPDULoadConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. phaseLoadOverload(4) indicates that the phase/bank load is greater than or equal to the rPDULoadConfigOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared.

rPDULoadStatusPhaseNumber.name: rPDULoadStatusPhaseNumber
rPDULoadStatusPhaseNumber.description: The phase number to which this record refers.

rPDULoadStatusBankNumber.name: rPDULoadStatusBankNumber
rPDULoadStatusBankNumber.description: The bank number to which this record refers. A value of 0 will be returned if any bank is not present or if it is phase related.

rPDULoadBankConfigTable.name: rPDULoadBankConfigTable
rPDULoadBankConfigTable.description: Allows for configuration of each Rack PDU bank. The number of entries is contained in the rPDULoadDevNumBanks OID.

rPDULoadBankConfigEntry.name: rPDULoadBankConfigEntry
rPDULoadBankConfigEntry.description: The Rack PDU bank to configure.

rPDULoadBankConfigIndex.name: rPDULoadBankConfigIndex
rPDULoadBankConfigIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU bank entry.

rPDULoadBankConfigLowLoadThreshold.name: rPDULoadBankConfigLowLoadThreshold
rPDULoadBankConfigLowLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is less than the threshold value. A threshold value of 0 Amps effectively disables this warning. Maximum value must be less than the value returned by the rPDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID.

rPDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold.name: rPDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold
rPDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than the value returned by the rPDULoadBankConfigLowLoadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the rPDULoadBankConfigOverloadThreshold OID.

rPDULoadBankConfigOverloadThreshold.name: rPDULoadBankConfigOverloadThreshold
rPDULoadBankConfigOverloadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load has entered an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than or equal to the value returned by the rPDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the rPDULoadDevMaxBankLoad OID.

rPDULoadBankConfigAlarm.name: rPDULoadBankConfigAlarm
rPDULoadBankConfigAlarm.description: Getting this OID will return the current Bank Alarm.

rPDUOutletDevCommand.name: rPDUOutletDevCommand
rPDUOutletDevCommand.description: Setting this OID to immediateAllOn (2) will turn all outlets on immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllOff (3) will turn all outlets off immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllReboot (4) will reboot all outlets immediately. Setting this OID to delayedAllOn (5) will turn all outlets on as defined by each outlet's rPDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime OID value. Setting this OID to delayedAllOff (6) will turn all outlets off as defined by each outlet's rPDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime OID value. Setting this OID to delayedAllReboot (7) will cause a delayedAllOff command to be performed. Once all outlets are off, the Switched Rack PDU will then delay the largest rPDUOutletConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedAllOn command. Setting this OID to cancelAllPendingCommands (8) will cause all pending commands on the Switched Rack PDU to be canceled. Getting this OID will return the noCommandAll (1) value.

rPDUOutletDevColdstartDelay.name: rPDUOutletDevColdstartDelay
rPDUOutletDevColdstartDelay.description: The amount of delay, in seconds, between when power is provided to the Switched Rack PDU and when the Switched Rack PDU provides basic master power to the outlets. Allowed values are: -1 - never apply power automatically. 0 - apply power immediately. 1 to 300 - delay up to 300 seconds (5 minutes).

rPDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets.name: rPDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets
rPDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets.description: The number of controlled outlets on this Switched Rack PDU.

rPDUOutletDevNumTotalOutlets.name: rPDUOutletDevNumTotalOutlets
rPDUOutletDevNumTotalOutlets.description: The total number of outlets on this Rack PDU.

rPDUOutletDevMonitoredOutlets.name: rPDUOutletDevMonitoredOutlets
rPDUOutletDevMonitoredOutlets.description: The total number of monitored outlets on this Rack PDU.

rPDUOutletPhaseTable.name: rPDUOutletPhaseTable
rPDUOutletPhaseTable.description: Allows for management of outlets on a per phase basis.

rPDUOutletPhaseIndex.name: rPDUOutletPhaseIndex
rPDUOutletPhaseIndex.description: The index to the Switched Rack PDU phase entry.

rPDUOutletPhaseOverloadRestriction.name: rPDUOutletPhaseOverloadRestriction
rPDUOutletPhaseOverloadRestriction.description: This OID controls the behavior of a Switched Rack PDU phase when an overload condition is possible and additional outlets are requested to be turned on. Setting this OID to alwaysAllowTurnON (1) will always allow the outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on. Setting this OID to restrictOnNearOverload (2) will not allow outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on if the rPDULoadConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded. Setting this OID to restrictOnOverload (3) will not allow outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on if the rPDULoadConfigOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded.

rPDUOutletControlTable.name: rPDUOutletControlTable
rPDUOutletControlTable.description: Allows for control of the individual outlets. The number of entries is contained in the rPDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets OID.

rPDUOutletControlIndex.name: rPDUOutletControlIndex
rPDUOutletControlIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

rPDUOutletControlOutletName.name: rPDUOutletControlOutletName
rPDUOutletControlOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. An error will be returned if the set request exceeds the max size. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

rPDUOutletControlOutletPhase.name: rPDUOutletControlOutletPhase
rPDUOutletControlOutletPhase.description: The phase/s associated with this outlet. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices, this object will return phase1 (1), phase2 (2), or phase3 (3) for outlets tied to a single phase. For outlets tied to two phases, this object will return phase1-2 (4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3 (5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1 (6) for phases 3 and 1.

rPDUOutletControlOutletCommand.name: rPDUOutletControlOutletCommand
rPDUOutletControlOutletCommand.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the immediateOn (1) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the immediateOff (2) value will be returned. Setting this variable to immediateOn (1) will immediately turn the outlet on. Setting this variable to immediateOff (2) will immediately turn the outlet off. Setting this variable to immediateReboot (3) will immediately reboot the outlet. Setting this variable to delayedOn (4) will turn the outlet on after the rPDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedOff (5) will turn the outlet off after the rPDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedReboot (6) will cause the Switched Rack PDU to perform a delayedOff command, wait the rPDUOutletConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedOn command. Setting this variable to cancelPendingCommand (7) will cause any pending command to this outlet to be canceled.

rPDUOutletControlOutletBank.name: rPDUOutletControlOutletBank
rPDUOutletControlOutletBank.description: The bank associated with this outlet.

rPDUOutletConfigTable.name: rPDUOutletConfigTable
rPDUOutletConfigTable.description: Allows for configuration of individual outlets. The number of entries is contained in the rPDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets OID.

rPDUOutletConfigIndex.name: rPDUOutletConfigIndex
rPDUOutletConfigIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

rPDUOutletConfigOutletName.name: rPDUOutletConfigOutletName
rPDUOutletConfigOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. An error will be returned if the set request exceeds the max size.

rPDUOutletConfigOutletPhase.name: rPDUOutletConfigOutletPhase
rPDUOutletConfigOutletPhase.description: The phase/s associated with this outlet. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices, this object will return phase1 (1), phase2 (2), or phase3 (3) for outlets tied to a single phase. For outlets tied to two phases, this object will return phase1-2 (4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3 (5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1 (6) for phases 3 and 1.

rPDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime.name: rPDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime
rPDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) the outlet will delay powering on at coldstart or when a command that requires a turn-on delay is issued. Allowed values are: -1 - never power on. 0 - power on immediately. 1 to 7200 - power on up to 7200 seconds after being commanded.

rPDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime.name: rPDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime
rPDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) the outlet will delay powering off when a command that requires a turn-off delay is issued. Allowed values are: -1 - never power off. 0 - power off immediately. 1 to 7200 - power off up to 7200 seconds after being commanded.

rPDUOutletConfigRebootDuration.name: rPDUOutletConfigRebootDuration
rPDUOutletConfigRebootDuration.description: During a reboot sequence, power is turned off and then back on. This OID defines the amount of time to wait, in seconds, after turning the power off, at the start of the sequence, before turning power back on, at the end of the reboot sequence. Allowed range is any value between 5 and 60 seconds (1 minute).

rPDUOutletConfigOutletBank.name: rPDUOutletConfigOutletBank
rPDUOutletConfigOutletBank.description: The bank associated with this outlet.

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredTableSize.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredTableSize
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredTableSize.description: The size of the Outlet Config Monitored Table

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredTable.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredTable
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredTable.description: Allows for getting/setting of outlet thresholds of an Outlet Monitored Rack PDU.

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredEntry.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredEntry
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredEntry.description: This gives access to Monitored Outlet entries

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredIndex.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredIndex
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredIndex.description: The index to the RACK PDU Phase entry.

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredName.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredName
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredName.description: The name of the Monitored Outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. An error will be returned if the set request exceeds the max size.

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNumber.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNumber
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNumber.description: The outlet number of an Outlet Monitored RACK PDU.

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredLowLoadThreshol.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredLowLoadThreshold
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredLowLoadThreshol.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is less than the threshold value. A threshold value of 0 Amps effectively disables this warning. Maximum value must be less than the value returned by the rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThreshold OID. 0 will be returned if the unit is not Outlet Monitored Rack PDU.

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThr.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThreshold
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThr.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than the value returned by the rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredLowLoadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredOverloadThreshold OID. 0 will be returned if the unit is not Outlet Monitored Rack PDU.

rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredOverloadThresho.name: rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredOverloadThreshold
rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredOverloadThresho.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load has entered an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than or equal to the value returned by the rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the rPDULoadDevMaxOutletLoad OID. 0 will be returned if the unit is not Outlet Monitored Rack PDU.

rPDUOutletStatusTable.name: rPDUOutletStatusTable
rPDUOutletStatusTable.description: Allows for getting of status of individual outlets. The number of entries is contained in the rPDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets OID or rPDUOutletDevMonitoredOutlets OID.

rPDUOutletStatusEntry.name: rPDUOutletStatusEntry
rPDUOutletStatusEntry.description: The outlet to gather status from.

rPDUOutletStatusIndex.name: rPDUOutletStatusIndex
rPDUOutletStatusIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

rPDUOutletStatusOutletName.name: rPDUOutletStatusOutletName
rPDUOutletStatusOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

rPDUOutletStatusOutletPhase.name: rPDUOutletStatusOutletPhase
rPDUOutletStatusOutletPhase.description: The phase/s associated with this outlet. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices, this object will return phase1 (1), phase2 (2), or phase3 (3) for outlets tied to a single phase. For outlets tied to two phases, this object will return phase1-2 (4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3 (5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1 (6) for phases 3 and 1.

rPDUOutletStatusOutletState.name: rPDUOutletStatusOutletState
rPDUOutletStatusOutletState.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the outletStatusOn (1) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the outletStatusOff (2) value will be returned.

rPDUOutletStatusCommandPending.name: rPDUOutletStatusCommandPending
rPDUOutletStatusCommandPending.description: Getting this variable will return the command pending state of the outlet. If a command is pending on the outlet, the outletStatusCommandPending (1) value will be returned. If there is not a command pending on the outlet, the outletStatusNoCommandPending (2) will be returned.

rPDUOutletStatusOutletBank.name: rPDUOutletStatusOutletBank
rPDUOutletStatusOutletBank.description: The bank associated with this outlet.

rPDUOutletStatusLoad.name: rPDUOutletStatusLoad
rPDUOutletStatusLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the measured Outlet load for an Outlet Monitored Rack PDU in tenths of Amps. For other models this OID is not supported.

rPDUOutletBankTable.name: rPDUOutletBankTable
rPDUOutletBankTable.description: Allows for management of outlets on a per bank basis.

rPDUOutletBankIndex.name: rPDUOutletBankIndex
rPDUOutletBankIndex.description: The index to the Switched Rack PDU bank entry.

rPDUOutletBankOverloadRestriction.name: rPDUOutletBankOverloadRestriction
rPDUOutletBankOverloadRestriction.description: This OID controls the behavior of a Switched Rack PDU bank when an overload condition is possible and additional outlets are requested to be turned on. Setting this OID to alwaysAllowTurnON (1) will always allow the outlets on the corresponding bank to turn on. Setting this OID to restrictOnNearOverload (2) will not allow outlets on the corresponding bank to turn on if the rPDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded. Setting this OID to restrictOnOverload (3) will not allow outlets on the corresponding bank to turn on if the rPDULoadBankConfigOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded.

rPDUPowerSupply1Status.name: rPDUPowerSupply1Status
rPDUPowerSupply1Status.description: Getting this OID will return powerSupply1Ok(1) if power supply 1 is functioning normally. If not functioning normally, this OID will return powerSupply1Failed(2).

rPDUPowerSupply2Status.name: rPDUPowerSupply2Status
rPDUPowerSupply2Status.description: Getting this OID will return powerSupply2Ok(1) if power supply 2 is functioning normally. If not functioning normally, this OID will return powerSupply2Failed(2). Metered Rack PDUs do not have a redundant powersupply.

rPDUPowerSupplyAlarm.name: rPDUPowerSupplyAlarm
rPDUPowerSupplyAlarm.description: Getting this OID will return powerSupply Alarm

rPDUStatusBankTableSize.name: rPDUStatusBankTableSize
rPDUStatusBankTableSize.description: The size of the Status Bank Table

rPDUStatusBankTable.name: rPDUStatusBankTable
rPDUStatusBankTable.description: Allows for getting of status of each Rack PDU Bank

rPDUStatusBankEntry.name: rPDUStatusBankEntry
rPDUStatusBankEntry.description: This gives access to Bank entries

rPDUStatusBankIndex.name: rPDUStatusBankIndex
rPDUStatusBankIndex.description: The index to the RACK PDU Bank entry.

rPDUStatusBankNumber.name: rPDUStatusBankNumber
rPDUStatusBankNumber.description: Getting this OID will return the bank number.

rPDUStatusBankState.name: rPDUStatusBankState
rPDUStatusBankState.description: Getting this OID will return the bank load state. bankLoadNormal(1) indicates that the bank is operating properly within the rPDULoadBankConfigLowLoadThreshold and rPDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID values. bankLoadLow(2) indicates that the bank load has dropped below the rPDULoadBankConfigLowLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. bankLoadNearOverload(3) indicates that the bank load is greater than or equal to the rPDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. bankLoadOverload(4) indicates that the bank load is greater than or equal to the rPDULoadBankConfigOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared.

rPDUStatusPhaseTableSize.name: rPDUStatusPhaseTableSize
rPDUStatusPhaseTableSize.description: The size of the Status Phase Table

rPDUStatusPhaseTable.name: rPDUStatusPhaseTable
rPDUStatusPhaseTable.description: Allows for getting of status of each Rack PDU Phase

rPDUStatusPhaseEntry.name: rPDUStatusPhaseEntry
rPDUStatusPhaseEntry.description: This gives access to Phase entries

rPDUStatusPhaseIndex.name: rPDUStatusPhaseIndex
rPDUStatusPhaseIndex.description: The index to the RACK PDU Phase entry.

rPDUStatusPhaseNumber.name: rPDUStatusPhaseNumber
rPDUStatusPhaseNumber.description: Getting this OID will return the phase number.

rPDUStatusPhaseState.name: rPDUStatusPhaseState
rPDUStatusPhaseState.description: Getting this OID will return the Phase load state. phaseLoadNormal(1) indicates that the Phase is operating properly within the rPDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold and rPDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID values. phaseLoadLow(2) indicates that the Phase load has dropped below the rPDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. phaseLoadNearOverload(3) indicates that the Phase load is greater than or equal to the rPDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. phaseLoadOverload(4) indicates that the Phase load is greater than or equal to the rPDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared.

rPDUStatusOutletTableSize.name: rPDUStatusOutletTableSize
rPDUStatusOutletTableSize.description: The size of the Status Outlet Table

rPDUStatusOutletTable.name: rPDUStatusOutletTable
rPDUStatusOutletTable.description: Allows for getting of status of each Outlet of an Outlet Monitored Rack PDU.

rPDUStatusOutletEntry.name: rPDUStatusOutletEntry
rPDUStatusOutletEntry.description: This gives access to Outlet entries

rPDUStatusOutletIndex.name: rPDUStatusOutletIndex
rPDUStatusOutletIndex.description: The index to the RACK PDU Outlet entry.

rPDUStatusOutletNumber.name: rPDUStatusOutletNumber
rPDUStatusOutletNumber.description: Getting this OID will return the Outlet number.

rPDUStatusOutletState.name: rPDUStatusOutletState
rPDUStatusOutletState.description: Getting this OID will return the Outlet load state. outletLoadNormal(1) indicates that the Outlet is operating properly within the rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredLowLoadThreshold and rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThreshold OID values. outletLoadLow(2) indicates that the Outlet load has dropped below the rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredLowLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. outletLoadNearOverload(3) indicates that the Outlet load is greater than or equal to the rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. outletLoadOverload(4) indicates that the Outlet load is greater than or equal to the rPDUOutletConfigMonitoredOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared.

rPDU2IdentTableSize.name: rPDU2IdentTableSize
rPDU2IdentTableSize.description: The total number of Rack PDUs

rPDU2IdentTable.description: A table of Rack PDU identification data

rPDU2IdentEntry.description: Identification data from Rack PDU being queried

rPDU2IdentName.description: A user-defined string identifying the Rack PDU

rPDU2IdentLocation.name: rPDU2IdentLocation
rPDU2IdentLocation.description: A user-defined string identifying the location of the Rack PDU

rPDU2IdentDateOfManufacture.name: rPDU2IdentDateOfManufacture
rPDU2IdentDateOfManufacture.description: The date the Rack PDU was manufactured in mm/dd/yyyy format

rPDU2IdentContact.name: rPDU2IdentContact
rPDU2IdentContact.description: A user-defined string identifying the person to contact regarding the Rack PDU

rPDU2IdentBootMonitorRev.name: rPDU2IdentBootMonitorRev
rPDU2IdentBootMonitorRev.description: The Rack PDU Boot Monitor version

rPDU2IdentLongDescription.name: rPDU2IdentLongDescription
rPDU2IdentLongDescription.description: The Rack PDU Long Description name

rPDU2IdentNMCSerialNumber.name: rPDU2IdentNMCSerialNumber
rPDU2IdentNMCSerialNumber.description: The Rack PDU Network Management Card (NMC) serial number

rPDU2DeviceTableSize.name: rPDU2DeviceTableSize
rPDU2DeviceTableSize.description: The total number of Rack PDUs

rPDU2DeviceConfigTable.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigTable
rPDU2DeviceConfigTable.description: A table of Rack PDU configuration data

rPDU2DeviceConfigEntry.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigEntry
rPDU2DeviceConfigEntry.description: Configuration data from Rack PDU being queried

rPDU2DeviceConfigIndex.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigIndex
rPDU2DeviceConfigIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU table entry

rPDU2DeviceConfigModule.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigModule
rPDU2DeviceConfigModule.description: The user-defined Rack PDU numeric ID

rPDU2DeviceConfigName.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigName
rPDU2DeviceConfigName.description: A user-defined string identifying the Rack PDU

rPDU2DeviceConfigLocation.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigLocation
rPDU2DeviceConfigLocation.description: A user-defined string identifying the location of the Rack PDU

rPDU2DeviceConfigDisplayOrientation.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigDisplayOrientation
rPDU2DeviceConfigDisplayOrientation.description: Indicates the intended physical orientation of the display. displayNormal(1) indicates normal orientation displayReverse(2) indicates upside down orientation

rPDU2DeviceConfigColdstartDelay.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigColdstartDelay
rPDU2DeviceConfigColdstartDelay.description: The amount of delay, measured in seconds, between when power is provided to the Rack PDU and when the Rack PDU provides basic master power to the outlets. Allowed values are: -1 - never apply power automatically. 0 - apply power immediately. 1 to 300 - delay up to 300 seconds (5 minutes).

rPDU2DeviceConfigLowLoadPowerThreshold.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigLowLoadPowerThreshold
rPDU2DeviceConfigLowLoadPowerThreshold.description: User-defined low power draw alarm threshold, measured in tenths of kilowatts. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of -1.

rPDU2DeviceConfigNearOverloadPowerThresh.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigNearOverloadPowerThreshold
rPDU2DeviceConfigNearOverloadPowerThresh.description: User-defined near power overload threshold, measured in tenths of kilowatts. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of -1.

rPDU2DeviceConfigOverloadPowerThreshold.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigOverloadPowerThreshold
rPDU2DeviceConfigOverloadPowerThreshold.description: User-defined power overload threshold, measured in tenths of kilowatts. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of -1.

rPDU2DeviceConfigDevicePeakPowerReset.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigDevicePeakPowerReset
rPDU2DeviceConfigDevicePeakPowerReset.description: Setting this OID to reset (2) will cause the existing peak power value to be replaced by the current load power value. Getting this OID will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of not supported (3). Attempts to set this OID in these models will fail.

rPDU2DeviceConfigDeviceEnergyReset.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigDeviceEnergyReset
rPDU2DeviceConfigDeviceEnergyReset.description: Setting this OID to reset (2) will cause the device energy meter value to be reset to zero. Getting this OID in models that support this feature will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of notSupported (3). Attempts to set this OID in these models will fail.

rPDU2DeviceConfigOutletsEnergyReset.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigOutletsEnergyReset
rPDU2DeviceConfigOutletsEnergyReset.description: Setting this OID to reset (2) will cause the all outlet energy meter values to be reset to zero. Getting this OID will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of notSupported (3). Attempts to set this OID in these models will fail.

rPDU2DeviceConfigOutletsPeakLoadReset.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigOutletsPeakLoadReset
rPDU2DeviceConfigOutletsPeakLoadReset.description: Setting this OID to reset (2) will cause the all outlet peak load values to be reset to zero. Getting this OID will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of notSupported (3). Attempts to set this OID in these models will fail.

rPDU2DeviceConfigContact.name: rPDU2DeviceConfigContact
rPDU2DeviceConfigContact.description: A user-defined string identifying the person to contact regarding the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesTable.description: A table of Rack PDU properties

rPDU2DevicePropertiesEntry.description: Properties of the Rack PDU being queried

rPDU2DevicePropertiesIndex.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesIndex
rPDU2DevicePropertiesIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU properties table entry

rPDU2DevicePropertiesModule.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesModule
rPDU2DevicePropertiesModule.description: The user-defined Rack PDU numeric ID

rPDU2DevicePropertiesName.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesName
rPDU2DevicePropertiesName.description: A user-defined string identifying the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumOutlets.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumOutlets
rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumOutlets.description: The number of outlets on the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumSwitchedOutlets.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumSwitchedOutlets
rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumSwitchedOutlets.description: The number of switched outlets on the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumMeteredOutlets.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumMeteredOutlets
rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumMeteredOutlets.description: The number of metered outlets on the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumPhases.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumPhases
rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumPhases.description: The number of phases present in the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumMeteredBanks.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumMeteredBanks
rPDU2DevicePropertiesNumMeteredBanks.description: The number of metered banks present in the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesMaxCurrentRating.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesMaxCurrentRating
rPDU2DevicePropertiesMaxCurrentRating.description: The maximum current rating, measured in Amps, for the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesOutletLayout.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesOutletLayout
rPDU2DevicePropertiesOutletLayout.description: Getting this OID will return outlet layout for the device. seqPhaseToNeutral(1) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-N,2:2-N,3:3-N,4:1-N,5:2-N,... or for single phase SKUs, all outlets 1-N seqPhaseToPhase(2) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-2,2:2-3,3:3-1,4:1-2,5:2-3,... seqPhToNeu21PhToPh(3) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-N,2:2-N...21:3-N,22:1-2,23:2-3,24:3-1,... seqPhToPhGrouped(4) indicates outlet layout as follows: For AP8xxx SKU's Group 1:1-2, Group 2:2-3, Group 3:3-1. seqPhToNGrouped(5) indicates outlet layout as follows: This unit has 3 outlet groups. Group 1:1-N, Group 2:2-N, Group 3:3-N. seqPToN1516PToPGrouped(6) indicates outlet layout as follows: This unit has 4 outlet groups. Group 1 (Outlets 1-14):1-2, Group 2 (Outlets 15-16):1-N, Group 3:2-3, Group 4:3-1. seqPhToPh2xGrouped(7) indicates outlet layout as follows: This unit has 6 outlet groups. Group 1:1-2, Group 2:1-2, Group 3:2-3, Group 4:2-3, Group 5:3-1, Group 6:3-1. seqPhToN2xGrouped(8) indicates outlet layout as follows: This unit has 6 outlet groups. Group 1:1-N, Group 2:1-N, Group 3:2-N, Group 4:2-N, Group 5:3-N, Group 6:3-N. seqNotApplicable(9): Outlet layout does not affect any of the user interfaces for AP88XX SKUs. These SKUs may report seqNotApplicable(9) if there is not an exact outlet layout match available. seqPhToNPhToPhPhToN(10) indicates outlet layout as follows: Group 1:1-N, Group 2:1-2, Group 3:2-N.

rPDU2DevicePropertiesMaxPhaseCurrentRati.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesMaxPhaseCurrentRating
rPDU2DevicePropertiesMaxPhaseCurrentRati.description: The maximum current rating, measured in Amps, for the Rack PDU

rPDU2DevicePropertiesDevicePowerRating.name: rPDU2DevicePropertiesDevicePowerRating
rPDU2DevicePropertiesDevicePowerRating.description: The maximum power rating, measured in Watts, for the Rack PDU

rPDU2DeviceStatusTable.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusTable
rPDU2DeviceStatusTable.description: A table of Rack PDU status information

rPDU2DeviceStatusEntry.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusEntry
rPDU2DeviceStatusEntry.description: Status information from the Rack PDU being queried

rPDU2DeviceStatusIndex.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusIndex
rPDU2DeviceStatusIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU status table entry

rPDU2DeviceStatusModule.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusModule
rPDU2DeviceStatusModule.description: The user-defined Rack PDU numeric ID

rPDU2DeviceStatusName.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusName
rPDU2DeviceStatusName.description: A user-defined string identifying the Rack PDU

rPDU2DeviceStatusLoadState.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusLoadState
rPDU2DeviceStatusLoadState.description: Indicates the present load status of the Rack PDU. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of notsupported (5).

rPDU2DeviceStatusPower.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusPower
rPDU2DeviceStatusPower.description: The power consumption of the Rack PDU load in hundredths of kilowatts. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of -1.

rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPower.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPower
rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPower.description: The peak power consumption of the Rack PDU load in hundredths of kilowatts. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of -1.

rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPowerTimestamp.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPowerTimestamp
rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPowerTimestamp.description: Indicates the date and time that peak power consumption occurred. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with string 'notsupported'.

rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPowerStartTime.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPowerStartTime
rPDU2DeviceStatusPeakPowerStartTime.description: Indicates the date and time of the last device peak power reset. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with string 'notsupported'.

rPDU2DeviceStatusEnergy.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusEnergy
rPDU2DeviceStatusEnergy.description: A user resettable energy meter measuring Rack PDU load energy consumption in tenths of kilowatt-hours. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of -1.

rPDU2DeviceStatusEnergyStartTime.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusEnergyStartTime
rPDU2DeviceStatusEnergyStartTime.description: Indicates the date and time of the last device energy meter reset. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with string 'notsupported'.

rPDU2DeviceStatusCommandPending.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusCommandPending
rPDU2DeviceStatusCommandPending.description: Indicates whether or not the device is processing a pending command. If the commandPendingUnknown (3) value is returned, all devices powered by the Rack PDU should be shut down. The Rack PDU's power should then be cycled to clear this condition.

rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupplyAlarm.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupplyAlarm
rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupplyAlarm.description: Indicates a power supply alarm is active when value equals alarm (2)

rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupply1Status.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupply1Status
rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupply1Status.description: Indicates whether or not an alarm is active in Power Supply 1

rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupply2Status.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupply2Status
rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerSupply2Status.description: Indicates whether or not an alarm is active in Power Supply 2

rPDU2DeviceStatusOutletsEnergyStartTime.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusOutletsEnergyStartTime
rPDU2DeviceStatusOutletsEnergyStartTime.description: Indicates the date and time of the last outlets energy meter reset. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with string 'notsupported'.

rPDU2DeviceStatusApparentPower.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusApparentPower
rPDU2DeviceStatusApparentPower.description: The apparent power consumption of the Rack PDU load in hundredths of kiloVoltAmps (kVA). Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of -1.

rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerFactor.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerFactor
rPDU2DeviceStatusPowerFactor.description: The power factor of the Rack PDU load in hundredths. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of -1.

rPDU2DeviceStatusNPSType.name: rPDU2DeviceStatusNPSType
rPDU2DeviceStatusNPSType.description: The device NPS status: notNPS (1) indicates the Rack PDU is not in an NPS group. host (2) indicates the Rack PDU has been designated as a host in an NPS group. Only one Rack PDU in an NPS group is allowed to be the host. guest (3) indicates the Rack PDU has been designated as a guest in an NPS group.

rPDU2DeviceControlTable.name: rPDU2DeviceControlTable
rPDU2DeviceControlTable.description: A table of Rack PDU control data

rPDU2DeviceControlEntry.name: rPDU2DeviceControlEntry
rPDU2DeviceControlEntry.description: Control data from Rack PDU being queried

rPDU2DeviceControlIndex.name: rPDU2DeviceControlIndex
rPDU2DeviceControlIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU control table entry

rPDU2DeviceControlModule.name: rPDU2DeviceControlModule
rPDU2DeviceControlModule.description: The user-defined Rack PDU numeric ID

rPDU2DeviceControlName.name: rPDU2DeviceControlName
rPDU2DeviceControlName.description: A user-defined string identifying the Rack PDU

rPDU2DeviceControlCommand.name: rPDU2DeviceControlCommand
rPDU2DeviceControlCommand.description: Setting this OID to immediateAllOn (1) will turn all outlets on immediately. Setting this OID to delayedAllOn (2) will turn all outlets on as defined by each outlet's rPDU2OutletSwitchedConfigPowerOnTime OID value. Setting this OID to immediateAllOff (3) will turn all outlets off immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllReboot (4) will cause an immediateAllOff command to be performed. Once all outlets are off, the Switched Rack PDU will then delay the rPDU2OutletSwitchedConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform an immediateAllOn command. Setting this OID to delayedAllReboot (5) will cause a delayedAllOff command to be performed. Once all outlets are off, the Switched Rack PDU will then delay the largest rPDU2OutletSwitchedConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedAllOn command. Setting this OID to noCommandAll (6) will have no effect. Setting this OID to delayedAllOff (7) will turn all outlets off as defined by each outlet's rPDU2OutletSwitchedConfigPowerOffTime OID value. Setting this OID to cancelAllPendingCommands (8) will cause all pending commands on the Switched Rack PDU to be cancelled. Getting this OID will return the noCommandAll (6) value.

rPDU2PhaseTableSize.name: rPDU2PhaseTableSize
rPDU2PhaseTableSize.description: The number of connected Rack PDU phases

rPDU2PhaseConfigTable.description: A table of Rack PDU phase configuration data

rPDU2PhaseConfigEntry.name: rPDU2PhaseConfigEntry
rPDU2PhaseConfigEntry.description: Configuration data from currently queried Rack PDU phase

rPDU2PhaseConfigIndex.name: rPDU2PhaseConfigIndex
rPDU2PhaseConfigIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU phase configuration table entry

rPDU2PhaseConfigModule.name: rPDU2PhaseConfigModule
rPDU2PhaseConfigModule.description: The user-defined Rack PDU numeric ID

rPDU2PhaseConfigOverloadRestriction.name: rPDU2PhaseConfigOverloadRestriction
rPDU2PhaseConfigOverloadRestriction.description: This OID controls the behavior of a Switched Rack PDU phase when an overload condition is possible and additional outlets are requested to be turned on. Setting this OID to alwaysAllowTurnON (1) will always allow the outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on. Setting this OID to restrictOnNearOverload (2) will not allow outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on if the rPDULoadConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded. Setting this OID to restrictOnOverload (3) will not allow outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on if the rPDULoadConfigOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of notSupported (4). Attempts to set this OID in these models will fail.

rPDU2PhaseConfigLowLoadCurrentThreshold.name: rPDU2PhaseConfigLowLoadCurrentThreshold
rPDU2PhaseConfigLowLoadCurrentThreshold.description: User-defined low load phase current threshold in Amps

rPDU2PhaseConfigNearOverloadCurrentThres.name: rPDU2PhaseConfigNearOverloadCurrentThreshold
rPDU2PhaseConfigNearOverloadCurrentThres.description: User-defined near phase overload warning threshold in Amps

rPDU2PhaseConfigOverloadCurrentThreshold.name: rPDU2PhaseConfigOverloadCurrentThreshold
rPDU2PhaseConfigOverloadCurrentThreshold.description: User-defined phase overload current threshold in Amps

rPDU2PhaseConfigPhasePeakCurrentReset.name: rPDU2PhaseConfigPhasePeakCurrentReset
rPDU2PhaseConfigPhasePeakCurrentReset.description: Setting this OID to reset (2) will cause the existing peak current value to be replaced by the present load current value. Getting this OID will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value.

rPDU2PhasePropertiesTable.description: A table of Rack PDU phase properties

rPDU2PhasePropertiesEntry.description: Properties of the currently queried Rack PDU phase

rPDU2PhasePropertiesIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU phase properties table entry

rPDU2PhasePropertiesModule.name: rPDU2PhasePropertiesModule
rPDU2PhasePropertiesModule.description: The user-defined Rack PDU numeric ID

rPDU2PhaseStatusTable.description: A table of Rack PDU phase status data

rPDU2PhaseStatusEntry.description: Status data from currently queried Rack PDU phase

rPDU2BankConfigOverloadRestriction.name: rPDU2BankConfigOverloadRestriction
rPDU2BankConfigOverloadRestriction.description: This OID controls the behavior of a Switched Rack PDU bank when an overload condition is possible and additional outlets are requested to be turned on. Setting this OID to alwaysAllowTurnON (1) will always allow the outlets on the corresponding bank to turn on. Setting this OID to restrictOnNearOverload (2) will not allow outlets on the corresponding bank to turn on if the rPDU2BankConfigNearOverloadCurrentThreshold OID is exceeded. Setting this OID to restrictOnOverload (3) will not allow outlets on the corresponding bank to turn on if the rPDU2BankConfigOverloadCurrentThreshold OID is exceeded. Models that do not support this feature will respond to this OID with a value of notSupported (4). Attempts to set this OID in these models will fail.

rPDU2OutletSwitchedControlCommand.name: rPDU2OutletSwitchedControlCommand
rPDU2OutletSwitchedControlCommand.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the immediateOn (1) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the immediateOff (2) value will be returned. If the state of the outlet cannot be determined, the outletUnknown (4) value will be returned. If the outletUnknown condition should occur, all devices powered by the PDU should be shut down. The PDU's power should then be cycled to clear this condition. Setting this variable to immediateOn (1) will immediately turn the outlet on. Setting this variable to immediateOff (2) will immediately turn the outlet off. Setting this variable to immediateReboot (3) will cause the Switched Rack PDU to perform an immediateOff command, wait the rPDU2OutletSwitchedConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform an immediateOn command. Setting this variable to delayedOn (5) will turn the outlet on after the rPDU2OutletSwitchedConfigPowerOnTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedOff (6) will turn the outlet off after the rPDU2OutletSwitchedConfigPowerOffTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedReboot (7) will cause the Switched Rack PDU to perform a delayedOff command, wait the rPDU2OutletSwitchedConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedOn command. Setting this variable to cancelPendingCommand (8) will cause any pending command to this outlet to be cancelled.

rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusTempF.name: rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusTempF

rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusTempC.name: rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusTempC
rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusTempC.description: Sensor temperature reading in tenths of degrees Celsius

rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusTempStatus.name: rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusTempStatus
rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusTempStatus.description: This OID reports the current state of the temperature probe. A notPresent (1) response indicates that no probe is attached. A belowMin (2) response indicates that the probe is present and its measured temperature lies below the minimum threshold. A belowLow (3) response indicates that the probe is present and its measured temperature lies below the low threshold. A normal (4) response indicates that the probe is present and its measured temperature lies within all temperature thresholds. An aboveHigh (5) response indicates that the probe is present and is measuring a temperature above the high threshold. An aboveMax (6) response indicates that the probe is present and is measuring a temperature above the max threshold.

rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusRelativeHum.name: rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusRelativeHumidity
rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusRelativeHum.description: Sensor humidity reading in percent relative humidity

rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusHumiditySta.name: rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusHumidityStatus
rPDU2SensorTempHumidityStatusHumiditySta.description: This OID reports the current state of the humidity probe. A notPresent (1) response indicates that no probe is attached. A belowMin (2) response indicates that the probe is present and its measured humidity lies below the minimum threshold. A belowLow (3) response indicates that the probe is present and its measured humidity lies below the low threshold. A normal (4) response indicates that the probe is present and its measured humidity lies within all humidity thresholds. An aboveHigh (5) response indicates that the probe is present and is measuring a humidity above the high threshold. An aboveMax (6) response indicates that the probe is present and is measuring a humidity above the max threshold.

rPDU2GroupNumberOfDevices.name: rPDU2GroupNumberOfDevices
rPDU2GroupNumberOfDevices.description: Getting this OID will return the number of Rack PDU devices contributing to the Network Port Sharing (NPS) group power and energy values. Queries to guest units in an NPS group are not applicable and will return 0.

rPDU2GroupTotalPower.name: rPDU2GroupTotalPower
rPDU2GroupTotalPower.description: Getting this OID will return the total power consumption of the Rack PDU Network Port Sharing (NPS) group devices in hundredths of kilowatts. Queries to guest units in an NPS group are not applicable and will return 0.

rPDU2GroupTotalEnergy.name: rPDU2GroupTotalEnergy
rPDU2GroupTotalEnergy.description: Getting this OID will return the total energy consumption of the Rack PDU Network Port Sharing (NPS) group devices in tenths of kilowatt-hours. To reset the energy meters for each of the Rack PDU devices that contribute to this value, see the rPDU2GroupEnergyReset OID. To view the start time for each of the Rack PDU device energy meters that contribute to this value, see the rPDU2DeviceStatusEnergyStartTime OID. Queries to guest units in an NPS group are not applicable and will return 0.

rPDU2GroupEnergyReset.name: rPDU2GroupEnergyReset
rPDU2GroupEnergyReset.description: Setting this OID to reset (2) will cause the device energy meter value on each device in the Rack PDU Network Port Sharing (NPS) group to be reset to zero. Each device in the Rack PDU group will also have its corresponding rPDU2DeviceStatusEnergyStartTime OID value updated. Getting this OID in models that support this feature will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. Models that do not support this feature, as well as guest units in an NPS group, will respond to this OID with a value of notSupported (3). Attempts to set this OID in these units will fail.

dm3ConfigSysHighTempThresh.name: dm3ConfigSysHighTempThresh
dm3ConfigSysHighTempThresh.description: Ambient high temperature threshold. Temperature sensor located on Master Controller board. Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dm3StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit). Attempts to set the value above or below the acceptable range of the powerplant will cause the value to be set at the high or low point of the range respectively.

dm3ConfigSysHighTempAlarm.name: dm3ConfigSysHighTempAlarm
dm3ConfigSysHighTempAlarm.description: For the System High Temperature Alarm; Setting this OID to alarmIgnore (1) results in the alarm condition being ignored. Setting this OID to alarmRelay1 (2) causes relay 1 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay2 (3) causes relay 2 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay3 (4) causes relay 3 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay4 (5) causes relay 4 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay5 (6) causes relay 5 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay6 (7) causes relay 6 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMinor (8) causes the Minor relay to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMajor (9) causes the Major relay to be activated for an alarm condition.

dm3ConfigSysLowTempThresh.name: dm3ConfigSysLowTempThresh
dm3ConfigSysLowTempThresh.description: Ambient low temperature threshold. Temperature sensor located on Master Controller board. Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dm3StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit). Attempts to set the value above or below the acceptable range of the powerplant will cause the value to be set at the high or low point of the range respectively.

dm3ConfigSysLowTempAlarm.name: dm3ConfigSysLowTempAlarm
dm3ConfigSysLowTempAlarm.description: For the System Low Temperature Alarm; Setting this OID to alarmIgnore (1) results in the alarm condition being ignored. Setting this OID to alarmRelay1 (2) causes relay 1 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay2 (3) causes relay 2 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay3 (4) causes relay 3 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay4 (5) causes relay 4 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay5 (6) causes relay 5 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay6 (7) causes relay 6 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMinor (8) causes the Minor relay to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMajor (9) causes the Major relay to be activated for an alarm condition.

dm3ConfigSysHardwareTempAlarm.name: dm3ConfigSysHardwareTempAlarm
dm3ConfigSysHardwareTempAlarm.description: For the System Hardware Temperature Alarm; Setting this OID to alarmIgnore (1) results in the alarm condition being ignored. Setting this OID to alarmRelay1 (2) causes relay 1 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay2 (3) causes relay 2 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay3 (4) causes relay 3 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay4 (5) causes relay 4 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay5 (6) causes relay 5 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay6 (7) causes relay 6 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMinor (8) causes the Minor relay to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMajor (9) causes the Major relay to be activated for an alarm condition.

dm3ConfigSysRemoteAccess.name: dm3ConfigSysRemoteAccess
dm3ConfigSysRemoteAccess.description: This OID is used to disable remote write access to the power plant. Setting this OID to accessEnabled (1) will have no affect. Setting this OID to accessDisabled (2) will disable the ability to remotely configure the DC powerplant. Once remote access is disabled, it can only be restored from the front panel of the DC power plant.

dm3ConfigLVDTable.name: dm3ConfigLVDTable

dm3ConfigLVDIndex.name: dm3ConfigLVDIndex
dm3ConfigLVDIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant LVD.

dm3ConfigLVDName.name: dm3ConfigLVDName
dm3ConfigLVDName.description: The name of the LVD. The maximum value is 16 characters.

dm3ConfigLVDEnable.name: dm3ConfigLVDEnable
dm3ConfigLVDEnable.description: This OID is used to control and indicate if the LVD is on or off. Setting this OID to enabledYes (1) will enable (turn on) the LVD. Setting this OID to enabledNo (2) will disable (turn off) the LVD.

dm3ConfigLVDTripThresh.name: dm3ConfigLVDTripThresh
dm3ConfigLVDTripThresh.description: LVD Trip threshold. If voltage exceeds threshold, the LVD will trip. Values are represented in thousandths of Volts (mV). Attempts to set the value above or below the acceptable range of the powerplant will cause the value to be set at the high or low point of the range respectively.

dm3ConfigLVDResetThresh.name: dm3ConfigLVDResetThresh
dm3ConfigLVDResetThresh.description: LVD Reset threshold. If voltage exceeds threshold, the LVD will reset. Values are represented in thousandths of Volts (mV). Attempts to set the value above or below the acceptable range of the powerplant will cause the value to be set at the high or low point of the range respectively.

dm3ConfigLVDOpenAlarm.name: dm3ConfigLVDOpenAlarm
dm3ConfigLVDOpenAlarm.description: For the LVD Open Alarm; Setting this OID to alarmIgnore (1) results in the alarm condition being ignored. Setting this OID to alarmRelay1 (2) causes relay 1 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay2 (3) causes relay 2 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay3 (4) causes relay 3 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay4 (5) causes relay 4 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay5 (6) causes relay 5 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay6 (7) causes relay 6 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMinor (8) causes the Minor relay to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMajor (9) causes the Major relay to be activated for an alarm condition.

dm3ConfigLVDHWAlarm.name: dm3ConfigLVDHWAlarm

dm3ConfigOutRlyTableSize.name: dm3ConfigOutRlyTableSize
dm3ConfigOutRlyTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant Output Relays controllable by this IP address.

dm3ConfigOutRlyTable.name: dm3ConfigOutRlyTable
dm3ConfigOutRlyTable.description: Allows for accessing settings of the Output Relays. The number of entries is contained in the dm3ConfigOutRlyTableSize OID.

dm3ConfigOutRlyIndex.name: dm3ConfigOutRlyIndex
dm3ConfigOutRlyIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant output relay.

dm3ConfigOutRlyName.name: dm3ConfigOutRlyName
dm3ConfigOutRlyName.description: The name of the output relay. The maximum value is 16 characters.

dm3ConfigOutRlyDelay.name: dm3ConfigOutRlyDelay
dm3ConfigOutRlyDelay.description: Output Relay Delay. This OID represents the time delay from the initiation of an output relay action to when the output relay action does occur. If the alarm condition disappears before the end of the delay, no action will occur. Delay for Major and Minor alarms is not configurable and is always set to 0. Values are represented in hundredths of seconds. Attempts to set the value above or below the acceptable range of the powerplant will cause the value to be set at the high or low point of the range respectively.

dm3ConfigOutRlyAlarm.name: dm3ConfigOutRlyAlarm
dm3ConfigOutRlyAlarm.description: Output Relay Alarm. This setting indicates what action to perform in the event of an output relay alarm condition; Setting this OID to alarmIgnore (1) results in the alarm condition being ignored. Setting this OID to alarmRelay1 (2) causes relay 1 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay2 (3) causes relay 2 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay3 (4) causes relay 3 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay4 (5) causes relay 4 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay5 (6) causes relay 5 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmRelay6 (7) causes relay 6 to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMinor (8) causes the Minor relay to be activated for an alarm condition. Setting this OID to alarmMajor (9) causes the Major relay to be activated for an alarm condition. Relay Alarm for Major and Minor alarms is not configurable and is always set to alarmMajor and alarmMinor respectively.

dm3ConfigInRlyTableSize.name: dm3ConfigInRlyTableSize
dm3ConfigInRlyTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant Input Relays controllable by this IP address.

dm3StatusSystemTemp.name: dm3StatusSystemTemp
dm3StatusSystemTemp.description: System temperature based on sensor on Master Controller PCB. Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dm3StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

dm3StatusSystemStart.name: dm3StatusSystemStart
dm3StatusSystemStart.description: Time stamp at DC powerplant initialization. The time is represented as MMM,DD,YYYY,HH:MM:SS.

dm3StatusSysRemoteAccess.name: dm3StatusSysRemoteAccess
dm3StatusSysRemoteAccess.description: Remote Access indicator This setting indicates if configuration (write) access to the powerplant is enabled or disabled at the powerplant level. This value will be accessEnabled (1) if remote configuration is enabled, and accessDisabled (2) if remote configuration is disabled.

dm3StatusSysSecurityLevel.name: dm3StatusSysSecurityLevel
dm3StatusSysSecurityLevel.description: This variable shows the current active security access level of controller. This can only be changed directly from the front panel.

dm3StatusSysTempSanity.name: dm3StatusSysTempSanity
dm3StatusSysTempSanity.description: System temperature sanity indicator. Indicates if the system temperature is reasonable. Reasonable is defined based on powerplant type. A value of saneYes (1) indicates temperature is reasonable, a value of saneNo (2) indicates it is not.

dm3StatusSysAlarmState.name: dm3StatusSysAlarmState
dm3StatusSysAlarmState.description: System Alarm State. Reflects the alarm status of the overall DC system. If a minor alarm is present, the value will be alarmMinor(1). If a major alarm is present, the value will be alarmMajor(2). If both minor and a major alarm is present, the value will be alarmBoth(3). If no alarm is present, the value will be alarmNone(4).

dm3StatusSysTempUnits.name: dm3StatusSysTempUnits
dm3StatusSysTempUnits.description: The temperature scale used to display the temperature in the DC system, Celsius(1) or Fahrenheit(2). This setting is based on the system preferences configuration in the agent.

dm3StatusAlarmsTableSize.name: dm3StatusAlarmsTableSize

dm3StatusAlarmsTable.name: dm3StatusAlarmsTable

dm3StatusAlarmsIndex.name: dm3StatusAlarmsIndex
dm3StatusAlarmsIndex.description: The index of the system alarm.

dm3StatusAlarmsText.name: dm3StatusAlarmsText

dm3StatusBattCurrent.name: dm3StatusBattCurrent

dm3StatusBattTemp.name: dm3StatusBattTemp

dm3StatusBattTempSanity.name: dm3StatusBattTempSanity

dm3StatusOEMrectGain.name: dm3StatusOEMrectGain
dm3StatusOEMrectGain.description: This OID shows the rectifier gain value in thousandths of Volts (mV/V).

dm3StatusOEMconvOffset.name: dm3StatusOEMconvOffset

dm3StatusOEMshuntGain.name: dm3StatusOEMshuntGain

dm3StatusLVDTableSize.name: dm3StatusLVDTableSize

dm3StatusLVDIndex.name: dm3StatusLVDIndex

dm3StatusLVDName.name: dm3StatusLVDName

dm3StatusLVDState.name: dm3StatusLVDState
dm3StatusLVDState.description: Getting this OID will return statusClosed (1) if the LVD is closed. statusOpened (2) will be returned if the LVD is opened.

dm3StatusLVDHwFault.description: Getting this OID will return statusFault (1) if the LVD is faulted. statusNofault (2) will be returned if the LVD is not faulted.

dm3StatusRectTableSize.name: dm3StatusRectTableSize

dm3StatusRectEntry.name: dm3StatusRectEntry

dm3StatusRectIndex.name: dm3StatusRectIndex

dm3StatusRectID.name: dm3StatusRectID

dm3StatusRectDesc.name: dm3StatusRectDesc

dm3StatusRectCurrent.name: dm3StatusRectCurrent
