dm3StatusRectStandby.name: dm3StatusRectStandby
dm3StatusRectStandby.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the rectifier is in the Standby state. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the rectifier is not in the Standby state.

dm3StatusRectFanFail.name: dm3StatusRectFanFail
dm3StatusRectFanFail.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the rectifier Fan has failed. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the rectifier Fan has not failed.

dm3StatusRectFail.name: dm3StatusRectFail
dm3StatusRectFail.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the rectifier has failed. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the rectifier has not failed.

dm3StatusRectDevType.name: dm3StatusRectDevType
dm3StatusRectDevType.description: This OID shows the rectifier device type.

dm3StatusRectPhyAddr.name: dm3StatusRectPhyAddr
dm3StatusRectPhyAddr.description: This OID shows the rectifier physical address (the address on the bus).

dm3StatusRectCfg.name: dm3StatusRectCfg
dm3StatusRectCfg.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the rectifier is present after power-up or set-configuration. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the rectifier is not configured.

dm3StatusRectPcbRev.name: dm3StatusRectPcbRev
dm3StatusRectPcbRev.description: This OID shows the rectifier device PCB serial number.

dm3StatusRectFwVer.name: dm3StatusRectFwVer
dm3StatusRectFwVer.description: This OID shows the rectifier device firmware revision.

dm3StatusRectPresent.name: dm3StatusRectPresent
dm3StatusRectPresent.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the rectifier is present. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the rectifier is not present.

dm3StatusRectDiagPass.name: dm3StatusRectDiagPass
dm3StatusRectDiagPass.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the rectifier diagnostics have passed. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the rectifier diagnostics have not passed.

dm3StatusRectState.name: dm3StatusRectState
dm3StatusRectState.description: This OID shows the rectifier device state as defined by the device status register.

dm3StatusSysRectVoltSanity.name: dm3StatusSysRectVoltSanity
dm3StatusSysRectVoltSanity.description: Rectifier voltage sanity indicator. Indicates if the rectifier voltage is reasonable. Reasonable is defined based on powerplant type. A value of saneYes (1) indicates voltage is reasonable, a value of saneNo (2) indicates it is not.

dm3StatusSysRectAvailable.name: dm3StatusSysRectAvailable
dm3StatusSysRectAvailable.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the rectifier is available. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the rectifier is not available.

dm3StatusSysRectType.name: dm3StatusSysRectType
dm3StatusSysRectType.description: This OID shows the type of rectifier the system has. There can only be a single type of rectifier in the power plant

dm3StatusSysRectVoltage.name: dm3StatusSysRectVoltage
dm3StatusSysRectVoltage.description: This OID shows the system level rectifier voltage in thousandths of Volts (mV).

dm3StatusSysRectCurrent.name: dm3StatusSysRectCurrent
dm3StatusSysRectCurrent.description: This OID shows the system level rectifier current in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dm3StatusConvTableSize.name: dm3StatusConvTableSize
dm3StatusConvTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant converters viewable by this IP address.

dm3StatusConvTable.name: dm3StatusConvTable
dm3StatusConvTable.description: Allows for viewing status of the converters. The number of entries is contained in the dm3StatusConvTableSize OID.

dm3StatusConvEntry.name: dm3StatusConvEntry
dm3StatusConvEntry.description: The converter to gather status from.

dm3StatusConvIndex.name: dm3StatusConvIndex
dm3StatusConvIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant converter.

dm3StatusConvID.name: dm3StatusConvID
dm3StatusConvID.description: This OID shows the converter ID. This enumerates the number of the converter within a group of converters.

dm3StatusConvDesc.name: dm3StatusConvDesc
dm3StatusConvDesc.description: This OID shows the 16 character converter description.

dm3StatusConvCurrent.name: dm3StatusConvCurrent
dm3StatusConvCurrent.description: This OID shows the converter current in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dm3StatusConvCurrentLimit.name: dm3StatusConvCurrentLimit
dm3StatusConvCurrentLimit.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the converter is in the Current Limit state. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the converter is not in the Current Limit state.

dm3StatusConvStandby.name: dm3StatusConvStandby
dm3StatusConvStandby.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the converter is in the Standby state. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the converter is not in the Standby state.

dm3StatusConvFanFail.name: dm3StatusConvFanFail
dm3StatusConvFanFail.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the converter Fan has failed. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the converter Fan has not failed.

dm3StatusConvFail.name: dm3StatusConvFail
dm3StatusConvFail.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the converter has failed. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the converter has not failed.

dm3StatusConvDevType.name: dm3StatusConvDevType
dm3StatusConvDevType.description: This OID shows the converter device type.

dm3StatusConvPhyAddr.name: dm3StatusConvPhyAddr
dm3StatusConvPhyAddr.description: This OID shows the converter physical address (the address on the bus).

dm3StatusConvCfg.name: dm3StatusConvCfg
dm3StatusConvCfg.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the converter is present after power-up or set-configuration. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the converter is not configured.

dm3StatusConvPcbRev.name: dm3StatusConvPcbRev
dm3StatusConvPcbRev.description: This OID shows the converter device PCB serial number.

dm3StatusConvFwVer.name: dm3StatusConvFwVer
dm3StatusConvFwVer.description: This OID shows the converter device firmware version.

dm3StatusConvPresent.name: dm3StatusConvPresent
dm3StatusConvPresent.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the converter is present. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the converter is not present.

dm3StatusConvDiagPass.name: dm3StatusConvDiagPass
dm3StatusConvDiagPass.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the converter diagnostics have passed. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the converter diagnostics have not passed.

dm3StatusConvState.name: dm3StatusConvState
dm3StatusConvState.description: This OID shows the converter state as defined by the device status register.

dm3StatusSysConvVoltSanity.name: dm3StatusSysConvVoltSanity
dm3StatusSysConvVoltSanity.description: Converter voltage sanity indicator. Indicates if the converter voltage is reasonable. Reasonable is defined based on powerplant type. A value of saneYes (1) indicates voltage is reasonable, a value of saneNo (2) indicates it is not.

dm3StatusSysConvAvailable.name: dm3StatusSysConvAvailable
dm3StatusSysConvAvailable.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the converter is available. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the converter is not available.

dm3StatusSysConvType.name: dm3StatusSysConvType
dm3StatusSysConvType.description: This OID shows the converter type.

dm3StatusSysConvVoltage.name: dm3StatusSysConvVoltage
dm3StatusSysConvVoltage.description: This OID shows the system level converter voltage in thousandths of volts (mV).

dm3StatusSysConvCurrent.name: dm3StatusSysConvCurrent
dm3StatusSysConvCurrent.description: This OID shows the system level converter current in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dm3StatusOutRlyTableSize.name: dm3StatusOutRlyTableSize
dm3StatusOutRlyTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant output relays viewable by this IP address.

dm3StatusOutRlyTable.name: dm3StatusOutRlyTable
dm3StatusOutRlyTable.description: Allows for viewing status of the output relays. The number of entries is contained in the dm3StatusOutRlyTableSize OID.

dm3StatusOutRlyEntry.name: dm3StatusOutRlyEntry
dm3StatusOutRlyEntry.description: The output relay to gather status from.

dm3StatusOutRlyIndex.name: dm3StatusOutRlyIndex
dm3StatusOutRlyIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant output relay.

dm3StatusOutRlyName.name: dm3StatusOutRlyName
dm3StatusOutRlyName.description: The name of the output relay. The maximum size is 16 characters. The name is set by using the dm3ConfigOutRlyName OID. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

dm3StatusOutRlyStatus.name: dm3StatusOutRlyStatus
dm3StatusOutRlyStatus.description: Getting this OID will return statusOn (1) if the output relay is enabled/on. statusOff (2) will be returned if the output relay is disabled/off.

dm3StatusInRlyTableSize.name: dm3StatusInRlyTableSize
dm3StatusInRlyTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant input relays viewable by this IP address.

dm3StatusInRlyTable.name: dm3StatusInRlyTable
dm3StatusInRlyTable.description: Allows for viewing status of the input relays. The number of entries is contained in the dm3StatusInRlyTableSize OID.

dm3StatusInRlyEntry.name: dm3StatusInRlyEntry
dm3StatusInRlyEntry.description: The input relays to gather status from.

dm3StatusInRlyIndex.name: dm3StatusInRlyIndex
dm3StatusInRlyIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant input relay.

dm3StatusInRlyName.name: dm3StatusInRlyName
dm3StatusInRlyName.description: The name of the input relay. The maximum size is 16 characters. The name is set by using the dm3ConfigInRlyName OID. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

dm3StatusInRlyStatus.name: dm3StatusInRlyStatus
dm3StatusInRlyStatus.description: Getting this OID will return statusOn (1) if the input relay is enabled/on. statusOff (2) will be returned if the input relay is disabled/off.

dm3StatusBreakersTableSize.name: dm3StatusBreakersTableSize
dm3StatusBreakersTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant circuit breakers viewable by this IP address.

dm3StatusBreakersTable.name: dm3StatusBreakersTable
dm3StatusBreakersTable.description: Allows for viewing status of the circuit breakers. The number of entries is contained in the dm3StatusBreakersTableSize OID.

dm3StatusBreakersEntry.name: dm3StatusBreakersEntry
dm3StatusBreakersEntry.description: The circuit breaker to gather status from.

dm3StatusBreakersIndex.name: dm3StatusBreakersIndex
dm3StatusBreakersIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant circuit breaker.

dm3StatusBreakersName.name: dm3StatusBreakersName
dm3StatusBreakersName.description: The name of the circuit breaker. The maximum size is 16 characters. The name is set by using the dm3ConfigBreakersName OID. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

dm3StatusBreakersStatus.name: dm3StatusBreakersStatus
dm3StatusBreakersStatus.description: Getting this OID will return statusClosed (1) if the circuit breaker is closed. statusOpen (2) will be returned if the circuit breaker is open.

dm3StatusFusesTableSize.name: dm3StatusFusesTableSize
dm3StatusFusesTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant fuses controllable by this IP address.

dm3StatusFusesTable.name: dm3StatusFusesTable
dm3StatusFusesTable.description: Allows for viewing status of the fuses. The number of entries is contained in the dm3StatusFusesTableSize OID.

dm3StatusFusesEntry.name: dm3StatusFusesEntry
dm3StatusFusesEntry.description: The fuse to gather status from.

dm3StatusFusesIndex.name: dm3StatusFusesIndex
dm3StatusFusesIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant fuse.

dm3StatusFusesName.name: dm3StatusFusesName
dm3StatusFusesName.description: The name of the fuse. The maximum size is 16 characters. The name is set by using the dm3ConfigFuseName OID. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

dm3StatusFusesStatus.name: dm3StatusFusesStatus
dm3StatusFusesStatus.description: Getting this OID will return statusClosed (1) if the fuse is closed. statusOpen (2) will be returned if the fuse is open.

atsIdentHardwareRev.name: atsIdentHardwareRev
atsIdentHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the Automatic Transfer Switch. This value is set at the factory.

atsIdentFirmwareRev.name: atsIdentFirmwareRev
atsIdentFirmwareRev.description: A string identifying the Automatic Transfer Switch firmware revision.

atsIdentFirmwareDate.name: atsIdentFirmwareDate
atsIdentFirmwareDate.description: The date of release for this Automatic Transfer Switch firmware revision.

atsIdentDateOfManufacture.name: atsIdentDateOfManufacture
atsIdentDateOfManufacture.description: The date when the Automatic Transfer Switch was manufactured in mm/dd/yyyy format. This value is set at the factory.

atsIdentModelNumber.name: atsIdentModelNumber
atsIdentModelNumber.description: A string identifying the model number of the Automatic Transfer Switch. This value is set at the factory.

atsIdentSerialNumber.name: atsIdentSerialNumber
atsIdentSerialNumber.description: A string identifying the serial number of the Automatic Transfer Switch. This value is set at the factory.

atsIdentNominalLineVoltage.name: atsIdentNominalLineVoltage
atsIdentNominalLineVoltage.description: RMS Utility Voltage measured in Volts.

atsIdentNominalLineFrequency.name: atsIdentNominalLineFrequency
atsIdentNominalLineFrequency.description: Utility Power Frequency measured in Hertz.

atsIdentDeviceRating.name: atsIdentDeviceRating
atsIdentDeviceRating.description: This gives the device rating in Amps

atsCalibrationNumInputs.name: atsCalibrationNumInputs
atsCalibrationNumInputs.description: The number of inputs to this device.

atsCalibrationNumInputPhases.name: atsCalibrationNumInputPhases
atsCalibrationNumInputPhases.description: The number of phases per input for this device.

atsCalibrationInputPhaseTable.name: atsCalibrationInputPhaseTable
atsCalibrationInputPhaseTable.description: The number of phases per input line to this device.

atsCalibrationInputPhaseEntry.name: atsCalibrationInputPhaseEntry
atsCalibrationInputPhaseEntry.description: An entry containing calibration information applicable to a particular input phase.

atsLineVoltageCalibrationFactor.name: atsLineVoltageCalibrationFactor
atsLineVoltageCalibrationFactor.description: The Line Voltage Calibration factor. This value is set at the factory.

atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltages.name: atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltages
atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltages.description: The number of power supply voltages supported by this device. This variable indicates the number of rows in the atsCalibrationPowerSupplyTable.

atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTable.name: atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTable
atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTable.description: A list of Power Supply table entries.

atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageEntry.name: atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageEntry
atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular Power Supply Voltage.

atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltage.name: atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltage
atsCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltage.description: This value describes the power supply voltage of 24V Source A, 24V Source B, +12V, -12V and 5V.

atsPowerSupplyVoltageCalibrationFactor.name: atsPowerSupplyVoltageCalibrationFactor
atsPowerSupplyVoltageCalibrationFactor.description: The Line Voltage Calibration factor. This value is set at the factory.

ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTable.name: ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTable
ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTable.description: A list of Power Supply table entries. It is not applicable to AP77xx ATS units.

ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageEntry.name: ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageEntry
ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular Power Supply Voltage. It is not applicable to AP77xx ATS units.

ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTableI.name: ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTableIndex
ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltageTableI.description: The power supply voltage identifier. It is not applicable to AP77xx ATS units.

ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltage.name: ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltage
ats4gCalibrationPowerSupplyVoltage.description: This value describes the power supply voltage of 24V Source A, 24V Source B, VBoost Source A, VBoost Source B, 3.3V, 1.0V. It is not applicable to AP77xx ATS units.

ats4gPowerSupplyVoltageCalibrationFactor.name: ats4gPowerSupplyVoltageCalibrationFactor
ats4gPowerSupplyVoltageCalibrationFactor.description: The Line Voltage Calibration factor. This value is set at the factory. It is not applicable to AP77xx ATS units.

atsCalibrationNumOutputs.name: atsCalibrationNumOutputs
atsCalibrationNumOutputs.description: The number of output lines from this device. This variable indicates the number of rows in the atsCalibrationOutputTable.

atsCalibrationNumOutputPhases.name: atsCalibrationNumOutputPhases
atsCalibrationNumOutputPhases.description: The number of output phases utilized in this device.

atsCalibrationOutputTable.name: atsCalibrationOutputTable
atsCalibrationOutputTable.description: A list of output table entries.

atsCalibrationOutputEntry.name: atsCalibrationOutputEntry
atsCalibrationOutputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output.

atsCalibrationOutputPhasesTableIndex.name: atsCalibrationOutputPhasesTableIndex
atsCalibrationOutputPhasesTableIndex.description: Description of each calibration factor for each output phase utilized in this device and one for neutral.

atsOutputCurrentCalibrationFactor.name: atsOutputCurrentCalibrationFactor
atsOutputCurrentCalibrationFactor.description: The output current calibration factor measured in Amps.

ats4gCalibrationOutputTable.name: ats4gCalibrationOutputTable
ats4gCalibrationOutputTable.description: A list of output table entries. It is not applicable to AP77xx ATS units.

ats4gCalibrationOutputEntry.name: ats4gCalibrationOutputEntry
ats4gCalibrationOutputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output.

ats4gCalibrationOutputPhasesTableIndex.name: ats4gCalibrationOutputPhasesTableIndex
ats4gCalibrationOutputPhasesTableIndex.description: Description of each calibration factor for each output phase utilized in this device and one for neutral. Bank 1 and Bank 2 are for units with two circuit breakers. It is not applicable to AP77xx ATS units.

ats4gOutputCurrentCalibrationFactor.name: ats4gOutputCurrentCalibrationFactor
ats4gOutputCurrentCalibrationFactor.description: The output current calibration factor measured in Amps. It is not applicable to AP7xxx ATS units.

atsControlResetATS.name: atsControlResetATS
atsControlResetATS.description: Setting this variable will cause the Automatic Transfer Switch to perform a power-on reset. It is not applicable to AP44xx units.

atsControlClearAllAlarms.name: atsControlClearAllAlarms
atsControlClearAllAlarms.description: Setting this variable will clear all alarms in the Automatic Transfer Switch. Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsConfigPreferredSource.name: atsConfigPreferredSource
atsConfigPreferredSource.description: This variable returns the preferred source of power when both sources are OK.

atsConfigFrontPanelLockout.name: atsConfigFrontPanelLockout
atsConfigFrontPanelLockout.description: Setting this variable to disableFrontPanel(1), prevents source preference configuration of the Automatic Transfer Switch via the Front Panel. Setting this variable to enableFrontPanel(2)allows, source preference configuration of the Automatic Transfer Switch via the Front Panel.

atsConfigVoltageSensitivity.name: atsConfigVoltageSensitivity
atsConfigVoltageSensitivity.description: This variable defines the sensitivity to changes in voltage: high(1) for best protection, low(2) for frequent small line voltage changes.

atsConfigTransferVoltageRange.name: atsConfigTransferVoltageRange
atsConfigTransferVoltageRange.description: This variable defines the range of acceptable voltage from a power source. If the voltage measured from the selected input source is not within this range, the Automatic Transfer Switch will switch over (transfer) to the alternate power source.

atsConfigCurrentLimit.name: atsConfigCurrentLimit
atsConfigCurrentLimit.description: The threshold (in Amps) at which an Over Current Alarm will be generated. This OID returns the overload threshold value of the OID atsConfigPhaseOverLoadThreshold for the 1U ATS and OID atsConfigBankOverLoadThreshold of total for the 2U ATS. Setting this OID does not have any impact on the device.

atsConfigResetValues.name: atsConfigResetValues
atsConfigResetValues.description: Resets the ATS configuration to its default values. Returns (-1) if not supported.

atsConfigLineVRMS.name: atsConfigLineVRMS
atsConfigLineVRMS.description: To configure the input RMS voltage.

atsConfigLineVRMSNarrowLimit.name: atsConfigLineVRMSNarrowLimit
atsConfigLineVRMSNarrowLimit.description: To configure the Line VRMS Narrow Limit.

atsConfigLineVRMSMediumLimit.name: atsConfigLineVRMSMediumLimit
atsConfigLineVRMSMediumLimit.description: To configure the Line VRMS Medium Limit.

atsConfigLineVRMSWideLimit.name: atsConfigLineVRMSWideLimit
atsConfigLineVRMSWideLimit.description: To configure the Line VRMS Wide Limit.

atsConfigFrequencyDeviation.name: atsConfigFrequencyDeviation
atsConfigFrequencyDeviation.description: To configure the frequency deviation. AP77xx units uses the options of 1, 2, or 3. AP44xx units uses the options of 3, 5, or 10.

atsConfigBankTableSize.name: atsConfigBankTableSize
atsConfigBankTableSize.description: The size of the bank table.

atsConfigBankTable.name: atsConfigBankTable
atsConfigBankTable.description: Allows for configuration of each ATS bank.

atsConfigBankEntry.name: atsConfigBankEntry
atsConfigBankEntry.description: This gives access to bank current threshold

atsConfigBankTableIndex.name: atsConfigBankTableIndex
atsConfigBankTableIndex.description: An index to the bank table entry.

atsConfigBank.name: atsConfigBank
atsConfigBank.description: The bank number of an ATS

atsConfigBankLowLoadThreshold.name: atsConfigBankLowLoadThreshold
atsConfigBankLowLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the current drawn is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is less than the threshold value. A threshold value of 0 Amps disables this warning. Maximum value must be less than the value returned by the atsConfigBankNearOverLoadThreshold OID.

atsConfigBankNearOverLoadThreshold.name: atsConfigBankNearOverLoadThreshold
atsConfigBankNearOverLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the current drawn is nearing an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than the value returned by the atsConfigBankLowLoadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the atsConfigBankOverLoadThreshold OID.

atsConfigBankOverLoadThreshold.name: atsConfigBankOverLoadThreshold
atsConfigBankOverLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the current drawn has entered an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than or equal to the value returned by the atsConfigBankNearOverLoadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by atsIdentDeviceRating OID.

atsConfigPhaseTableSize.name: atsConfigPhaseTableSize
atsConfigPhaseTableSize.description: The size of the phase table.

atsConfigPhaseTable.name: atsConfigPhaseTable
atsConfigPhaseTable.description: Allows for configuration of each ATS phase.

atsConfigPhaseEntry.name: atsConfigPhaseEntry
atsConfigPhaseEntry.description: This gives access to phase threshold

atsConfigPhaseTableIndex.name: atsConfigPhaseTableIndex
atsConfigPhaseTableIndex.description: The index to the phase table entry.

atsConfigPhase.name: atsConfigPhase
atsConfigPhase.description: The phase number of an ATS

atsConfigPhaseLowLoadThreshold.name: atsConfigPhaseLowLoadThreshold
atsConfigPhaseLowLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the current drawn is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is less than the threshold value. A threshold value of 0 Amps disables this warning. Maximum value must be less than the value returned by the atsConfigPhaseNearOverLoadThreshold OID.

atsConfigPhaseNearOverLoadThreshold.name: atsConfigPhaseNearOverLoadThreshold
atsConfigPhaseNearOverLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the current drawn is nearing an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than the value returned by the atsConfigPhaseLowLoadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the atsConfigPhaseOverLoadThreshold OID.

atsConfigPhaseOverLoadThreshold.name: atsConfigPhaseOverLoadThreshold
atsConfigPhaseOverLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the current drawn has entered an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than or equal to the value returned by the atsConfigPhaseNearOverLoadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by atsIdentDeviceRating OID.

atsStatusCommStatus.name: atsStatusCommStatus
atsStatusCommStatus.description: This variable returns the current communication status of the Automatic Transfer Switch.

atsStatusSelectedSource.name: atsStatusSelectedSource
atsStatusSelectedSource.description: This variable returns the current source of power.

atsStatusRedundancyState.name: atsStatusRedundancyState
atsStatusRedundancyState.description: This variable returns the current redundancy state of the ATS. atsRedundancyLost(1) indicates that the ATS is unable to switch over to the alternate power source if the current source fails. atsFullyRedundant(2) indicates that the ATS will switch over to the alternate power source if the current source fails.

atsStatusOverCurrentState.name: atsStatusOverCurrentState
atsStatusOverCurrentState.description: This variable returns the output current state of the ATS. atsOverCurrent(1) indicates that the ATS has exceeded the output current threshold and will not allow a switch over to the alternate power source if the current source fails. atsCurrentOK(2) indicates that the output current is below the output current threshold. This OID returns the value of the OID atsOutputPhaseState for the 1U ATS and OID atsOutputBankState for the 2U ATS.

atsStatus5VPowerSupply.name: atsStatus5VPowerSupply
atsStatus5VPowerSupply.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS 5V power supply. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the 5V power supply has failed and that the ATS serial port Configuration Menu is not accessible . atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS 5V power supply is operating within tolerance. This is only supported by AP77xx SKUs.

atsStatus24VPowerSupply.name: atsStatus24VPowerSupply
atsStatus24VPowerSupply.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS 24V power supply for Source A. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the 24V power supply has failed and the ATS is unable to switch over to the alternate power source if the current source fails. atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS 24V power supply is operating within tolerance.

atsStatus24VSourceBPowerSupply.name: atsStatus24VSourceBPowerSupply
atsStatus24VSourceBPowerSupply.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS 24V power supply for Source B. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the 24V power supply has failed and the ATS is unable to switch over to the alternate power source if the current source fails. atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS 24V power supply is operating within tolerance.

atsStatusPlus12VPowerSupply.name: atsStatusPlus12VPowerSupply
atsStatusPlus12VPowerSupply.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS 12V power supply. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the 12V power supply has failed and the ATS is unable to monitor the current sensors. atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS 12V power supply is operating within tolerance. This is only supported by AP77xx SKUs.

atsStatusMinus12VPowerSupply.name: atsStatusMinus12VPowerSupply
atsStatusMinus12VPowerSupply.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS -12V power supply. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the -12V power supply has failed and the ATS is unable to monitor the current sensors. atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS -12V power supply is operating within tolerance. This is only supported by AP77xx SKUs.

atsStatusSwitchStatus.name: atsStatusSwitchStatus
atsStatusSwitchStatus.description: This variable returns the status of the ATS.

atsStatusFrontPanel.name: atsStatusFrontPanel
atsStatusFrontPanel.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS front panel. locked(1): Front panel button cannot be used to change the sources. unlocked(2): Front panel button can be used to change the sources.

atsStatusSourceAStatus.name: atsStatusSourceAStatus
atsStatusSourceAStatus.description: This variable returns the status of the Source A.

atsStatusSourceBStatus.name: atsStatusSourceBStatus
atsStatusSourceBStatus.description: This variable returns the status of the Source B.

atsStatusPhaseSyncStatus.name: atsStatusPhaseSyncStatus
atsStatusPhaseSyncStatus.description: This variable returns the status of the phase synch.

atsStatusVoltageOutStatus.name: atsStatusVoltageOutStatus
atsStatusVoltageOutStatus.description: This variable returns the output voltage status.

atsStatusHardwareStatus.name: atsStatusHardwareStatus
atsStatusHardwareStatus.description: This variable returns the status of display board hardware.

atsStatus3dot3VPowerSupply.name: atsStatus3dot3VPowerSupply
atsStatus3dot3VPowerSupply.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS 3.3V power supply. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the 3.3V power supply has failed. atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS 3.3V power supply is operating within tolerance. This is only supported by AP44xx units.

atsStatus1Dot0VPowerSupply.name: atsStatus1Dot0VPowerSupply
atsStatus1Dot0VPowerSupply.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS 1.0V power supply. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the 1V power supply has failed. atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS 1.0V power supply is operating within tolerance. This is only supported by AP44xx units.

atsStatusVBoostSourceA.name: atsStatusVBoostSourceA
atsStatusVBoostSourceA.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS Source A Boost 48V voltage. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the ATS Source A Boost 48V voltage has failed. atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS Source A Boost 48V voltage is operating within tolerance. This is only supported by AP44xx units.

atsStatusVBoostSourceB.name: atsStatusVBoostSourceB
atsStatusVBoostSourceB.description: This variable returns the present state of the ATS Source B Boost 48V voltage. atsPowerSupplyFailure(1) indicates the ATS Source B Boost 48V voltage has failed. atsPowerSupplyOK(2) indicates that the ATS Source B Boost 48V voltage is operating within tolerance. This is only supported by AP44xx units.

atsStatusResetMaxMinValues.name: atsStatusResetMaxMinValues
atsStatusResetMaxMinValues.description: Resets the maximum and minimum ATS values: atsInputMaxVoltage, atsInputMinVoltage, atsInputMaxCurrent, atsInputMinCurrent, atsInputMaxPower, atsInputMinPower, atsOutputMaxCurrent, atsOutputMinCurrent, atsOutputMaxLoad, atsOutputMinLoad, atsOutputMaxPercentLoad, atsOutputMinPercentLoad, atsOutputMaxPower, atsOutputMinPower, atsOutputMaxPercentPower, atsOutputMinPercentPower. These variables represent the maximum and minimum ATS values since the last time they were read or reset by this OID. Values unsupported by this ATS will return (-1).

atsNumInputs.name: atsNumInputs
atsNumInputs.description: The number of input feeds to this device. This variable indicates the number of rows in the input table.

atsInputTable.name: atsInputTable
atsInputTable.description: A list of input table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of atsNumInputs.

atsInputEntry.name: atsInputEntry
atsInputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular input.

atsNumInputPhases.name: atsNumInputPhases
atsNumInputPhases.description: The number of input phases utilized in this device. The sum of all the atsNumInputPhases variable indicates the number of rows in the input phase table.

atsInputVoltageOrientation.name: atsInputVoltageOrientation
atsInputVoltageOrientation.description: The input voltage orientation: 1: unknown for this Source 2: singlePhase - phase 1 voltage is between Phase 1 and Neutral. 3: splitPhase - phase 1 voltage is between Phase 1 and Neutral; phase 2 voltage is between Phase 2 and Neutral; phase 3 voltage is between Phase 1 and Phase 2. 4: threePhasePhaseToNeutral - phase 1 voltage is between Phase 1 and Neutral; phase 2 voltage is between Phase 2 and Neutral; phase 3 voltage is between Phase 3 and Neutral. 5: threePhasePhaseToPhase - phase 1 voltage is between Phase 1 and Phase 2; phase 2 voltage is between Phase 2 and Phase 3; phase 3 voltage is between Phase 3 and Phase 1.

atsInputFrequency.name: atsInputFrequency
atsInputFrequency.description: The input frequency in Hertz, or -1 if it's unsupported by this Source.

atsInputName.name: atsInputName
atsInputName.description: A name given to a particular input.

atsInputPhaseTable.name: atsInputPhaseTable
atsInputPhaseTable.description: A list of input table entries. The number of entries is given by the sum of the atsNumInputPhases.

atsInputPhaseEntry.name: atsInputPhaseEntry
atsInputPhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular input phase.

atsInputVoltage.name: atsInputVoltage
atsInputVoltage.description: The input voltage in VAC, or -1 if it's unsupported by this Source.

atsInputMaxVoltage.name: atsInputMaxVoltage
atsInputMaxVoltage.description: The maximum input voltage in VAC measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsInputMinVoltage.name: atsInputMinVoltage
atsInputMinVoltage.description: The minimum input voltage in VAC measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsInputCurrent.name: atsInputCurrent
atsInputCurrent.description: The input current in amperes, or -1 if it's unsupported by this Source.

atsInputMaxCurrent.name: atsInputMaxCurrent
atsInputMaxCurrent.description: The maximum input current in amperes measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsInputMinCurrent.name: atsInputMinCurrent
atsInputMinCurrent.description: The minimum input current in amperes measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsInputPower.name: atsInputPower
atsInputPower.description: The input power in Watts, or -1 if it's unsupported by this Source.

atsInputMaxPower.name: atsInputMaxPower
atsInputMaxPower.description: The maximum input power in Watts measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsInputMinPower.name: atsInputMinPower
atsInputMinPower.description: The minimum input power in Watts measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsNumOutputs.name: atsNumOutputs
atsNumOutputs.description: The number of output feeds to this device. This variable indicates the number of rows in the output table.

atsOutputTable.name: atsOutputTable
atsOutputTable.description: A list of output table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of atsOutputNumPhases.

atsOutputEntry.name: atsOutputEntry
atsOutputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output.

atsNumOutputPhases.name: atsNumOutputPhases
atsNumOutputPhases.description: The number of output phases utilized in this device. The sum of all the atsNumOutputPhases variable indicates the number of rows in the output phase table.

atsOutputVoltageOrientation.name: atsOutputVoltageOrientation
atsOutputVoltageOrientation.description: The output voltage orientation: 1: unknown for this ATS 2: singlePhase - phase 1 voltage is between Phase 1 and Neutral. 3: splitPhase - phase 1 voltage is between Phase 1 and Neutral; phase 2 voltage is between Phase 2 and Neutral; phase 3 voltage is between Phase 1 and Phase 2. 4: threePhasePhaseToNeutral - phase 1 voltage is between Phase 1 and Neutral; phase 2 voltage is between Phase 2 and Neutral; phase 3 voltage is between Phase 3 and Neutral. 5: threePhasePhaseToPhase - phase 1 voltage is between Phase 1 and Phase 2; phase 2 voltage is between Phase 2 and Phase 3; phase 3 voltage is between Phase 3 and Phase 1.

atsOutputFrequency.name: atsOutputFrequency
atsOutputFrequency.description: The output frequency in Hertz, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputPhaseTable.name: atsOutputPhaseTable
atsOutputPhaseTable.description: A list of output table entries. The number of entries is given by the sum of the atsNumOutputPhases.

atsOutputPhaseEntry.name: atsOutputPhaseEntry
atsOutputPhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output phase.

atsOutputPhaseIndex.name: atsOutputPhaseIndex
atsOutputPhaseIndex.description: Description of each output phase utilized in this device and one for neutral.

atsOutputVoltage.name: atsOutputVoltage
atsOutputVoltage.description: The output voltage in VAC, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputCurrent.name: atsOutputCurrent
atsOutputCurrent.description: The output current in 0.1 amperes drawn by the load on the ATS, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputMaxCurrent.name: atsOutputMaxCurrent
atsOutputMaxCurrent.description: The maximum output current in 0.1 amperes measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputMinCurrent.name: atsOutputMinCurrent
atsOutputMinCurrent.description: The minimum output current in 0.1 amperes measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputLoad.name: atsOutputLoad
atsOutputLoad.description: The output load in VA, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputMaxLoad.name: atsOutputMaxLoad
atsOutputMaxLoad.description: The maximum output load in VA measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputMinLoad.name: atsOutputMinLoad
atsOutputMinLoad.description: The minimum output load in VA measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputPercentLoad.name: atsOutputPercentLoad
atsOutputPercentLoad.description: The percentage of the ATS load capacity in VA at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this output phase, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputMaxPercentLoad.name: atsOutputMaxPercentLoad
atsOutputMaxPercentLoad.description: The maximum percentage of the ATS load capacity in VA measured at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this output phase since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputMinPercentLoad.name: atsOutputMinPercentLoad
atsOutputMinPercentLoad.description: The minimum percentage of the ATS load capacity in VA measured at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this output phase since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputPower.name: atsOutputPower
atsOutputPower.description: The output power in VA, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputMaxPower.name: atsOutputMaxPower
atsOutputMaxPower.description: The maximum output power in VAs measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputMinPower.name: atsOutputMinPower
atsOutputMinPower.description: The minimum output power in VA measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputPercentPower.name: atsOutputPercentPower
atsOutputPercentPower.description: The percentage of the ATSpower capacity in VA at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this output phase, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputMaxPercentPower.name: atsOutputMaxPercentPower
atsOutputMaxPercentPower.description: The maximum percentage of the ATSpower capacity in VA measured at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this output phase since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputMinPercentPower.name: atsOutputMinPercentPower
atsOutputMinPercentPower.description: The minimum percentage of the ATSpower capacity in VA measured at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this output phase since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputPhaseState.name: atsOutputPhaseState
atsOutputPhaseState.description: Getting this OID will return the phase load state. normal(1) indicates that the bank is operating properly within the atsConfigPhaseLowLoadThreshold and atsConfigPhaseNearOverLoadThreshold OID values. lowload(2) indicates that the bank load has dropped below the atsConfigPhaseLowLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. nearoverload(3) indicates that the bank load is greater than or equal to the atsConfigPhaseNearOverLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. overload(4) indicates that the bank load is greater than or equal to the atsConfigPhaseOverLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared.

atsOutputBankTableSize.name: atsOutputBankTableSize
atsOutputBankTableSize.description: The size of the bank table.

atsOutputBankEntry.name: atsOutputBankEntry
atsOutputBankEntry.description: This gives access to bank table entries

atsOutputBankTableIndex.name: atsOutputBankTableIndex
atsOutputBankTableIndex.description: The index to the bank table entry.

atsOutputPhase.name: atsOutputPhase
atsOutputPhase.description: The phase number of an ATS

atsOutputBank.name: atsOutputBank
atsOutputBank.description: The bank number of an ATS

atsOutputBankCurrent.name: atsOutputBankCurrent
atsOutputBankCurrent.description: Getting this OID will return the bank current measured in tenths of Amps.

atsOutputBankState.name: atsOutputBankState
atsOutputBankState.description: Getting this OID will return the bank load state. normal(1) indicates that the bank is operating properly within the atsConfigBankLowLoadThreshold and atsConfigBankNearOverLoadThreshold OID values. lowload(2) indicates that the bank load has dropped below the atsConfigBankLowLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. nearoverload(3) indicates that the bank load is greater than or equal to the atsConfigBankNearOverLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. overload(4) indicates that the bank load is greater than or equal to the atsConfigBankOverLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared.

atsOutputBankOutputVoltage.name: atsOutputBankOutputVoltage
atsOutputBankOutputVoltage.description: The output voltage in VAC, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputBankMaxCurrent.name: atsOutputBankMaxCurrent
atsOutputBankMaxCurrent.description: The maximum output current, on the bank represented by OID atsOutputBank, in 0.1 amperes measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankMinCurrent.name: atsOutputBankMinCurrent
atsOutputBankMinCurrent.description: The minimum output current, on the bank represented by OID atsOutputBank, in 0.1 amperes measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankLoad.name: atsOutputBankLoad
atsOutputBankLoad.description: The output load, on the bank represented by OID atsOutputBank, in VA, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputBankMaxLoad.name: atsOutputBankMaxLoad
atsOutputBankMaxLoad.description: The maximum output load, on the bank represented by OID atsOutputBank, in VA measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankMinLoad.name: atsOutputBankMinLoad
atsOutputBankMinLoad.description: The minimum output load, on the bank represented by OID atsOutputBank, in VA measured since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankPercentLoad.name: atsOutputBankPercentLoad
atsOutputBankPercentLoad.description: The percentage of the ATS load capacity in VA at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this bank, represented by OID atsOutputBank. Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankMaxPercentLoad.name: atsOutputBankMaxPercentLoad
atsOutputBankMaxPercentLoad.description: The maximum percentage of the ATS load capacity in VA measured at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this bank, represented by OID atsOutputBank, since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankMinPercentLoad.name: atsOutputBankMinPercentLoad
atsOutputBankMinPercentLoad.description: The minimum percentage of the ATS load capacity in VA measured at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this bank, represented by OID atsOutputBank, since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankPower.name: atsOutputBankPower
atsOutputBankPower.description: The output power in VA on the bank represented by OID atsOutputBank or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputBankMaxPower.name: atsOutputBankMaxPower
atsOutputBankMaxPower.description: The maximum output power in VA measured on the bank represented by OID atsOutputBank since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankMinPower.name: atsOutputBankMinPower
atsOutputBankMinPower.description: The minimum output power in VA measured on the bank represented by OID atsOutputBank since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankPercentPower.name: atsOutputBankPercentPower
atsOutputBankPercentPower.description: The percentage of the ATSpower capacity in Watts at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this bank, represented by OID atsOutputBank, or -1 if it's unsupported by this ATS.

atsOutputBankMaxPercentPower.name: atsOutputBankMaxPercentPower
atsOutputBankMaxPercentPower.description: The maximum percentage of the ATSpower capacity in VA measured at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this bank, represented by OID atsOutputBank, since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

atsOutputBankMinPercentPower.name: atsOutputBankMinPercentPower
atsOutputBankMinPercentPower.description: The minimum percentage of the ATSpower capacity in VA measured at redundancy @ (n + x) presently being used on this bank, represented by OID atsOutputBank since the last time this variable was read or reset (atsStatusResetMaxMinValues). Returns (-1) if unsupported.

dcmim2IdentSysFWVersion.name: dcmim2IdentSysFWVersion
dcmim2IdentSysFWVersion.description: Integer representation of the power plant Master Controller firmware revision.

dcmim2ControlRunFunctBatteryTest.name: dcmim2ControlRunFunctBatteryTest
dcmim2ControlRunFunctBatteryTest.description: Getting this OID will return the battery functional test state. If the test is off, the battTestOff (1) value will be returned. If the test is on, the battTestOn (2) value will be returned. Setting this OID to battTestOff (1) will turn the battery functional test off. Setting this OID to battTestOn (2) will turn the battery functional test on.

dcmim2ControlRunCapacityBatteryTest.name: dcmim2ControlRunCapacityBatteryTest
dcmim2ControlRunCapacityBatteryTest.description: Getting this OID will return the battery capacity test state. If the test is off, the battTestOff (1) value will be returned. If the test is on, the battTestOn (2) value will be returned. Setting this OID to battTestOff (1) will turn the battery capacity test off. Setting this OID to battTestOn (2) will turn the battery capacity test on.

dcmim2ConfigSysHighTempTrip.name: dcmim2ConfigSysHighTempTrip
dcmim2ConfigSysHighTempTrip.description: Trip level (threshold) at which System High Temp alarm condition is created. Range 28 to 100 (degC). Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

dcmim2ConfigSysHighTempReset.name: dcmim2ConfigSysHighTempReset
dcmim2ConfigSysHighTempReset.description: Level at which System High Temp alarm condition is reset (cleared). Range 25 to (upper temp - 3) (degC). Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

dcmim2ConfigSysLowTempTrip.name: dcmim2ConfigSysLowTempTrip
dcmim2ConfigSysLowTempTrip.description: Trip level (threshold) at which System Low Temp alarm condition is created. Range -100 to 10 (degC). Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

dcmim2ConfigSysLowTempReset.name: dcmim2ConfigSysLowTempReset
dcmim2ConfigSysLowTempReset.description: Level at which System Low Temp alarm condition is reset (cleared). Range (lower temp + 3) to 13 (degC). Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

dcmim2ConfigBattFloatVolt.name: dcmim2ConfigBattFloatVolt
dcmim2ConfigBattFloatVolt.description: Battery Float Voltage defined at 25 degrees Celsius. Values are represented in thousandths of Volts (mV).

dcmim2ConfigBattMaxRecharge.name: dcmim2ConfigBattMaxRecharge
dcmim2ConfigBattMaxRecharge.description: Battery Maximum Recharge Rate. This is the maximum current used during battery charging. Values are represented in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dcmim2ConfigBattMfgCapacity.name: dcmim2ConfigBattMfgCapacity
dcmim2ConfigBattMfgCapacity.description: Battery capacity (Amp-Hour Size) as specified by the battery manufacturer. Values are represented in thousandths of Amp hours (mAHr).

dcmim2ConfigBattType.name: dcmim2ConfigBattType
dcmim2ConfigBattType.description: Type of battery in the powerplant Valid values range from 0 to 254.

dcmim2ConfigBattFunctTestDuration.name: dcmim2ConfigBattFunctTestDuration
dcmim2ConfigBattFunctTestDuration.description: Duration of the battery functional test. Values are represented in thousandths of seconds (mSecs).

dcmim2ConfigBattFunctTestThresh.name: dcmim2ConfigBattFunctTestThresh
dcmim2ConfigBattFunctTestThresh.description: Threshold the battery voltage of the system must remain above in order to pass the battery functional test. Values are represented in thousandths of Volts (mV).

dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestPercent.name: dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestPercent
dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestPercent.description: Threshold for good battery capacity test results. Values range from 0 to 100 percent.

dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestEndThresh.name: dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestEndThresh
dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestEndThresh.description: Safeguard voltage at which battery capacity test will end if there is a battery problem. Values are represented in thousandths of Volts (mV).

dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestCurrent.name: dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestCurrent
dcmim2ConfigBattCapacityTestCurrent.description: Constant current value used during battery capacity testing. Values are represented in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dcmim2ConfigLVDTableSize.name: dcmim2ConfigLVDTableSize
dcmim2ConfigLVDTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant LVDs controllable by this IP address.

dcmim2ConfigLVDTable.name: dcmim2ConfigLVDTable
dcmim2ConfigLVDTable.description: Allows for accessing settings of the LVDs. The number of entries is contained in the dcmim2ConfigLVDTableSize OID.

dcmim2ConfigLVDIndex.name: dcmim2ConfigLVDIndex
dcmim2ConfigLVDIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant LVD.

dcmim2ConfigLVDTrip.name: dcmim2ConfigLVDTrip
dcmim2ConfigLVDTrip.description: LVD Trip threshold. System bus voltage at which LVD will trip (open) during a battery backup operation. Values are represented in thousandths of Volts (mV).

dcmim2ConfigLVDReset.name: dcmim2ConfigLVDReset
dcmim2ConfigLVDReset.description: LVD Reset threshold. System bus voltage at which LVD will reset (close) after AC power has been restored. Values are represented in thousandths of Volts (mV).

dcmim2ConfigLVDState.name: dcmim2ConfigLVDState
dcmim2ConfigLVDState.description: Getting this OID will return statusClosed (1) if the LVD is closed. statusOpened (2) will be returned if the LVD is opened.

dcmim2StatusSysRectCurrent.name: dcmim2StatusSysRectCurrent
dcmim2StatusSysRectCurrent.description: System (Total Rectifier) current in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dcmim2StatusSysLoadCurrent.name: dcmim2StatusSysLoadCurrent
dcmim2StatusSysLoadCurrent.description: Load current in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dcmim2StatusSysBusVoltage.name: dcmim2StatusSysBusVoltage
dcmim2StatusSysBusVoltage.description: System bus voltage in thousandths of Volts (mV).

dcmim2StatusSysAmbientTemp.name: dcmim2StatusSysAmbientTemp
dcmim2StatusSysAmbientTemp.description: System temperature based on sensor on Master Controller PCB. Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

dcmim2StatusSysUpTime.name: dcmim2StatusSysUpTime
dcmim2StatusSysUpTime.description: Length of time since the DC Powerplant controller has been powered up.

dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits.name: dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits
dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits.description: The temperature scale used to display the temperature in the DC system, Celsius(1) or Fahrenheit(2). This setting is based on the system preferences configuration in the agent.

dcmim2StatusRectTableSize.name: dcmim2StatusRectTableSize
dcmim2StatusRectTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant rectifiers viewable by this IP address.

dcmim2StatusRectTable.name: dcmim2StatusRectTable
dcmim2StatusRectTable.description: Allows for accessing settings of the rectifiers. The number of entries is contained in the dcmim2StatusRectTableSize OID.

dcmim2StatusRectEntry.name: dcmim2StatusRectEntry
dcmim2StatusRectEntry.description: The rectifier to gather status from.

dcmim2StatusRectIndex.name: dcmim2StatusRectIndex
dcmim2StatusRectIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant rectifier.

dcmim2StatusRectDevType.name: dcmim2StatusRectDevType
dcmim2StatusRectDevType.description: This OID shows the rectifier device type.

dcmim2StatusRectID.name: dcmim2StatusRectID
dcmim2StatusRectID.description: This OID shows the rectifier ID. This enumerates the number of the rectifier within a group of rectifiers.

dcmim2StatusRectPhyAddr.name: dcmim2StatusRectPhyAddr
dcmim2StatusRectPhyAddr.description: This OID shows the rectifier physical address (the address on the bus).

dcmim2StatusRectFail.name: dcmim2StatusRectFail
dcmim2StatusRectFail.description: Getting this OID will return statusTrue (1) if the rectifier has failed. statusFalse (2) will be returned if the rectifier has not failed.

dcmim2StatusRectCurrent.name: dcmim2StatusRectCurrent
dcmim2StatusRectCurrent.description: This OID shows the individual rectifier current in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dcmim2StatusBattFloatVolt.name: dcmim2StatusBattFloatVolt
dcmim2StatusBattFloatVolt.description: Battery Float Voltage represented in thousandths of Volts (mV).

dcmim2StatusBattCurrent.name: dcmim2StatusBattCurrent
dcmim2StatusBattCurrent.description: Battery Current: This OID shows the battery current in thousandths of Amps (mA).

dcmim2StatusBattTemp.name: dcmim2StatusBattTemp
dcmim2StatusBattTemp.description: Battery Temperature: Values are represented in thousandths of a degree. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the 'dcmim2StatusSysTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

dcmim2StatusBattMfgCapacity.name: dcmim2StatusBattMfgCapacity
dcmim2StatusBattMfgCapacity.description: Battery capacity (Amp-Hour Size) as specified by the battery manufacturer. Values are represented in thousandths of Amp hours (mAHr).

dcmim2StatusBattTestCapacity.name: dcmim2StatusBattTestCapacity
dcmim2StatusBattTestCapacity.description: Battery capacity (Amp-Hour Size) as determined by the battery capacity test. Values are represented in thousandths of Amp hours (mAHr).

dcmim2StatusBattFunctTestResult.name: dcmim2StatusBattFunctTestResult
dcmim2StatusBattFunctTestResult.description: Results of the last battery functional test that was run.

dcmim2StatusBattCapacityTestResult.name: dcmim2StatusBattCapacityTestResult
dcmim2StatusBattCapacityTestResult.description: Results of the last battery capacity test that was run.

dcmim2StatusLVDTableSize.name: dcmim2StatusLVDTableSize
dcmim2StatusLVDTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant LVDs accessible by this IP address.

dcmim2StatusLVDTable.name: dcmim2StatusLVDTable
dcmim2StatusLVDTable.description: Allows for accessing the LVDs. The number of entries is contained in the dcmim2StatusLVDTableSize OID.

dcmim2StatusLVDIndex.name: dcmim2StatusLVDIndex
dcmim2StatusLVDIndex.description: The index to the DC powerplant LVD.

dcmim2StatusLVDState.name: dcmim2StatusLVDState
dcmim2StatusLVDState.description: Getting this OID will return statusClosed (1) if the LVD is closed. statusOpened (2) will be returned if the LVD is opened.

dcmim2StatusAlarmsTableSize.name: dcmim2StatusAlarmsTableSize
dcmim2StatusAlarmsTableSize.description: The number of DC powerplant alarms viewable by this IP address.

dcmim2StatusAlarmsTable.name: dcmim2StatusAlarmsTable
dcmim2StatusAlarmsTable.description: Allows for accessing system alarms. The number of entries is contained in the dcmim2StatusAlarmsTableSize OID.

dcmim2StatusAlarmsIndex.name: dcmim2StatusAlarmsIndex
dcmim2StatusAlarmsIndex.description: The index of the system alarm.

dcmim2StatusAlarmsText.name: dcmim2StatusAlarmsText
dcmim2StatusAlarmsText.description: The 16 character text describing the active alarm condition.

emIdentFirmwareRevision.name: emIdentFirmwareRevision
emIdentFirmwareRevision.description: The firmware revision of the Environmental Monitor.

emConfigProbesNumProbes.name: emConfigProbesNumProbes
emConfigProbesNumProbes.description: The number of temperature and humidity probes available.

emConfigProbesTable.name: emConfigProbesTable
emConfigProbesTable.description: A list of probes supported by the Environmental Monitor and their configurations.

emConfigProbeNumber.name: emConfigProbeNumber
emConfigProbeNumber.description: The index into an Environmental Monitor probe entry.

emConfigProbeName.name: emConfigProbeName
emConfigProbeName.description: A descriptive name of the probe set by the user, possibly denoting its location or purpose.

emConfigProbeHighTempThreshold.name: emConfigProbeHighTempThreshold
emConfigProbeHighTempThreshold.description: The high temperature alarm threshold for the probe. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'emConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emConfigProbeLowTempThreshold.name: emConfigProbeLowTempThreshold
emConfigProbeLowTempThreshold.description: The low temperature alarm threshold for the probe. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'emConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emConfigProbeTempUnits.name: emConfigProbeTempUnits
emConfigProbeTempUnits.description: The temperature scale used to display the temperature thresholds of the probe, Celsius(1) or Fahrenheit(2). This setting is based on the system preferences configuration in the agent.

emConfigProbeHighHumidThreshold.name: emConfigProbeHighHumidThreshold
emConfigProbeHighHumidThreshold.description: The high humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity.

emConfigProbeLowHumidThreshold.name: emConfigProbeLowHumidThreshold
emConfigProbeLowHumidThreshold.description: The low humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity.

emConfigProbeHighTempEnable.name: emConfigProbeHighTempEnable
emConfigProbeHighTempEnable.description: The high temperature alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

emConfigProbeLowTempEnable.name: emConfigProbeLowTempEnable
emConfigProbeLowTempEnable.description: The low temperature alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

emConfigProbeHighHumidEnable.name: emConfigProbeHighHumidEnable
emConfigProbeHighHumidEnable.description: The high humidity alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

emConfigProbeLowHumidEnable.name: emConfigProbeLowHumidEnable
emConfigProbeLowHumidEnable.description: The low humidity alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

emConfigProbeMaxTempThreshold.name: emConfigProbeMaxTempThreshold
emConfigProbeMaxTempThreshold.description: The maximum temperature alarm threshold for the probe. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'emConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emConfigProbeMinTempThreshold.name: emConfigProbeMinTempThreshold
emConfigProbeMinTempThreshold.description: The minimum temperature alarm threshold for the probe. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'emConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emConfigProbeMaxHumidThreshold.name: emConfigProbeMaxHumidThreshold
emConfigProbeMaxHumidThreshold.description: The maximun humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity.

emConfigProbeMinHumidThreshold.name: emConfigProbeMinHumidThreshold
emConfigProbeMinHumidThreshold.description: The minimum humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity.

emConfigProbeMaxTempEnable.name: emConfigProbeMaxTempEnable
emConfigProbeMaxTempEnable.description: The maximum temperature alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

emConfigProbeMinTempEnable.name: emConfigProbeMinTempEnable
emConfigProbeMinTempEnable.description: The minimum temperature alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

emConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable.name: emConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable
emConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable.description: The maximum humidity alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

emConfigProbeMinHumidEnable.name: emConfigProbeMinHumidEnable
emConfigProbeMinHumidEnable.description: The minimum humidity alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

emConfigProbeTempHysteresis.name: emConfigProbeTempHysteresis
emConfigProbeTempHysteresis.description: The number of degrees beyond the temperature thresholds at which an active temperature alarm will be cleared. This configuration setting applies to all temperature thresholds. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'emConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emConfigProbeHumidHysteresis.name: emConfigProbeHumidHysteresis
emConfigProbeHumidHysteresis.description: The number of percent RH points beyond the humidity thresholds at which an active humidity alarm will be cleared. This configuration setting applies to all humidity thresholds. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'emConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emConfigProbeLocation.name: emConfigProbeLocation
emConfigProbeLocation.description: A string describing the location of the probe.

emConfigContactsNumContacts.name: emConfigContactsNumContacts
emConfigContactsNumContacts.description: The number of contacts supported by the Environmental Monitor.

emConfigContactsTable.name: emConfigContactsTable
emConfigContactsTable.description: A list of contacts supported by the Environmental Monitor and their configurations.

emConfigContactNumber.name: emConfigContactNumber
emConfigContactNumber.description: The index of an Environmental Monitor contact.

emConfigContactName.name: emConfigContactName
emConfigContactName.description: A descriptive name for an Environmental Monitor contact set by the user, possibly denoting its location or purpose.

emConfigContactEnable.name: emConfigContactEnable
emConfigContactEnable.description: An Environmental Monitor contact alarm enable/disable. No alarm will be generated if the contact is disabled(1). An alarm will be generated if the contact is enabled(2) and the contact has been faulted.

emConfigContactSeverity.name: emConfigContactSeverity
emConfigContactSeverity.description: The severity of the alarm that will be triggered when the input contact is activated. The alarms can be critical(1), warning(2) or informational(3).

emConfigContactNormalState.name: emConfigContactNormalState
emConfigContactNormalState.description: The contact state that will be considered normal, i.e. will not trigger an alarm. The states are open(1) or closed(2).

emConfigContactLocation.name: emConfigContactLocation
emConfigContactLocation.description: A descriptive label for the contact denoting its location or purpose.

emStatusCommStatus.name: emStatusCommStatus
emStatusCommStatus.description: The communication status between the agent and the Environmental Monitor. noComm(1), Communication has never been established. comm(2), Communication has been established. commLost(3), Communication was established, but was lost.

emStatusProbesNumProbes.name: emStatusProbesNumProbes
emStatusProbesNumProbes.description: The number of available probes on the Environmental Monitor.

emStatusProbesTable.name: emStatusProbesTable
emStatusProbesTable.description: A list of probes supported by the Environmental Monitor and their status.

emStatusProbeName.name: emStatusProbeName
emStatusProbeName.description: A descriptive name for the probe set by the user, possibly denoting its location or purpose.

emStatusProbeStatus.name: emStatusProbeStatus
emStatusProbeStatus.description: The connected status of the probe, either disconnected(1) or connected(2).

emStatusProbeCurrentTemp.name: emStatusProbeCurrentTemp
emStatusProbeCurrentTemp.description: The current temperature reading from the probe displayed in the units shown in the 'emStatusProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emStatusProbeTempUnits.name: emStatusProbeTempUnits
emStatusProbeTempUnits.description: The temperature scale used to display the temperature thresholds of the probe, Celsius(1) or Fahrenheit(2). This setting is based on the system preferences configuration in the agent.

emStatusProbeCurrentHumid.name: emStatusProbeCurrentHumid
emStatusProbeCurrentHumid.description: The current humidity reading from the probe in percent relative humidity.

emStatusProbeHighTempViolation.name: emStatusProbeHighTempViolation
emStatusProbeHighTempViolation.description: The high temperature violation status of the probe temperature reading. This OID will show a highTempViolation(2) if the current temperature reading shown in the 'emStatusProbeCurrentTemp' OID is greater than or equal to the high temperature threshold value, the 'emConfigProbeHighTempThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'emConfigProbeHighTempEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'emConfigProbeHighTempEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

emStatusProbeLowTempViolation.name: emStatusProbeLowTempViolation
emStatusProbeLowTempViolation.description: The high temperature violation status of the probe temperature reading. This OID will show a lowTempViolation(2) if the current temperature reading shown in the 'emStatusProbeCurrentTemp' OID is less than or equal to the low temperature threshold value, the 'emConfigProbeLowTempThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'emConfigProbeLowTempEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'emConfigProbeLowTempEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

emStatusProbeHighHumidViolation.name: emStatusProbeHighHumidViolation
emStatusProbeHighHumidViolation.description: The high humidity violation status of the probe humidity reading. This OID will show a highTempViolation(2) if the current humidity reading shown in the 'emStatusProbeCurrentHumid' OID is greater than or equal to the high humidity threshold value, the 'emConfigProbeHighHumidThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'emConfigProbeHighHumidEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'emConfigProbeHighHumidEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3)

emStatusProbeLowHumidViolation.name: emStatusProbeLowHumidViolation
emStatusProbeLowHumidViolation.description: The low humidity violation status of the probe humidity reading. This OID will show a lowTempViolation(2) if the current humidity reading shown in the 'emStatusProbeCurrentHumid' OID is less than or equal to the low humidity threshold value, the 'emConfigProbeLowHumidThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'emConfigProbeLowHumidEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'emConfigProbeLowHumidEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

emStatusProbeMaxTempViolation.name: emStatusProbeMaxTempViolation
emStatusProbeMaxTempViolation.description: The max temperature violation status of the probe temperature reading. This OID will show a maxTempViolation(2) if the current temperature reading shown in the 'emStatusProbeCurrentTemp' OID is greater than or equal to the maximun temperature threshold value, the 'emConfigProbeMaxTempThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'emConfigProbeMaxTempEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'emConfigProbeMaxTempEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

emStatusProbeMinTempViolation.name: emStatusProbeMinTempViolation
emStatusProbeMinTempViolation.description: The minimum temperature violation status of the probe temperature reading. This OID will show a minTempViolation(2) if the current temperature reading shown in the 'emStatusProbeCurrentTemp' OID is less than or equal to the minimum temperature threshold value, the 'emConfigProbeMinTempThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'emConfigProbeMinTempEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'emConfigProbeMinTempEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

emStatusProbeMaxHumidViolation.name: emStatusProbeMaxHumidViolation
emStatusProbeMaxHumidViolation.description: The maximum humidity violation status of the probe humidity reading. This OID will show a maxTempViolation(2) if the current humidity reading shown in the 'emStatusProbeCurrentHumid' OID is greater than or equal to the maximum humidity threshold value, the 'emConfigProbeMaxHumidThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'emConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'emConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3)

emStatusProbeMinHumidViolation.name: emStatusProbeMinHumidViolation
emStatusProbeMinHumidViolation.description: The minimum humidity violation status of the probe humidity reading. This OID will show a minTempViolation(2) if the current humidity reading shown in the 'emStatusProbeCurrentHumid' OID is less than or equal to the minimum humidity threshold value, the 'emConfigProbeMinHumidThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'emConfigProbeMinHumidEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'emConfigProbeMinHumidEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

emStatusContactsNumContacts.name: emStatusContactsNumContacts
emStatusContactsNumContacts.description: The number of contacts supported by the Environmental Monitor.

emStatusContactsTable.name: emStatusContactsTable
emStatusContactsTable.description: A list of contacts supported by the Environmental Monitor and their status.

emStatusContactNumber.name: emStatusContactNumber
emStatusContactNumber.description: The index of the Environmental Monitor contact.

emStatusContactName.name: emStatusContactName
emStatusContactName.description: A descriptive name for the Environmental Monitor contact set by the user, possibly denoting its location or purpose.

emStatusContactStatus.name: emStatusContactStatus
emStatusContactStatus.description: The status of the Environmental Monitor contact. The status will show noFault(1) if the contact is in the normal state and the 'emConfigContactEnable' OID is enabled. The status will show a fault(2) if the contact is faulted and the 'emContactEnable' OID is enabled. If the 'emConfigContactEnable' OID is disabled, the status will show disabled(3).

memSensorsTempMaxThresh.description: The temperature at which the MEM will generate a maximum temperature threshold violation alarm on this sensor. The temperature scale is based on the memSensorsStatusSysTempUnits OID.

memSensorsTempHighThresh.name: memSensorsTempHighThresh
memSensorsTempHighThresh.description: The temperature at which the MEM will generate a high temperature threshold violation alarm on this sensor. The temperature scale is based on the memSensorsStatusSysTempUnits OID.

memSensorsTempLowThresh.name: memSensorsTempLowThresh
memSensorsTempLowThresh.description: The temperature at which the MEM will generate a low temperature threshold violation alarm on this sensor. The temperature scale is based on the memSensorsStatusSysTempUnits OID.

memSensorsTempMinThresh.name: memSensorsTempMinThresh
memSensorsTempMinThresh.description: The temperature at which the MEM will generate a minimum temperature threshold violation alarm on this sensor. The temperature scale is based on the memSensorsStatusSysTempUnits OID.

memSensorsTempThreshHysteresis.name: memSensorsTempThreshHysteresis
memSensorsTempThreshHysteresis.description: The change in temperature required to cause a temperature alarm to change from an active to an inactive state. The temperature scale is based on the memSensorsStatusSysTempUnits OID.

memSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshValue.name: memSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshValue
memSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshValue.description: The value of the temperature short-term decreasing rate time that will cause an alarm to be generated. The temperature scale is based on the memSensorsStatusSysTempUnits OID.

memSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshTime.name: memSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshTime
memSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshTime.description: The time over which the temperature may not decrease beyond the value specified by the temperature short-term decreasing rate threshold value.

memSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshValue.name: memSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshValue
memSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshValue.description: The value of the temperature short-term increasing rate time that will cause an alarm to be generated. The temperature scale is based on the memSensorsStatusSysTempUnits OID.

memSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshTime.name: memSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshTime
memSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshTime.description: The time over which the temperature may not increase beyond the value specified by the temperature short-term increasing rate threshold value.

memSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshValue.name: memSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshValue
memSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshValue.description: The value of the temperature long-term decreasing rate time that will cause an alarm to be generated. The temperature scale is based on the memSensorsStatusSysTempUnits OID.

memSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshTime.name: memSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshTime
memSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshTime.description: The time over which the temperature may not decrease beyond the value specified by the temperature long-term decreasing rate threshold value.

memSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshValue.name: memSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshValue

memSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshTime.description: The time over which the temperature may not increase beyond the value specified by the temperature long-term increasing rate threshold value.

memSensorsHumidityLowThresh.name: memSensorsHumidityLowThresh
memSensorsHumidityLowThresh.description: The humidity at which the low humidity threshold alarm will be generated.

wirelessSensorStatusAlarmStatus.description: The alarm status of the wireless sensor. This integer should be interpreted as a bit map, with each bit representing the presence or absence of the specific alarm conditions listed below. The bit will be '1' if the condition is present, and '0' if the condition is not present. Bit Hex. Value Description 1 0x0001 Maximum temperature exceeded. 2 0x0002 High temperature exceeded. 3 0x0004 Low temperature exceeded. 4 0x0008 Minimum temperature exceeded. 5 0x0010 Maximum humidity exceeded. 6 0x0020 High humidity exceeded. 7 0x0040 Low humidity exceeded. 8 0x0080 Minimum humidity exceeded. 9 0x0100 Low battery exceeded. 10 0x0200 Minimum battery exceeded. 11 0x0400 Low signal strength exceeded. 12 0x0800 Minimum signal strength exceeded. 13 0x1000 Sensor inactive.

If the normal state is open, the normallyOpen (0) value will be returned. Setting this variable will change the normal state of the dry contact.

wirelessSensorPodConfigMinTempThresh.name: wirelessSensorPodConfigMinTempThresh

wirelessSensorPodConfigMaxHumidityThresh.description: Values are represented in whole number percentage.
