iemConfigProbesTable.name: iemConfigProbesTable
iemConfigProbesTable.description: A list of probes supported by the Environmental Monitor and their configurations.

iemConfigProbeNumber.name: iemConfigProbeNumber
iemConfigProbeNumber.description: The index to a Environmental Monitor probe entry.

iemConfigProbeName.name: iemConfigProbeName
iemConfigProbeName.description: A descriptive name for the probe set by the user, possibly denoting its location or purpose.

iemConfigProbeHighTempThreshold.name: iemConfigProbeHighTempThreshold
iemConfigProbeHighTempThreshold.description: The high temperature alarm threshold for the probe. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'iemConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

iemConfigProbeLowTempThreshold.name: iemConfigProbeLowTempThreshold
iemConfigProbeLowTempThreshold.description: The low temperature alarm threshold for the probe. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'iemConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

iemConfigProbeTempUnits.name: iemConfigProbeTempUnits
iemConfigProbeTempUnits.description: The temperature scale used to display the temperature thresholds of the probe, Celsius(1) or Fahrenheit(2). This setting is based on the system preferences configuration in the agent.

iemConfigProbeHighHumidThreshold.name: iemConfigProbeHighHumidThreshold
iemConfigProbeHighHumidThreshold.description: The high humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity.

iemConfigProbeLowHumidThreshold.name: iemConfigProbeLowHumidThreshold
iemConfigProbeLowHumidThreshold.description: The low humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity.

iemConfigProbeHighTempEnable.name: iemConfigProbeHighTempEnable
iemConfigProbeHighTempEnable.description: The high temperature alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

iemConfigProbeLowTempEnable.name: iemConfigProbeLowTempEnable
iemConfigProbeLowTempEnable.description: The low temperature alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

iemConfigProbeHighHumidEnable.name: iemConfigProbeHighHumidEnable
iemConfigProbeHighHumidEnable.description: The high humidity alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

iemConfigProbeLowHumidEnable.name: iemConfigProbeLowHumidEnable
iemConfigProbeLowHumidEnable.description: The low humidity alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

iemConfigProbeMaxTempThreshold.name: iemConfigProbeMaxTempThreshold
iemConfigProbeMaxTempThreshold.description: The maximun temperature alarm threshold for the probe. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'iemConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

iemConfigProbeMinTempThreshold.name: iemConfigProbeMinTempThreshold
iemConfigProbeMinTempThreshold.description: The minimun temperature alarm threshold for the probe. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'iemConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

iemConfigProbeMaxHumidThreshold.name: iemConfigProbeMaxHumidThreshold
iemConfigProbeMaxHumidThreshold.description: The maximum humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity.

iemConfigProbeMinHumidThreshold.name: iemConfigProbeMinHumidThreshold
iemConfigProbeMinHumidThreshold.description: The minimum humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity.

iemConfigProbeMaxTempEnable.name: iemConfigProbeMaxTempEnable
iemConfigProbeMaxTempEnable.description: The maximum temperature alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

iemConfigProbeMinTempEnable.name: iemConfigProbeMinTempEnable
iemConfigProbeMinTempEnable.description: The low temperature alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

iemConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable.name: iemConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable
iemConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable.description: The maximum humidity alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

iemConfigProbeMinHumidEnable.name: iemConfigProbeMinHumidEnable
iemConfigProbeMinHumidEnable.description: The minimum humidity alarm enable/disable for the probe. No alarm will be generated if this value is set to disabled(1). The alarm will be generated if this value is set to enabled(2) and the threshold has been violated.

iemConfigProbeTempHysteresis.name: iemConfigProbeTempHysteresis
iemConfigProbeTempHysteresis.description: The number of degrees beyond the temperature thresholds at which an active temperature alarm will be cleared. This configuration setting applies to all temperature thresholds. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'emConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

iemConfigProbeHumidHysteresis.name: iemConfigProbeHumidHysteresis
iemConfigProbeHumidHysteresis.description: The number of percent RH points beyond the humidity thresholds at which an active humidity alarm will be cleared. This configuration setting applies to all humidity thresholds. Units are displayed in the scale selected in the 'emConfigProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

iemConfigProbeLocation.name: iemConfigProbeLocation
iemConfigProbeLocation.description: A string describing the location of the probe.

iemConfigContactsNumContacts.name: iemConfigContactsNumContacts
iemConfigContactsNumContacts.description: The number of contacts available on the Environmental Monitor.

iemConfigContactsTable.name: iemConfigContactsTable
iemConfigContactsTable.description: A list of contacts supported by the Environmental Monitor and their configurations.

iemConfigContactNumber.name: iemConfigContactNumber
iemConfigContactNumber.description: The index of an Environmental Monitor contact.

iemConfigContactName.name: iemConfigContactName
iemConfigContactName.description: A descriptive name for the Environmental Monitor contact set by the user, possibly denoting its location or purpose.

iemConfigContactEnable.name: iemConfigContactEnable
iemConfigContactEnable.description: An Environmental Monitor contact alarm enable/disable.

iemConfigContactSeverity.name: iemConfigContactSeverity
iemConfigContactSeverity.description: The severtity of the alarm that will be triggered when the input contact is activated. The alarms can be critical(1), warning(2) or informational(3). NOTE: informational(3) is deprecated (and no longer valid) for this OID.

iemConfigContactNormalState.name: iemConfigContactNormalState
iemConfigContactNormalState.description: The contact state that will be considered normal, i.e. will not trigger an alarm. The states are open(1) or closed(2).

iemConfigContactLocation.name: iemConfigContactLocation
iemConfigContactLocation.description: A descriptive label for the contact denoting its location or purpose.

iemConfigConfigRelaysNumRelays.name: iemConfigConfigRelaysNumRelays
iemConfigConfigRelaysNumRelays.description: The number of output relays supported by the Environmental Monitor.

iemConfigRelaysTable.name: iemConfigRelaysTable
iemConfigRelaysTable.description: A list of output relays supported by the Environmental Monitor and their configurations.

iemConfigRelaysEntry.name: iemConfigRelaysEntry
iemConfigRelaysEntry.description: The Environmental Monitor output relay configurations.

iemConfigRelayNumber.name: iemConfigRelayNumber
iemConfigRelayNumber.description: The index of an Environmental Monitor output relay.

iemConfigRelayName.name: iemConfigRelayName
iemConfigRelayName.description: A descriptive name of an Environmental Monitor output relay, set by the user, describing its location or purpose.

iemConfigRelayNormalState.name: iemConfigRelayNormalState
iemConfigRelayNormalState.description: The normal state (non-fault state) of an Environmental Monitor output relay, either open(1) or closed(2).

iemConfigRelayFaultCondition.name: iemConfigRelayFaultCondition
iemConfigRelayFaultCondition.description: The fault condition used to activate the output relay.

iemStatusProbesNumProbes.name: iemStatusProbesNumProbes
iemStatusProbesNumProbes.description: The number of available probes on the Environmental Monitor.

iemStatusProbesTable.name: iemStatusProbesTable
iemStatusProbesTable.description: A list of probes supported by the Environmental Monitor and their status.

iemStatusProbeName.name: iemStatusProbeName
iemStatusProbeName.description: A descriptive name for the probe set by the user.

iemStatusProbeStatus.name: iemStatusProbeStatus
iemStatusProbeStatus.description: The connected status of the probe, either disconnected(1) or connected(2).

iemStatusProbeCurrentTemp.name: iemStatusProbeCurrentTemp
iemStatusProbeCurrentTemp.description: The current temperature reading from the probe displayed in the units shown in the 'iemStatusProbeTempUnits' OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

iemStatusProbeTempUnits.name: iemStatusProbeTempUnits
iemStatusProbeTempUnits.description: The temperature scale used to display the temperature thresholds of the probe, Celsius(1) or Fahrenheit(2). This setting is based on the system preferences configuration in the agent.

iemStatusProbeCurrentHumid.name: iemStatusProbeCurrentHumid
iemStatusProbeCurrentHumid.description: The current humidity reading from the probe in percent relative humidity.

iemStatusProbeHighTempViolation.name: iemStatusProbeHighTempViolation
iemStatusProbeHighTempViolation.description: The high temperature violation status of the probe temperature reading. This OID will show a highTempViolation(2) if the current temperature reading shown in the 'iemStatusProbeCurrentTemp' OID is greater than or equal to the high temperature threshold value, the 'iemConfigProbeHighTempThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'iemConfigProbeHighTempEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'iemConfigProbeHighTempEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

iemStatusProbeLowTempViolation.name: iemStatusProbeLowTempViolation
iemStatusProbeLowTempViolation.description: The high temperature violation status of the probe temperature reading. This OID will show a lowTempViolation(2) if the current temperature reading shown in the 'iemStatusProbeCurrentTemp' OID is less than or equal to the low temperature threshold value, the 'iemConfigProbeLowTempThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'iemPConfigrobeLowTempEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'iemConfigProbeLowTempEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

iemStatusProbeHighHumidViolation.name: iemStatusProbeHighHumidViolation
iemStatusProbeHighHumidViolation.description: The high humidity violation status of the probe humidity reading. This OID will show a highTempViolation(2) if the current humidity reading shown in the 'iemStatusProbeCurrentHumid' OID is greater than or equal to the high humidity threshold value, the 'iemConfigProbeHighHumidThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'iemConfigProbeHighHumidEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'iemConfigProbeHighHumidEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

iemStatusProbeLowHumidViolation.name: iemStatusProbeLowHumidViolation
iemStatusProbeLowHumidViolation.description: The low humidity violation status of the probe humidity reading. This OID will show a lowTempViolation(2) if the current humidity reading shown in the 'iemStatusProbeCurrentHumid' OID is less than or equal to the low humidity threshold value, the 'iemConfigProbeLowHumidThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'iemConfigProbeLowHumidEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'iemConfigProbeLowHumidEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

iemStatusProbeMaxTempViolation.name: iemStatusProbeMaxTempViolation
iemStatusProbeMaxTempViolation.description: The max temperature violation status of the probe temperature reading. This OID will show a maxTempViolation(2) if the current temperature reading shown in the 'iemStatusProbeCurrentTemp' OID is greater than or equal to the maximun temperature threshold value, the 'iemConfigProbeMaxTempThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'iemConfigProbeMaxTempEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'iemConfigProbeMaxTempEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

iemStatusProbeMinTempViolation.name: iemStatusProbeMinTempViolation
iemStatusProbeMinTempViolation.description: The minimum temperature violation status of the probe temperature reading. This OID will show a minTempViolation(2) if the current temperature reading shown in the 'iemStatusProbeCurrentTemp' OID is less than or equal to the minimum temperature threshold value, the 'iemConfigProbeMinTempThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'iemConfigProbeMinTempEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'iemConfigProbeMinTempEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

iemStatusProbeMaxHumidViolation.name: iemStatusProbeMaxHumidViolation
iemStatusProbeMaxHumidViolation.description: The maximum humidity violation status of the probe humidity reading. This OID will show a maxTempViolation(2) if the current humidity reading shown in the 'iemStatusProbeCurrentHumid' OID is greater than or equal to the maximum humidity threshold value, the 'iemConfigProbeMaxHumidThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'iemConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'iemConfigProbeMaxHumidEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3)

iemStatusProbeMinHumidViolation.name: iemStatusProbeMinHumidViolation
iemStatusProbeMinHumidViolation.description: The minimum humidity violation status of the probe humidity reading. This OID will show a minTempViolation(2) if the current humidity reading shown in the 'iemStatusProbeCurrentHumid' OID is less than or equal to the minimum humidity threshold value, the 'iemConfigProbeMinHumidThreshold' OID, and the value of the 'iemConfigProbeMinHumidEnable' OID is enabled. Otherwise it will show noViolation(1). If the 'iemConfigProbeMinHumidEnable' OID is disabled, this OID will show disabled(3).

iemStatusProbeLocation.name: iemStatusProbeLocation
iemStatusProbeLocation.description: A descriptive location for the probe set by the user.

iemStatusContactsNumContacts.name: iemStatusContactsNumContacts
iemStatusContactsNumContacts.description: The number of contacts supported on the Environmental Monitor.

iemStatusContactsTable.name: iemStatusContactsTable
iemStatusContactsTable.description: A list of contacts supported by the Environmental Monitor and their status.

iemStatusContactNumber.name: iemStatusContactNumber
iemStatusContactNumber.description: The index of the Environmental Monitor contact.

iemStatusContactName.name: iemStatusContactName
iemStatusContactName.description: A descriptive name for the Environmental Monitor contact set by the user, denoting its location or purpose.

iemStatusContactStatus.name: iemStatusContactStatus
iemStatusContactStatus.description: The status of the Environmental Monitor contact. The status will show noFault(1) if the contact is in the normal state and the 'iemConfigContactEnable' OID is enabled. The status will show a fault(2) if the contact is faulted and the 'iemConfigContactEnable' OID is enabled. If the 'iemConfigContactEnable' OID is disabled, the status will show disabled(3).

iemStatusRelaysNumRelays.name: iemStatusRelaysNumRelays
iemStatusRelaysNumRelays.description: The number of output relays supported on the Environmental Monitor.

iemStatusRelaysTable.name: iemStatusRelaysTable
iemStatusRelaysTable.description: A list of output relays supported by the Environmental Monitor and their status.

iemStatusRelayNumber.name: iemStatusRelayNumber
iemStatusRelayNumber.description: The index of the output relay.

iemStatusRelayName.name: iemStatusRelayName
iemStatusRelayName.description: A descriptive name for the output relay set by the user, denoting its location or purpose.

iemStatusRelayStatus.name: iemStatusRelayStatus
iemStatusRelayStatus.description: The status of the output relay, either faultState(1) or normalState(2).

emsIdentEMSName.name: emsIdentEMSName
emsIdentEMSName.description: A character string identifying the device.

emsIdentProductNumber.name: emsIdentProductNumber
emsIdentProductNumber.description: A character string identifying the model number of the device. This value is set at the factory.

emsIdentFirmwareRev.name: emsIdentFirmwareRev
emsIdentFirmwareRev.description: The firmware revision of the device.

emsIdentHardwareRev.name: emsIdentHardwareRev
emsIdentHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the device. This value is set at the factory.

emsIdentDateOfManufacture.name: emsIdentDateOfManufacture
emsIdentDateOfManufacture.description: The date when the device was manufactured in mm/dd/yyyy format. This value is set at the factory.

emsIdentSerialNumber.name: emsIdentSerialNumber
emsIdentSerialNumber.description: A character string identifying the serial number of the device. This value is set at the factory.

emsOutputRelayControlTable.name: emsOutputRelayControlTable
emsOutputRelayControlTable.description: Allows for control of individual output relays. The number of entries is contained in the emsStatusOutputRelayCount OID.

emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayIndex.name: emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayIndex
emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayIndex.description: The index to the output relay entry.

emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayName.name: emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayName
emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayName.description: The name of the output relay. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayCommand.name: emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayCommand
emsOutputRelayControlOutputRelayCommand.description: Getting this variable will return the output relay state. If the output relay is closed, the immediateCloseEMS (1) value will be returned. If the output relay is open, the immediateOpenEMS (2) value will be returned. Setting this variable to immediateCloseEMS (1) will immediately close the relay. Setting this variable to immediateOpenEMS (2) will immediately open the relay.

emsOutletControlTable.name: emsOutletControlTable
emsOutletControlTable.description: Allows for control of individual outlet switches. The number of entries is contained in the emsStatusOutletCount OID.

emsOutletControlOutletIndex.name: emsOutletControlOutletIndex
emsOutletControlOutletIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

emsOutletControlOutletName.name: emsOutletControlOutletName
emsOutletControlOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

emsOutletControlOutletCommand.name: emsOutletControlOutletCommand
emsOutletControlOutletCommand.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the immediateOnEMS (1) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the immediateOffEMS (2) value will be returned. Setting this variable to immediateOnEMS (1) will immediately turn the outlet on. Setting this variable to immediateOffEMS (2) will immediately turn the outlet off.

emsSensorControlTable.name: emsSensorControlTable
emsSensorControlTable.description: Allows for control/reset of individual sensors. The number of entries is contained in the emsStatusSensorCount OID.

emsSensorControlSensorIndex.name: emsSensorControlSensorIndex
emsSensorControlSensorIndex.description: The index to the sensor entry.

emsSensorControlSensorSystemName.name: emsSensorControlSensorSystemName
emsSensorControlSensorSystemName.description: The system name of the sensor. This describes the hardware system intent of this sensor.

emsSensorControlSensorUserName.name: emsSensorControlSensorUserName
emsSensorControlSensorUserName.description: The name of the sensor as given by the system user.

emsSensorControlSensorCommand.name: emsSensorControlSensorCommand
emsSensorControlSensorCommand.description: Getting this variable will return noCommandEMS(1). Setting this variable to resetCommandEMS(2) will issue a reset command to the sensor. Some sensors cannot be manually reset and will not be affected by this command.

emsAlarmDeviceControlTable.name: emsAlarmDeviceControlTable
emsAlarmDeviceControlTable.description: Allows for control of individual alarm devices. Note: Some alarm devices are not controllable. The number of entries is contained in the emsStatusAlarmDeviceCount OID.

emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceIndex.name: emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceIndex
emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceIndex.description: The index to the alarm device entry.

emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceName.name: emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceName
emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceName.description: The name of the alarm device. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceCommand.name: emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceCommand
emsAlarmDeviceControlDeviceCommand.description: Getting this variable will return the device state. If the device is active, the alarmDeviceOnEMS (1) value will be returned. If the device is inactive, the alarmDeviceOffEMS (2) value will be returned. If the device is not installed, the alarmDeviceNotInstalledEMS (3) value will be returned. Actions resulting from setting this variable are device-dependent. Setting this variable to alarmDeviceOnEMS (1) will turn that device (ex. Beacon) on. Setting this variable to alarmDeviceOffEMS (2) will turn that device off.

emsConfigCheckLogLight.name: emsConfigCheckLogLight
emsConfigCheckLogLight.description: The setting of this OID determines the level of event that will trigger the check-log light on the EMS. This is not available on the EMU2. lightDisabled (1) disables the check-log light. lightOnInformational (2) lights check-log for any event of informational severity or above. lightOnWarning (3) lights check-log for any event of warning severity or above. lightOnSevere (4) lights check-log for any event of severe severity.

emsProbeConfigTable.name: emsProbeConfigTable
emsProbeConfigTable.description: Allows for configuration of individual probes. The number of entries is contained in the emsStatusProbeCount OID.

emsProbeConfigProbeIndex.name: emsProbeConfigProbeIndex
emsProbeConfigProbeIndex.description: The index to the probe entry.

emsProbeConfigProbeHighTempThresh.name: emsProbeConfigProbeHighTempThresh
emsProbeConfigProbeHighTempThresh.description: Probe high temperature threshold. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeConfigProbeLowTempThresh.name: emsProbeConfigProbeLowTempThresh
emsProbeConfigProbeLowTempThresh.description: Probe low temperature threshold. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeConfigProbeHighHumidityThresh.name: emsProbeConfigProbeHighHumidityThresh
emsProbeConfigProbeHighHumidityThresh.description: Probe high humidity threshold. Values are represented in whole number percentage.

emsProbeConfigProbeLowHumidityThresh.name: emsProbeConfigProbeLowHumidityThresh
emsProbeConfigProbeLowHumidityThresh.description: Probe low humidity threshold. Values are represented in whole number percentage.

emsProbeConfigProbeMaxTempThresh.name: emsProbeConfigProbeMaxTempThresh
emsProbeConfigProbeMaxTempThresh.description: Probe maximum temperature threshold. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeConfigProbeMinTempThresh.name: emsProbeConfigProbeMinTempThresh
emsProbeConfigProbeMinTempThresh.description: Probe minimum temperature threshold. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeConfigProbeDeltaTemp.name: emsProbeConfigProbeDeltaTemp
emsProbeConfigProbeDeltaTemp.description: Probe delta temperature. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeConfigProbeMaxHumidityThresh.name: emsProbeConfigProbeMaxHumidityThresh
emsProbeConfigProbeMaxHumidityThresh.description: Probe maximum humidity threshold. Values are represented in whole number percentage.

emsProbeConfigProbeMinHumidityThresh.name: emsProbeConfigProbeMinHumidityThresh
emsProbeConfigProbeMinHumidityThresh.description: Probe minimum humidity threshold. Values are represented in whole number percentage.

emsProbeConfigProbeDeltaHumidity.name: emsProbeConfigProbeDeltaHumidity
emsProbeConfigProbeDeltaHumidity.description: Probe delta humidity. Values are represented in whole number percentage.

emsProbeConfigProbeSTIncTempVariance.name: emsProbeConfigProbeSTIncTempVariance
emsProbeConfigProbeSTIncTempVariance.description: Probe short-term increasing temperature variance used for rate of change alarms. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeConfigProbeSTIncTempTime.name: emsProbeConfigProbeSTIncTempTime
emsProbeConfigProbeSTIncTempTime.description: Probe short-term increasing temperature time used for rate of change alarms. Values are represented in whole number minutes.

emsProbeConfigProbeSTDecTempVariance.name: emsProbeConfigProbeSTDecTempVariance
emsProbeConfigProbeSTDecTempVariance.description: Probe short-term decreasing temperature variance used for rate of change alarms. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeConfigProbeSTDecTempTime.name: emsProbeConfigProbeSTDecTempTime
emsProbeConfigProbeSTDecTempTime.description: Probe short-term decreasing temperature time used for rate of change alarms. Values are represented in whole number minutes.

emsProbeConfigProbeLTIncTempVariance.name: emsProbeConfigProbeLTIncTempVariance
emsProbeConfigProbeLTIncTempVariance.description: Probe long-term increasing temperature variance used for rate of change alarms. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeConfigProbeLTIncTempTime.name: emsProbeConfigProbeLTIncTempTime
emsProbeConfigProbeLTIncTempTime.description: Probe long-term increasing temperature time used for rate of change alarms. Values are represented in whole number hours.

emsProbeConfigProbeLTDecTempVariance.name: emsProbeConfigProbeLTDecTempVariance

emsStatusCheckLogLight.name: emsStatusCheckLogLight
emsStatusCheckLogLight.description: The status of the check-log light on the device. For the EMU2, this will always indicate lightOff(1). lightOff (1) indicates the light is off (no new log entries). lightOn (2) indicates the light is on (new log entries present).

emsStatusHardwareStatus.name: emsStatusHardwareStatus
emsStatusHardwareStatus.description: The status of the EMS hardware. This integer should be interpreted as a bit map, with each bit representing the presence or absence of a specific hardware error condition. 0 indicates there are no error conditions detected in the EMS hardware. 1 indicates a Current Limit error condition related to the Alink port. 2 indicates incorrect hardware is plugged into an EMS port. 3 indicates that both of these error conditions are present.

emsProbeStatusProbeHighTempThresh.name: emsProbeStatusProbeHighTempThresh
emsProbeStatusProbeHighTempThresh.description: Probe high temperature threshold. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeStatusProbeLowTempThresh.name: emsProbeStatusProbeLowTempThresh

emsProbeStatusProbeSerialNumber.name: emsProbeStatusProbeSerialNumber

emsProbeStatusProbeCommStatus.name: emsProbeStatusProbeCommStatus
emsProbeStatusProbeCommStatus.description: The state of communications to the probe. commNeverDiscovered(1) indicates there has never been communications with this device. commsEstablished(2) indicates communication is normal and active with this device. commsLost(3) indicates communication had been established, but is no longer.

emsProbeStatusProbeAlarmStatus.name: emsProbeStatusProbeAlarmStatus
emsProbeStatusProbeAlarmStatus.description: The alarm status of the probe. This integer should be interpreted as a bit map, with each bit representing the presence or absence of the specific alarm conditions listed below. The bit will be '1' if the condition is present, and '0' if the condition is not present. Bit Hex. Value Description 1 0x0001 Maximum temperature exceeded. 2 0x0002 High temperature exceeded. 3 0x0004 Low temperature exceeded. 4 0x0008 Minimum temperature exceeded. 5 0x0010 Short-term increasing temperature rate exceeded. 6 0x0020 Short-term decreasing temperature rate exceeded. 7 0x0040 Long-term increasing temperature rate exceeded. 8 0x0080 Long-term decreasing temperature rate exceeded. 9 0x0100 Maximum humidity exceeded. 10 0x0200 High humidity exceeded. 11 0x0400 Low humidity exceeded. 12 0x0800 Minimum humidity exceeded.

emsProbeStatusProbeMaxTempThresh.name: emsProbeStatusProbeMaxTempThresh
emsProbeStatusProbeMaxTempThresh.description: Probe maximum temperature threshold. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the emsStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

emsProbeStatusProbeMinTempThresh.name: emsProbeStatusProbeMinTempThresh

emsProbeStatusProbeMinHumidityThresh.name: emsProbeStatusProbeMinHumidityThresh

A value of notApplicable indicates that this alarm does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysActualElectricReheat.description: The electric reheating output of the System. Measured in percent. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysSteamHotGasReheatDmd.name: airFMSysSteamHotGasReheatDmd
airFMSysSteamHotGasReheatDmd.description: The steam, hot water, or hot gas reheating output demanded by the System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysActualSteamHotGasReheat.description: The steam, hot water, or hot gas reheating output of the System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysSteamElectrodeHumDmd.name: airFMSysSteamElectrodeHumDmd
airFMSysSteamElectrodeHumDmd.description: The steam electrode humidification output demanded by the System. Measured in percent. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysActualSteamElectrodeHum.name: airFMSysActualSteamElectrodeHum
airFMSysActualSteamElectrodeHum.description: The average steam electrode humidification output measured for the Modules in the System. Measured in percent. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysSteamHumDmd.name: airFMSysSteamHumDmd
airFMSysSteamHumDmd.description: The steam humidification output demanded by the System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysActualSteamHum.name: airFMSysActualSteamHum
airFMSysActualSteamHum.description: The steam humidification output for the System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysNumModules.name: airFMSysNumModules
airFMSysNumModules.description: The number of Modules in this System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysNumPCIOMs.name: airFMSysNumPCIOMs
airFMSysNumPCIOMs.description: The number of Programmable Customer Input/Output Modules (PCIOMs) installed in the Main Module of this System. Each PCIOM adds four input contacts and four output relays to the System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysMainsVlt.name: airFMSysMainsVlt
airFMSysMainsVlt.description: The mains voltage for the Modules in this System. A value of N/A indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysUPSVlt.name: airFMSysUPSVlt
airFMSysUPSVlt.description: The UPS voltage for the Modules in this System. A value of N/A indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoilCfg.name: airFMSysCoilCfg
airFMSysCoilCfg.description: The type of cooling coils installed in the Modules in this System: DX coil, DX and MultiCool (chilled water) coils, DX and Economizer coils, or only a Chilled Liquid coil. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysRefrigType.name: airFMSysRefrigType
airFMSysRefrigType.description: The type of refrigerant used by each compressor in the system. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysHeatRejection.name: airFMSysHeatRejection
airFMSysHeatRejection.description: The method the Modules in this System use to transfer heat away from the refrigerant. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysDischAirPtrn.name: airFMSysDischAirPtrn
airFMSysDischAirPtrn.description: The discharge air pattern for the Modules in this System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysAirFltr.name: airFMSysAirFltr
airFMSysAirFltr.description: The type of air filters (standard or high efficiency) installed in the Modules of this System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysFlowSwitch.name: airFMSysFlowSwitch
airFMSysFlowSwitch.description: The location of the optional flow switch. None: No flow switch is installed in this System. DX: Coolant input to the heat exchanger (condenser). MultiCool: Chilled water input to the MultiCool coil. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoilFluidVlvAct.name: airFMSysCoilFluidVlvAct
airFMSysCoilFluidVlvAct.description: The type of valve actuator installed on the coil fluid valve. The coil fluid valve controls the flow of coolant into a fluid cooling coil, such as a MultiCool or Economizer coil. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoilFluidVlvType.name: airFMSysCoilFluidVlvType
airFMSysCoilFluidVlvType.description: The type of coil fluid valve installed for the Modules in this System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvAct.name: airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvAct
airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvAct.description: The type of valve actuator installed on the Condenser fluid valve. The Condenser fluid valve controls the flow of coolant into the heat exchanger (condenser) to regulate head pressure. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvType.name: airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvType
airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvType.description: The type of Condenser fluid valve installed for the Modules in this System. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysHotWaterVlvAct.name: airFMSysHotWaterVlvAct
airFMSysHotWaterVlvAct.description: The type of valve actuator installed on the hot water valve. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysNumRemoteSensors.name: airFMSysNumRemoteSensors
airFMSysNumRemoteSensors.description: The number of remote sensors detected by the system.

airFMSysPrimaryControlSensor.name: airFMSysPrimaryControlSensor
airFMSysPrimaryControlSensor.description: Selects whether return or remote sensors will control the system. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysRemoteSensorData.name: airFMSysRemoteSensorData
airFMSysRemoteSensorData.description: Selects whether average temperature or max temperature will be used when remote sensors are selected for control of the system. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysFastStartup.name: airFMSysFastStartup
airFMSysFastStartup.description: Minimizes the time for the cooling process to begin after other delay constraints have been met. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysStartupDelay.name: airFMSysStartupDelay
airFMSysStartupDelay.description: Set the delay that begins when power is applied and ends when the System starts. This allows you to create a staged restart among your Systems after a power loss. Measured in seconds. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysModeDelay.name: airFMSysModeDelay
airFMSysModeDelay.description: Set the delay between starting the blowers and engaging the modes. It allows the sensors to read room conditions accurately and allows the controller to check for major alarms before engaging a mode. Measured in seconds. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCommLossShutdownDelay.name: airFMSysCommLossShutdownDelay
airFMSysCommLossShutdownDelay.description: Set the delay between an Expansion Module losing communication with the Main Module and the Expansion Module shutting down. A value of -1 will keep the Expansion Module running after a communication loss. Measured in hours. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysResetSysFailure.name: airFMSysResetSysFailure
airFMSysResetSysFailure.description: Setting this OID to reset(2) will allows the system to return from any failure condition, if the failure(s) have cleared. Getting this OID will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysResetUserDflts.name: airFMSysResetUserDflts
airFMSysResetUserDflts.description: Setting this OID to reset(2) will reset all system parameters that can be edited by the user to their factory default values. Getting this OID will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysResetFldSrvcDflts.name: airFMSysResetFldSrvcDflts
airFMSysResetFldSrvcDflts.description: Setting this OID to reset(2) will reset all system parameters that can only be edited by the field service engineer to their factory default values. Getting this OID will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysResetRunHours.name: airFMSysResetRunHours
airFMSysResetRunHours.description: Setting this OID to reset(2) will reset the system Run Hours. Getting this OID will do nothing and return the noOperation(1) value. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCompMinOnTime.name: airFMSysCompMinOnTime
airFMSysCompMinOnTime.description: Set the minimum time the compressor continues to operate after it is started. The delay protects the compressor from damage. Caution: Reducing this delay shortens compressor life. Measured in seconds. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCompMinOffTime.name: airFMSysCompMinOffTime
airFMSysCompMinOffTime.description: Set the minimum time the compressor will remain off after it ceases operation. The delay protects the compressor from damage. Caution: Reducing this delay shortens compressor life. Measured in seconds. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCompRotPeriod.name: airFMSysCompRotPeriod
airFMSysCompRotPeriod.description: Set how often to perform compressor runtime balancing. Measured in hours. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysEconIsolVlvOpenDelay.name: airFMSysEconIsolVlvOpenDelay
airFMSysEconIsolVlvOpenDelay.description: Set the delay between opening the Economizer Isolator output relay and engaging the compressors. Measured in seconds. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysEconIsolVlvCloseDelay.name: airFMSysEconIsolVlvCloseDelay
airFMSysEconIsolVlvCloseDelay.description: Set the delay between disengaging the compressor and closing the Economizer Isolator output relay. Measured in seconds. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvCloseDelay.name: airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvCloseDelay
airFMSysCndsrFluidVlvCloseDelay.description: Set the time the condenser valve remains open after the compressors disengage. Measured in seconds. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysInterstageDelay.name: airFMSysInterstageDelay
airFMSysInterstageDelay.description: The DX interstage delay allows the first compressor's cooling to take effect before engaging the second compressor. This prevents the second compressor from cycling on and off excessively. Measured in seconds. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolState.name: airFMSysCoolState
airFMSysCoolState.description: Set the mode to enabled or disabled. Disabled modes will not operate, and you cannot make changes to their settings while they are disabled. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolEssFunction.name: airFMSysCoolEssFunction
airFMSysCoolEssFunction.description: Set the priority of the mode for alarms and events with the nonessential stop behavior. Nonessential modes are disabled during nonessential stop alarms and events. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolSetpointC.name: airFMSysCoolSetpointC
airFMSysCoolSetpointC.description: The target value for the selected control sensor air for this mode. It must be at least 1.0 C above the reheat setpoint if a heater is installed. Measured in tenths of degrees Celsius. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolSetpointF.name: airFMSysCoolSetpointF
airFMSysCoolSetpointF.description: The target value for the selected control sensor air for this mode. It must be at least 1.0 C above the reheat setpoint if a heater is installed. Measured in tenths of degrees Fahrenheit. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolDeadbandC.name: airFMSysCoolDeadbandC
airFMSysCoolDeadbandC.description: The temperature range that controls output when the selected control sensor temperature is above the setpoint. At the top of this range, the cool mode outputs at 100%. The deadband does not apply to PID- controlled modes. Measured in tenths of degrees Celsius. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolDeadbandF.name: airFMSysCoolDeadbandF
airFMSysCoolDeadbandF.description: The temperature range that controls output when the selected control sensor temperature is above the setpoint. At the top of this range, the cool mode outputs at 100%. The deadband does not apply to PID- controlled modes. Measured in tenths of degrees Fahrenheit. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolEconIsolFunction.name: airFMSysCoolEconIsolFunction
airFMSysCoolEconIsolFunction.description: Set the Economizer Automatic Coolant Isolation valve to enabled or disabled. This valve anticipates a cooling demand and opens the coil fluid valve. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysSuctPresCompensation.name: airFMSysSuctPresCompensation
airFMSysSuctPresCompensation.description: Set the Suction Pressure Compensation to enabled or disabled. This function attempts to keep the suction pressure from exceeding 95 psi. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoilFluidActivThreshC.name: airFMSysCoilFluidActivThreshC
airFMSysCoilFluidActivThreshC.description: The minimum coolant temperature required to use the optional MultiCool or Economizer coil. Measured in tenths of degrees Celsius. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoilFluidActivThreshF.name: airFMSysCoilFluidActivThreshF
airFMSysCoilFluidActivThreshF.description: The minimum coolant temperature required to use the optional MultiCool or Economizer coil. Measured in tenths of degrees Fahrenheit. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoilFluidActivDeadbandC.name: airFMSysCoilFluidActivDeadbandC
airFMSysCoilFluidActivDeadbandC.description: The controller will disengage the MultiCool or Economizer coil when the coolant temperature reaches the coil fluid temperature activation threshold plus the deadband. Measured in tenths of degrees Celsius. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoilFluidActivDeadbandF.name: airFMSysCoilFluidActivDeadbandF
airFMSysCoilFluidActivDeadbandF.description: The controller will disengage the MultiCool or Economizer coil when the coolant temperature reaches the coil fluid temperature activation threshold plus the deadband. airFMSysCoolPIDMethod.name: airFMSysCoolPIDMethod
airFMSysCoolPIDMethod.description: Set the multipliers that the PID algorithm will use to calculate the cool output. Proportional, Proportional + Integral, or Proportional + Integral + Derivative. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolPIDGainP.name: airFMSysCoolPIDGainP
airFMSysCoolPIDGainP.description: Set the proportional multiplier to correct for differences between the selected control sensor actual temperature and the setpoint. Measured in %/C. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolPIDResetRateI.name: airFMSysCoolPIDResetRateI
airFMSysCoolPIDResetRateI.description: Set the integral multiplier to correct for the proportional offset. Measured in %/(C * min). A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysCoolPIDDerivativeD.name: airFMSysCoolPIDDerivativeD
airFMSysCoolPIDDerivativeD.description: Set the derivative multiplier to counteract overshoot and droop during changes in the room load. Measured in %/(C / min). A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysHumState.name: airFMSysHumState
airFMSysHumState.description: Set the mode to enabled or disabled. Disabled modes will not operate, and you cannot make changes to their settings while they are disabled. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysHumEssFunction.name: airFMSysHumEssFunction
airFMSysHumEssFunction.description: Set the priority of the mode for alarms and events with the nonessential stop behavior. Nonessential modes are disabled during nonessential stop alarms and events. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysHumSetpoint.name: airFMSysHumSetpoint
airFMSysHumSetpoint.description: The target value for the selected control sensor air for this mode. It must be at least 1.0 % RH below the dehumidification setpoint. Measured in tenths of percent relative humidity. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysHumDeadband.name: airFMSysHumDeadband
airFMSysHumDeadband.description: The humidity range that controls output when the selected control sensor humidity is below the setpoint. At the top of this range, the humidification mode outputs at 100%. The deadband does not apply to PID-controlled modes. Measured in tenths of percent relative humidity. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysHumCtrlSetting.name: airFMSysHumCtrlSetting
airFMSysHumCtrlSetting.description: Set the method to control the humidity in the room. The two methods are Relative Humidity (RH) or Dew Point of the selected control sensor air. The dew point method helps correct for hot spots near the selected control sensors. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysActualHumCtrl.name: airFMSysActualHumCtrl
airFMSysActualHumCtrl.description: The humidity control method the system is using. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysHumSensBand.name: airFMSysHumSensBand
airFMSysHumSensBand.description: The percentage of relative humidity below the setpoint at which the humidifier will output at 100% of capacity. Measured in percent relative humidity. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysDehumState.name: airFMSysDehumState
airFMSysDehumState.description: Set the mode to enabled or disabled. Disabled modes will not operate, and you cannot make changes to their settings while they are disabled. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysDehumEssFunction.name: airFMSysDehumEssFunction
airFMSysDehumEssFunction.description: Set the priority of the mode for alarms and events with the nonessential stop behavior. airFMSysDehumSetpoint.name: airFMSysDehumSetpoint
airFMSysDehumSetpoint.description: The target value for the selected control sensor air for this mode. It must be at least 1.0 % RH above the humidification setpoint if a humidifier is installed. airFMSysDehumDeadband.name: airFMSysDehumDeadband

airFMSysDehumCapacity.name: airFMSysDehumCapacity

airFMSysDehumPIDMethod.name: airFMSysDehumPIDMethod
airFMSysDehumPIDMethod.description: Set the multipliers that the PID algorithm will use to calculate the output. Proportional, Proportional + Integral, or Proportional + Integral + Derivative. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysDehumPIDGainP.name: airFMSysDehumPIDGainP
airFMSysDehumPIDGainP.description: Set the proportional multiplier to correct for differences between the selected control sensor actual humidity and the setpoint. Measured in %/%RH. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysDehumPIDResetRateI.name: airFMSysDehumPIDResetRateI
airFMSysDehumPIDResetRateI.description: Set the integral multiplier to correct for the proportional offset. Measured in %/(%RH * min). A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysDehumPIDDerivativeD.name: airFMSysDehumPIDDerivativeD
airFMSysDehumPIDDerivativeD.description: Set the derivative multiplier to counteract overshoot and droop during changes in the room humidity. Measure in %/(%RH / min). A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysReheatState.name: airFMSysReheatState
airFMSysReheatState.description: Set the mode to enabled or disabled. Disabled modes will not operate, and you cannot make changes to their settings while they are disabled. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysReheatEssFunction.name: airFMSysReheatEssFunction
airFMSysReheatEssFunction.description: Set the priority of the mode for alarms and events with the nonessential stop behavior. Nonessential modes are disabled during nonessential stop alarms and events. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysReheatSetpointC.name: airFMSysReheatSetpointC
airFMSysReheatSetpointC.description: The target value for the selected control sensor air for this mode. It must be at least 1.0 C below the cooling setpoint. Measured in tenths of degrees Celsius. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysReheatSetpointF.name: airFMSysReheatSetpointF
airFMSysReheatSetpointF.description: The target value for the selected control sensor air for this mode. It must be at least 1.0 C below the cooling setpoint. Measured in tenths of degrees Fahrenheit. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysReheatDeadbandC.name: airFMSysReheatDeadbandC
airFMSysReheatDeadbandC.description: The temperature range that controls output when the selected control sensor temperature is below the setpoint. At the bottom of this range, the reheat mode outputs at 100%. The deadband does not apply to PID-controlled modes. Measured in tenths of degrees Celsius. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysReheatDeadbandF.name: airFMSysReheatDeadbandF
airFMSysReheatDeadbandF.description: The temperature range that controls output when the selected control sensor temperature is below the setpoint. At the bottom of this range, the reheat mode outputs at 100%. The deadband does not apply to PID-controlled modes. Measured in tenths of degrees Fahrenheit. A value of -2147483648 indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysReheatPIDMethod.name: airFMSysReheatPIDMethod
airFMSysReheatPIDMethod.description: Set the multipliers that the PID algorithm will use to calculate the output. Proportional, Proportional + Integral, or Proportional + Integral + Derivative. A value of notApplicable indicates that this OID does not apply to this device due to its configuration.

airFMSysReheatPIDGainP.name: airFMSysReheatPIDGainP
