rARUIdentName.name: rARUIdentName
rARUIdentName.description: A character string identifying the device.

rARUConfigTable.name: rARUConfigTable
rARUConfigTable.description: Allows for configuration of the individual ARU devices accessible from this IP address. The number of entries is contained in the rARUStatusAruDeviceCount OID.

rARUConfigAruIndex.name: rARUConfigAruIndex
rARUConfigAruIndex.description: The index to the ARU entry.

rARUConfigAruRemoteSetpoint.name: rARUConfigAruRemoteSetpoint
rARUConfigAruRemoteSetpoint.description: This OID defines the desired base airflow of the ARU, and sets the speed of the ARU fans when the temperature override is inactive. Values specified in cfm (cubic feet per minute) can be converted to metric values using the conversion factor: 1 cfm = 1.70 m^3/hr (cubic meters per hour). Values (1) through (9) are for support of legacy (1st generation) ARUs. Writing these values to a 2nd generation ARU will result in the following: A value greater than (9) will be ignored by a 1st generation ARU. aruOff (1) - Ignored aru85F-29C (2) - 1200 cfm aru90F-32C (3) - 800 cfm aru95F-35C (4) - 500 cfm aru100F-38C (5) - 400 cfm aru7kW (6) - 1200 cfm aru5kW (7) - 800 cfm aru3kW (8) - 500 cfm aru2kW (9) - 400 cfm NOTE: -1 will be returned if the ARU is not communicating.

rARUConfigAruTempOvrdEnableDisable.name: rARUConfigAruTempOvrdEnableDisable
rARUConfigAruTempOvrdEnableDisable.description: This OID is used to enable/disable the remote temperature override setting of the ARU. If this OID is set to 1, the remote setting for temperature override is disabled. If this OID is set to 2, the remote setting for temperature override is enabled.

rARUConfigAruTempOvrdSetpoint.name: rARUConfigAruTempOvrdSetpoint
rARUConfigAruTempOvrdSetpoint.description: This OID is the Temperature Override setpoint of the ARU. NOTE: -1 will be returned if the ARU is not communicating. Values are represented in whole number degrees using the units specified in the rARUStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

rARUConfigAruMasterControl.name: rARUConfigAruMasterControl
rARUConfigAruMasterControl.description: This is the master on/off control for the ARU.

rARUStatusAruDeviceCount.name: rARUStatusAruDeviceCount
rARUStatusAruDeviceCount.description: The total number of ARUs accessible from this IP.

rARUStatusSysTempUnits.name: rARUStatusSysTempUnits
rARUStatusSysTempUnits.description: The temperature scale used to display the temperature in the system, Celsius(1) or Fahrenheit(2). This setting is based on the system preferences configuration in the agent.

rARUStatusTable.name: rARUStatusTable
rARUStatusTable.description: Allows for query of the individual ARUs accessible from this IP address. The number of entries is contained in the rARUStatusAruDeviceCount OID.

rARUStatusAruIndex.name: rARUStatusAruIndex
rARUStatusAruIndex.description: The index to the ARU entry.

rARUStatusAruRemoteSetpoint.name: rARUStatusAruRemoteSetpoint
rARUStatusAruRemoteSetpoint.description: This OID defines the desired base airflow of the ARU, or the speed of the ARU fans when the temperature override is inactive. See also the rARUConfigAruRemoteSetpoint OID. NOTE: -1 will be returned if the ARU is not communicating.

rARUStatusAruManualSetpoint.name: rARUStatusAruManualSetpoint
rARUStatusAruManualSetpoint.description: Manual operating setpoint of the ARU, which is set on the panel of the ARU. If the ARU doesn't have a manual , the OID will always return a value of aruRem (10). NOTE: -1 will be returned if the ARU is not communicating. Values are represented in whole number degrees or kW. If the manual setpoint is set to Remote, or if the ARU doesn't have a manual switch, this OID will return aruRem.

rARUStatusAruTemp1.name: rARUStatusAruTemp1
rARUStatusAruTemp1.description: ARU temperature probe #1 reading. The summary exhaust temperature on 2nd generation ARUs. NOTE: -1 will be returned if the ARU is not communicating. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the rARUStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

rARUStatusAruTemp2.name: rARUStatusAruTemp2
rARUStatusAruTemp2.description: ARU temperature probe #2 reading. The exhaust temperature in the upper plenum on 2nd generation ARUs. NOTE: -1 will be returned if the ARU is not communicating. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the rARUStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

rARUStatusAruTemp3.name: rARUStatusAruTemp3
rARUStatusAruTemp3.description: ARU temperature probe #3 reading. The exhaust temperature in the lower plenum on 2nd generation ARUs. NOTE: -1 will be returned if the ARU is not communicating. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the rARUStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

rARUStatusAruTempOvrdEnableDisable.name: rARUStatusAruTempOvrdEnableDisable
rARUStatusAruTempOvrdEnableDisable.description: This OID indicates whether the ARU remote temperature override is enabled or disabled. If this OID is a 1, the remote setting for temperature override is disabled. If this OID is a 2, the remote setting for temperature override is enabled.

rARUStatusAruTempOvrdSetpoint.name: rARUStatusAruTempOvrdSetpoint
rARUStatusAruTempOvrdSetpoint.description: ARU remote temperature override setpoint setting. NOTE: -1 will be returned if the ARU is not communicating. Values are represented in whole number degrees. Units are displayed in the scale shown in the rARUStatusSysTempUnits OID (Celsius or Fahrenheit).

rARUStatusAruAlarmState.name: rARUStatusAruAlarmState
rARUStatusAruAlarmState.description: An ASCII string containing the 8 flags representing the current alarm state of the ARU. If the state of the ARU is unknown, this variable is set to 'UNKNOWN'. The flags are numbered 1 to 8, read from left to right. The flags are defined as follows: Flag 1: Fan Fail 1 Flag 2: Fan Fail 2 Flag 3: Fan Fail 3 Flag 4: Smoke (if ARU is equipped with smoke detector) Flag 5: High Temp (Out of Thermal Control) Flag 6: Over Temp (Exhaust Temp. Exceeds Override Setpoint) Flag 7: Fan Fail 4 (Gen 2 ARU only) Flag 8: Reserved

rARUStatusAruCommStatus.name: rARUStatusAruCommStatus
rARUStatusAruCommStatus.description: The state of communications to the device. commNeverDiscovered(1) indicates there has never been communications with this device. commsEstablished(2) indicates communication is normal and active with this device. commsLost(3) indicates communication had been established, but is no device.

rARUStatusAruTempOvrdStatus.name: rARUStatusAruTempOvrdStatus
rARUStatusAruTempOvrdStatus.description: Specifies whether the ARU is increasing airflow because exhaust air temperature has exceeded the setting specified in the rARUConfigAruTempOvrdSetpoint OID.

rARUStatusAruMasterControl.name: rARUStatusAruMasterControl
rARUStatusAruMasterControl.description: This is the master on/off control for the ARU.

rARUStatusAruTotalAirflow.name: rARUStatusAruTotalAirflow
rARUStatusAruTotalAirflow.description: The total airflow provided by the aru. Specified in cfm (cubic feet per minute). Can be converted to metric values using the conversion factor: 1 cfm = 1.70 m^3/hr (cubic meters per hour).

rARUFanStatusTable.name: rARUFanStatusTable
rARUFanStatusTable.description: Allows for query of the individual devices. The number of entries is contained in the rARUStatusAruDeviceCount OID.

rARUFanStatusAruIndex.name: rARUFanStatusAruIndex
rARUFanStatusAruIndex.description: The index to the ARU entry.

rARUFanStatusNominalFanSpeed.name: rARUFanStatusNominalFanSpeed
rARUFanStatusNominalFanSpeed.description: The nominal rotational speed (RPM) of the fans when they are operating at the 100% level.

rARUFanStatusSelectedFanLevel.name: rARUFanStatusSelectedFanLevel
rARUFanStatusSelectedFanLevel.description: The currently selected ARU speed level, specified in percent of full capacity.

rARUFanStatusReplacementThreshold.name: rARUFanStatusReplacementThreshold
rARUFanStatusReplacementThreshold.description: Threshold above which a run hour alarm will exist, indicating that it might be time to proactively replace a fan.

rARUFanStatusFanIndex.name: rARUFanStatusFanIndex
rARUFanStatusFanIndex.description: The index to an individual fan table entry.

rARUFanStatusFanOperatingStatus.name: rARUFanStatusFanOperatingStatus
rARUFanStatusFanOperatingStatus.description: The current operating state of the fan.

rARUFanStatusFanRpmSpeed.name: rARUFanStatusFanRpmSpeed
rARUFanStatusFanRpmSpeed.description: The current rotational speed of the fan, specified in rotations per minute (RPM).

rARUFanStatusFanFlowRate.name: rARUFanStatusFanFlowRate
rARUFanStatusFanFlowRate.description: The flow rate provided by the fan, based on its measured rotational speed. Specified in cfm (cubic feet per minute). Can be converted to metric values using the conversion factor: 1 cfm = 1.70 m^3/hr (cubic meters per hour).

rARUFanStatusFanInServiceDate.name: rARUFanStatusFanInServiceDate
rARUFanStatusFanInServiceDate.description: The installation/replacement date of the fan.

rARUFanStatusFanRunhourCounter.name: rARUFanStatusFanRunhourCounter
rARUFanStatusFanRunhourCounter.description: The total time for which the fan has been running. Specified in 10ths of hours.

rARUFanStatusFanRunhourReset.name: rARUFanStatusFanRunhourReset
rARUFanStatusFanRunhourReset.description: Writing yes to this This OID will reset a fan's total run hour counter, which is shown in the rARUFanStatusFanRunhourCounter OID.

rARUPowerStatusTable.name: rARUPowerStatusTable
rARUPowerStatusTable.description: Allows for query of the individual ARUs accessible from this IP address. The number of entries is contained in the rARUStatusAruDeviceCount OID.

rARUPowerStatusAruIndex.name: rARUPowerStatusAruIndex
rARUPowerStatusAruIndex.description: The index to the ARU entry.

rARUPowerStatusPrimaryAcPresent.name: rARUPowerStatusPrimaryAcPresent
rARUPowerStatusPrimaryAcPresent.description: Indicates whether or not line voltage is present on AC input 1.

rARUPowerStatusAuxiliaryAcPresent.name: rARUPowerStatusAuxiliaryAcPresent
rARUPowerStatusAuxiliaryAcPresent.description: Indicates whether or not line voltage is present on AC input 2.

rARUPowerStatusRedundantAcConfig.name: rARUPowerStatusRedundantAcConfig
rARUPowerStatusRedundantAcConfig.description: Indicates whether or not a dual cord is in use. When this setting is set to dualCord (2), aruRedundantPowerLostAlarm traps will be generated when either primary or auxiliary input voltage is not present. When this setting is set to singleCord (1), aruRedundantPowerLostAlarm traps will not be generated.

rARUSensorsStatusTableSize.name: rARUSensorsStatusTableSize
rARUSensorsStatusTableSize.description: The number of entries in the rARUSensorsStatusTable.

rARUSensorsStatusTable.name: rARUSensorsStatusTable
rARUSensorsStatusTable.description: Allows for getting environmental sensor status information.

rARUSensorsStatusEntry.name: rARUSensorsStatusEntry
rARUSensorsStatusEntry.description: The unit to get data from.

rARUSensorsStatusAruIndex.name: rARUSensorsStatusAruIndex
rARUSensorsStatusAruIndex.description: The index to the ARU entry.

rARUSensorsStatusSensorNumber.name: rARUSensorsStatusSensorNumber
rARUSensorsStatusSensorNumber.description: The number of the sensor on the device.

rARUSensorsTemperature.name: rARUSensorsTemperature
rARUSensorsTemperature.description: The sensor's current temperature reading. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsConfigTableSize.name: rARUSensorsConfigTableSize
rARUSensorsConfigTableSize.description: The number of entries in the rARUSensorsConfigTable.

rARUSensorsConfigTable.name: rARUSensorsConfigTable
rARUSensorsConfigTable.description: Allows for getting configuration information from environmental sensors attached to the device.

rARUSensorsConfigEntry.name: rARUSensorsConfigEntry
rARUSensorsConfigEntry.description: The unit to get data from.

rARUSensorsConfigAruIndex.name: rARUSensorsConfigAruIndex
rARUSensorsConfigAruIndex.description: The index to the ARU entry.

rARUSensorsConfigSensorNumber.name: rARUSensorsConfigSensorNumber
rARUSensorsConfigSensorNumber.description: The number of the sensor on the device.

rARUSensorsName.name: rARUSensorsName
rARUSensorsName.description: A descriptive name for the sensor.

rARUSensorsTempMaxThresh.name: rARUSensorsTempMaxThresh
rARUSensorsTempMaxThresh.description: The temperature at which a maximum temperature threshold violation alarm will be generated for this sensor. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempHighThresh.name: rARUSensorsTempHighThresh
rARUSensorsTempHighThresh.description: The temperature at which a high temperature threshold violation alarm will be generated for this sensor. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempLowThresh.name: rARUSensorsTempLowThresh
rARUSensorsTempLowThresh.description: The temperature at which a low temperature threshold violation alarm will be generated for this sensor. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempMinThresh.name: rARUSensorsTempMinThresh
rARUSensorsTempMinThresh.description: The temperature at which a min temperature threshold violation alarm will be generated for this sensor. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempThreshHysteresis.name: rARUSensorsTempThreshHysteresis
rARUSensorsTempThreshHysteresis.description: The change in temperature required to cause a temperature alarm to change from an active to an inactive state. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshValue.name: rARUSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshValue
rARUSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshValue.description: The value of the temperature short-term decreasing rate time that will cause an alarm to be generated. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshTime.name: rARUSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshTime
rARUSensorsTempShortDecRateThreshTime.description: The time over which the temperature may not decrease beyond the value specified by the temperature short-term decreasing rate threshold value.

rARUSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshValue.name: rARUSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshValue
rARUSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshValue.description: The value of the temperature short-term increasing rate time that will cause an alarm to be generated. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshTime.name: rARUSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshTime
rARUSensorsTempShortIncRateThreshTime.description: The time over which the temperature may not increase beyond the value specified by the temperature short-term increasing rate threshold value.

rARUSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshValue.name: rARUSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshValue
rARUSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshValue.description: The value of the temperature long-term decreasing rate time that will cause an alarm to be generated. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshTime.name: rARUSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshTime
rARUSensorsTempLongDecRateThreshTime.description: The time over which the temperature may not decrease beyond the value specified by the temperature long-term decreasing rate threshold value.

rARUSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshValue.name: rARUSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshValue
rARUSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshValue.description: The value of the temperature long-term increasing rate time that will cause an alarm to be generated. The temperature scale is based on the system preferences configuration.

rARUSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshTime.name: rARUSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshTime
rARUSensorsTempLongIncRateThreshTime.description: The time over which the temperature may not increase beyond the value specified by the temperature long-term increasing rate threshold value.

isxModularDistInfoTableSize.name: isxModularDistInfoTableSize
isxModularDistInfoTableSize.description: The number of entries in the isxModularDistInfoTable.

isxModularDistInfoTable.name: isxModularDistInfoTable
isxModularDistInfoTable.description: Allows for getting information about the modular distribution metering equipment.

isxModularDistInfoEntry.name: isxModularDistInfoEntry
isxModularDistInfoEntry.description: An entry containing information about an individual metering segment.

isxModularDistInfoSegmentIndex.name: isxModularDistInfoSegmentIndex
isxModularDistInfoSegmentIndex.description: The index of the metering segment.

isxModularDistInfoMeterModelNumber.name: isxModularDistInfoMeterModelNumber
isxModularDistInfoMeterModelNumber.description: The model number of the metering board for this segment.

isxModularDistInfoMeterSerialNumber.name: isxModularDistInfoMeterSerialNumber
isxModularDistInfoMeterSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the metering board for this segment.

isxModularDistInfoMeterDateOfManufacture.name: isxModularDistInfoMeterDateOfManufacture
isxModularDistInfoMeterDateOfManufacture.description: The date of manufacture for the metering board for this segment, in the format mm/dd/yyyy.

isxModularDistInfoMeterFirmwareRev.name: isxModularDistInfoMeterFirmwareRev
isxModularDistInfoMeterFirmwareRev.description: The firmware revision number of the metering board for this segment.

isxModularDistInfoMeterHardwareRev.name: isxModularDistInfoMeterHardwareRev
isxModularDistInfoMeterHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision number of the metering board for this segment.

isxModularDistModuleInfoTableSize.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoTableSize
isxModularDistModuleInfoTableSize.description: The number of entries in the isxModularDistModuleInfoTable.

isxModularDistModuleInfoTable.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoTable
isxModularDistModuleInfoTable.description: Allows for getting basic information about the distribution modules installed in the system.

isxModularDistModuleInfoEntry.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoEntry
isxModularDistModuleInfoEntry.description: An entry containing information about a specific distribution module.

isxModularDistModuleInfoModIndex.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoModIndex
isxModularDistModuleInfoModIndex.description: The number of the distribution module.

isxModularDistModuleInfoAlarmStatus.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoAlarmStatus
isxModularDistModuleInfoAlarmStatus.description: The status of this module. This reflects the indicator lamp(s) on the front of the module. A value of notPresent indicates that the module is not installed. A value of unknown indicates that there is no communication with the metering segment for this module.

isxModularDistModuleInfoModelNumber.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoModelNumber
isxModularDistModuleInfoModelNumber.description: The model number of the distribution module.

isxModularDistModuleInfoSerialNumber.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoSerialNumber
isxModularDistModuleInfoSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the distribution module.

isxModularDistModuleInfoDateOfManufactur.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoDateOfManufacture
isxModularDistModuleInfoDateOfManufactur.description: The date that the distribution module was manufactured.

isxModularDistModuleInfoNumCables.name: isxModularDistModuleInfoNumCables
isxModularDistModuleInfoNumCables.description: The number of cables provided by this distribution module.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerTableSize.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerTableSize
isxModularDistModuleBreakerTableSize.description: The number of entries in the isxModularDistModuleBreakerTable.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerTable.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerTable
isxModularDistModuleBreakerTable.description: Allows for getting operational information about the distribution modules.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerEntry.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerEntry
isxModularDistModuleBreakerEntry.description: An entry containing information about a specific distribution modules and circuit breakers.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerPhaseIndex.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerPhaseIndex
isxModularDistModuleBreakerPhaseIndex.description: The index to an individual breaker in the distribution module. The index also corresponds to the system phase to which the breaker is attached.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerAlarmStatus.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerAlarmStatus
isxModularDistModuleBreakerAlarmStatus.description: This is a bit map representing the active alarms for this breaker: b0 - Minimum current threshold exceeded (critical) b1 - Low current threshold exceeded (warning) b2 - High current threshold exceeded (warning) b3 - Maximum current threshold exceeded (critical) b4 - Breaker is open (critical) If a bit is set, the corresponding alarm is active.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerRating.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerRating
isxModularDistModuleBreakerRating.description: The current rating of the breaker.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerPhysicalGroup.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerPhysicalGroup
isxModularDistModuleBreakerPhysicalGroup.description: Numeric value used to indicate that a breaker is a part of a multi-pole breaker. Breakers within a distribution module, with equivalent physical group numbers, may have their handles physically tied together. A value of 1 indicates breakers that are physically tied together as part of a multi-pole breaker. A value of 0 indicates a single-handle breaker that is not physically tied to another breaker.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerCableNum.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerCableNum
isxModularDistModuleBreakerCableNum.description: Numeric value used to indicate the distribution cable to which this breaker is connected. These distribution cables are described in the table isxModularDistModuleOutputTable, and indexed by the OID isxModularDistModuleOutputCordIndex.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerPosition.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerPosition
isxModularDistModuleBreakerPosition.description: The physical status of this breaker pole, either closed or open (including tripped).

isxModularDistModuleBreakerPositionAlarm.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerPositionAlarms
isxModularDistModuleBreakerPositionAlarm.description: Enable or disable breaker position alarms for this circuit breaker.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerCurrent.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerCurrent
isxModularDistModuleBreakerCurrent.description: The current flowing though this breaker. Measured in tenths of amps.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerPercent.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerPercent
isxModularDistModuleBreakerPercent.description: The loading on this breaker as a percentage of the breaker's current rating. Expressed in tenths of percent.

isxModularDistModuleBreakerPower.name: isxModularDistModuleBreakerPower
isxModularDistModuleBreakerPower.description: The power being supplied through this breaker. Measured in tenths of kW.

isxModularDistModuleOutputsTableSize.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputsTableSize
isxModularDistModuleOutputsTableSize.description: The number of entries in the isxModularDistModuleOutputTable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputTable.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputTable
isxModularDistModuleOutputTable.description: Allows for getting and setting information related to the load equipment being fed by the distribution modules in the ISX Modular Distribution System.

isxModularDistModuleOutputEntry.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputEntry
isxModularDistModuleOutputEntry.description: An entry containing information about a specific distribution module and its output distribution cables.

isxModularDistModuleOutputModIndex.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputModIndex
isxModularDistModuleOutputModIndex.description: The number of the distribution module supplying power to the load equipment.

isxModularDistModuleOutputNumCables.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputNumCables
isxModularDistModuleOutputNumCables.description: The number of distribution cables provided by this module.

isxModularDistModuleOutputCordIndex.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputCordIndex
isxModularDistModuleOutputCordIndex.description: The index of an individual distribution cable supplied by this module.

isxModularDistModuleOutputName.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputName
isxModularDistModuleOutputName.description: A string describing the load equipment being supplied by this distribution cable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputLocation.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputLocation
isxModularDistModuleOutputLocation.description: A string describing the location of equipment being supplied by distribution cable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputStatus.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputStatus
isxModularDistModuleOutputStatus.description: This reflects the worse case severity for alarms associated with this distribution cable. A value of notPresent indicates that the cable does not exist for this module. A value of unknown indicates that the there is no communication with the metering segment for this distribution cable's module.

isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmGeneratio.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmGeneration
isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmGeneratio.description: Enable or disable all alarm generation related to this distribution cable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputBreakerMap.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputBreakerMap
isxModularDistModuleOutputBreakerMap.description: This is a bit map representing the breaker poles within the module that are associated with this distribution cable. The following 3 bits are used to indicate the indices of the breakers feeding the cable: b0 - Module breaker L1 b1 - Module breaker L2 b2 - Module breaker L3 If a bit is set, the breaker is used to feed this distribution cable. These breakers are described in the table isxModularDistModuleBreakerTable, and indexed by the OID isxModularDistModuleBreakerPhaseIndex.

isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdMin.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdMin
isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdMin.description: When the current drops below this value a critical alarm will exist.

isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdLow.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdLow
isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdLow.description: When the current drops below this value a warning alarm will exist.

isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdHigh.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdHigh
isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdHigh.description: When the current exceeds this value a warning alarm will exist.

isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdMax.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdMax
isxModularDistModuleOutputThresholdMax.description: When the current exceeds this value a critical alarm will exist.

isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmMinEnable.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmMinEnable
isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmMinEnable.description: Enable or disable minimum current alarm generation for this distribution cable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmLowEnable.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmLowEnable
isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmLowEnable.description: Enable or disable low current alarm generation for this distribution cable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmHighEnabl.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmHighEnable
isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmHighEnabl.description: Enable or disable high current alarm generation for this distribution cable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmMaxEnable.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmMaxEnable
isxModularDistModuleOutputAlarmMaxEnable.description: Enable or disable maximum current alarm generation for this distribution cable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputCableLength.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputCableLength
isxModularDistModuleOutputCableLength.description: The length of this distribution cable. Specified in tenths of meters.

isxModularDistModuleOutputConnectorType.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputConnectorType
isxModularDistModuleOutputConnectorType.description: A string describing the connector on the end of this distribution cable.

isxModularDistModuleOutputAvailableVolta.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputAvailableVoltages
isxModularDistModuleOutputAvailableVolta.description: This is a bit map representing the voltages that are available at the connector. 6 bits are used to indicate the following: b0 - L1 b1 - L2 b2 - L3 b3 - L1-2 b4 - L2-3 b5 - L3-1

isxModularDistModuleOutputTotalPower.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputTotalPower
isxModularDistModuleOutputTotalPower.description: The total power being consumed by the load equipment supplied by this distribution cable. Measured in tenths of kW.

isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhUsage.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhUsage
isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhUsage.description: The total energy consumed by the load equipment fed by this distribution cable. This is the total since the date specified in the isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhResetDate OID, and may be cleared using the isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhReset OID. Measured in tenths of kWh.

isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhReset.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhReset
isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhReset.description: Writing yes to this OID will reset the total kWh usage shown in the isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhUsage OID.

isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhResetDate.name: isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhResetDate
isxModularDistModuleOutputKwhResetDate.description: The date that the kWh usage was reset, in the format mm/dd/yyyy. Example: 01/01/2000.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTableSize.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTableSize
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTableSize.description: The number of entries in the isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTable.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTable.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTable
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTable.description: Allows for getting information about distribution subfeed breakers.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoEntry.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoEntry
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoEntry.description: An entry containing information about a specific distribution subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoSubIndex.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoSubIndex
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoSubIndex.description: The index of an individual subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoName.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoName
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoName.description: A string describing the load equipment being supplied by this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoLocation.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoLocation
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoLocation.description: A string describing the location of the equipment being supplied by this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerRating.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerRating
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerRating.description: The current rating of this subfeed breaker.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerPosition.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerPosition
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerPosition.description: The operational status of this breaker, either closed or open (including tripped).

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmStatus.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmStatus
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmStatus.description: The worst case alarm status for this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmGeneration.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmGeneration
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmGeneration.description: Enable or disable all alarm generation related to this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdMin.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdMin
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdMin.description: When the current drops below this value a critical alarm will exist.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdLow.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdLow
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdLow.description: When the current drops below this value a warning alarm will exist.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdHigh.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdHigh
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdHigh.description: When the current exceeds this value a warning alarm will exist.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdMax.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdMax
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoThresholdMax.description: When the current exceeds this value a critical alarm will exist.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmMinEnable.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmMinEnable
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmMinEnable.description: Enable or disable minimum current alarm generation for this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmLowEnable.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmLowEnable
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmLowEnable.description: Enable or disable low current alarm generation for this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmHighEnable.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmHighEnable
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmHighEnable.description: Enable or disable high current alarm generation for this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmMaxEnable.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmMaxEnable
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoAlarmMaxEnable.description: Enable or disable maximum current alarm generation for this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerAlarmEna.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerAlarmEnable
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoBreakerAlarmEna.description: Enable or disable breaker position alarms for this subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTotalPower.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTotalPower
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoTotalPower.description: The total power being supplied by this subfeed. Measured in tenths of kW.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhUsage.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhUsage
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhUsage.description: The total energy consumed by the load equipment fed by this subfeed. This is the total since the date specified in the isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhResetDate OID, and may be cleared using the isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhReset OID. Measured in tenths of kWh.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhReset.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhReset
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhReset.description: Writing yes to this OID will reset the total kWh usage shown in the isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhUsage OID.

isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhResetDate.name: isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhResetDate
isxModularDistSubFeedInfoKwhResetDate.description: The date that the kWh usage was reset, in the format mm/dd/yyyy. Example: 01/01/2000.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingTableSize.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingTableSize
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingTableSize.description: The number of entries in the isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingTable.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingTable.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingTable
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingTable.description: Allows for getting subfeed phase loading information.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingEntry.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingEntry
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingEntry.description: An entry containing data for an individual subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingSubIndex.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingSubIndex
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingSubIndex.description: The index of an individual subfeed.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPhaseIndex.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPhaseIndex
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPhaseIndex.description: Description of each input phase entry in the table.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingAlarmStatus.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingAlarmStatus
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingAlarmStatus.description: This is a bit map representing the active alarms for this subfeed: b0 - Minimum current threshold exceeded (critical) b1 - Low current threshold exceeded (warning) b2 - High current threshold exceeded (warning) b3 - Maximum current threshold exceeded (critical) b4 - Breaker is open (critical) If a bit is set, the corresponding alarm is active.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingCurrent.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingCurrent
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingCurrent.description: The current flowing though this subfeed phase. Measured in tenths of amps.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPercent.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPercent
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPercent.description: The loading on this subfeed phase as a percentage of the subfeed's current rating. Expressed in tenths of percent.

isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPower.name: isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPower
isxModularDistSubFeedLoadingPower.description: The power being supplied by this subfeed phase. Measured in tenths of kW.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLin.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLineToNeutral
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLin.description: The nominal line-to-neutral voltage available at the distribution panel.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLin.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLineToLine
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLin.description: The nominal line-to-line voltage available at the distribution panel.

isxModularDistSysOutputNominalFrequency.name: isxModularDistSysOutputNominalFrequency
isxModularDistSysOutputNominalFrequency.description: The nominal system output frequency. Measured in tenths of Hertz.

isxModularDistSysOutputFrequency.name: isxModularDistSysOutputFrequency
isxModularDistSysOutputFrequency.description: The system output frequency in tenths of Hertz. -1 if not available.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageMonitoring.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageMonitoring
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageMonitoring.description: Indicates whether or not output voltage alarm generation is present.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdM.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdMin
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdM.description: When the line-to-neutral voltage of any phase drops below this value a critical alarm will exist. Specified as a percent of the nominal voltage, isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLineToNeutral. This value is returned as a positive number which represents a negative percentage. A value of -1 indicates that the threshold is not available in the device.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdL.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdLow
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdL.description: When the line-to-neutral voltage of any phase drops below this value a warning alarm will exist. Specified as a percent of the nominal voltage, isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLineToNeutral. This value is returned as a positive number which represents a negative percentage. A value of -1 indicates that the threshold is not available in the device.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdH.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdHigh
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdH.description: When the line-to-neutral voltage of any phase exceeds this value a warning alarm will exist. Specified as a percent of the nominal voltage, isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLineToNeutral. A value of -1 indicates that the threshold is not available in the device.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdM.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdMax
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageThresholdM.description: When the line-to-neutral voltage of any phase exceeds this value a critical alarm will exist. Specified as a percent of the nominal voltage, isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageNominalLineToNeutral. A value of -1 indicates that the threshold is not available in the device.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmMinEn.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmMinEnable
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmMinEn.description: Enable or disable minimum voltage alarm generation for the distribution panel.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmLowEn.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmLowEnable
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmLowEn.description: Enable or disable low voltage alarm generation for the distribution panel.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmHighE.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmHighEnable
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmHighE.description: Enable or disable high voltage alarm generation for the distribution panel.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmMaxEn.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmMaxEnable
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageAlarmMaxEn.description: Enable or disable maximum voltage alarm generation for the distribution panel.

isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageFrequencyT.name: isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageFrequencyTolerance
isxModularDistSysOutputVoltageFrequencyT.description: The circuit panel output frequency tolerance in Hertz. When the system output frequency deviates from the nominal by more than this range, a critical alarm will be generated.

isxModularDistSysVoltageTable.description: Allows for getting the system output voltage information.

isxModularDistSysVoltageEntry.name: isxModularDistSysVoltageEntry
isxModularDistSysVoltageEntry.description: An entry containing data for an individual system output phase.

isxModularDistSysVoltagePhaseIndex.name: isxModularDistSysVoltagePhaseIndex
isxModularDistSysVoltagePhaseIndex.description: Description of each phase entry in the table.

isxModularDistSysVoltageAlarmStatus.name: isxModularDistSysVoltageAlarmStatus
isxModularDistSysVoltageAlarmStatus.description: This is a bit map representing the active alarms for this output phase: b0 - Minimum voltage threshold exceeded (critical) b1 - Low voltage threshold exceeded (warning) b2 - High voltage threshold exceeded (warning) b3 - Maximum voltage threshold exceeded (critical) If a bit is set, the corresponding alarm is active.

isxModularDistSysVoltageLtoN.name: isxModularDistSysVoltageLtoN
isxModularDistSysVoltageLtoN.description: Line-to-neutral system output voltage available at the distribution panel. Measured in tenths of Volts.

isxModularDistSysVoltageLtoL.name: isxModularDistSysVoltageLtoL
isxModularDistSysVoltageLtoL.description: Line-to-line system output voltage available at the distribution panel. Measured in tenths of Volts.

isxModularDistSysCurrentRating.description: The 100 percent current rating of the distribution panel.

isxModularDistSysCurrentMonitoring.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentMonitoring
isxModularDistSysCurrentMonitoring.description: Indicates whether or not total output current measurements and alarm generation are present.

isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdMin.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdMin
isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdMin.description: When total system current in any phase drops below this value a critical alarm will exist. Specified as a percent of the panel rating, isxModularDistSysCurrentRating. A value of -1 indicates that the threshold is not available in the device.

isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdLow.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdLow
isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdLow.description: When total system current in any phase drops below this value a warning alarm will exist. Specified as a percent of the panel rating, isxModularDistSysCurrentRating. A value of -1 indicates that the threshold is not available in the device.

isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdHigh.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdHigh
isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdHigh.description: When total system current in any phase exceeds this value a warning alarm will exist. Specified as a percent of the panel rating, isxModularDistSysCurrentRating. A value of -1 indicates that the threshold is not available in the device.

isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdMax.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdMax
isxModularDistSysCurrentThresholdMax.description: When total system current in any phase exceeds this value a critical alarm will exist. Specified as a percent of the panel rating, isxModularDistSysCurrentRating. A value of -1 indicates that the threshold is not available in the device.

isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmMinEnable.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmMinEnable
isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmMinEnable.description: Enable or disable minimum total output current alarm generation.

isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmLowEnable.description: Enable or disable low total output current alarm generation.

isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmHighEnable.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmHighEnable
isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmHighEnable.description: Enable or disable high total output current alarm generation.

isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmMaxEnable.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmMaxEnable
isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmMaxEnable.description: Enable or disable maximum total output current alarm generation.

isxModularDistSysCurrentTable.description: Allows for getting the total system phase current information.

isxModularDistSysCurrentEntry.description: An entry containing data for an individual system output phase.

isxModularDistSysCurrentPhaseIndex.description: Description of each phase entry in the table.

isxModularDistSysCurrentAlarmStatus.description: This is a bit map representing the active alarms for this output phase: b0 - Minimum current threshold exceeded (critical) b1 - Low current threshold exceeded (warning) b2 - High current threshold exceeded (warning) b3 - Maximum current threshold exceeded (critical) If a bit is set, the corresponding alarm is active.

isxModularDistSysCurrentAmps.name: isxModularDistSysCurrentAmps
isxModularDistSysCurrentAmps.description: The current flowing though this system output phase. Measured in tenths of amps.

isxModularDistSysCurrentPercent.description: The loading on this system output phase as a percentage of the panel current rating. Expressed in tenths of percent.

isxModularDistSysPowerTotal.name: isxModularDistSysPowerTotal
isxModularDistSysPowerTotal.description: The total system power being supplied. Measured in tenths of kW.

isxModularDistSysPowerKwhUsage.name: isxModularDistSysPowerKwhUsage
isxModularDistSysPowerKwhUsage.description: The total system energy consumed by the load equipment. This is the total since the date specified in the isxModularDistSysOutputKwhResetDate OID, and may be cleared using the isxModularDistSysOutputKwhReset OID. Measured in tenths of kWh.

isxModularDistSysPowerKwhReset.name: isxModularDistSysPowerKwhReset
isxModularDistSysPowerKwhReset.description: Writing yes to this OID will reset the total kWh usage shown in the isxModularDistSysPowerKwhUsage OID.

isxModularDistSysPowerKwhResetDate.name: isxModularDistSysPowerKwhResetDate
isxModularDistSysPowerKwhResetDate.description: The date that the kWh usage was reset, in the format mm/dd/yyyy. Example: 01/01/2000.

isxModularDistSysPowerTable.name: isxModularDistSysPowerTable
isxModularDistSysPowerTable.description: Allows for getting the total system phase power loading information.

isxModularDistSysPowerEntry.name: isxModularDistSysPowerEntry
isxModularDistSysPowerEntry.description: An entry containing data for an individual system output phase.

isxModularDistSysPowerPhaseIndex.name: isxModularDistSysPowerPhaseIndex
isxModularDistSysPowerPhaseIndex.description: Description of each phase entry in the table.

isxModularDistSysPowerKw.name: isxModularDistSysPowerKw
isxModularDistSysPowerKw.description: The power being supplied by this system output phase. Measured in tenths of kW.

isxModularDistSysPowerKwhPhaseUsage.name: isxModularDistSysPowerKwhPhaseUsage
isxModularDistSysPowerKwhPhaseUsage.description: The energy consumed by the load equipment on this system output phase. This is the total since the date specified in the isxModularDistSysPowerKwhResetDate OID, and may be cleared using the isxModularDistSysPowerKwhReset OID. Measured in tenths of kWh.

isxModularPduIdentModelNumber.description: A character string identifying the model number of the PDU. This value is set at the factory.

isxModularPduIdentSerialNumber.name: isxModularPduIdentSerialNumber
isxModularPduIdentSerialNumber.description: A character string identifying the serial number of the PDU. This value is set at the factory.

isxModularPduIdentDateOfManufacture.name: isxModularPduIdentDateOfManufacture
isxModularPduIdentDateOfManufacture.description: The date when the PDU was manufactured in mm/dd/yyyy format. This value is set at the factory.

isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardSerialNumbe.name: isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardSerialNumber
isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardSerialNumbe.description: A character string identifying the serial number of the PDU monitor card. This value is set at the factory.

isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardHardwareRev.name: isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardHardwareRev
isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the PDU monitor card. This value is set at the factory.

isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardFirmwareApp.name: isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardFirmwareAppRev
isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardFirmwareApp.description: An ID string identifying the application firmware revision of the PDU monitor card.

isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardFirmwareApp.name: isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardFirmwareAppOSRev
isxModularPduIdentMonitorCardFirmwareApp.description: An ID string identifying the application operating system firmware revision of the PDU monitor card.

isxModularPduDeviceTransformerPresent.name: isxModularPduDeviceTransformerPresent
isxModularPduDeviceTransformerPresent.description: Indicates the type of transformer present in this PDU.

isxModularPduDeviceServiceType.name: isxModularPduDeviceServiceType
isxModularPduDeviceServiceType.description: The type of utility input to the PDU. Either 3 wires (delta), or 4 wires (wye).

isxModularPduDeviceFansPresent.name: isxModularPduDeviceFansPresent
isxModularPduDeviceFansPresent.description: Indicates whether or not cooling fans are installed in the PDU.

isxModularPduDeviceNominalMainInputVolta.name: isxModularPduDeviceNominalMainInputVoltage
isxModularPduDeviceNominalMainInputVolta.description: The nominal main input voltage to the system. Measured in Volts, line-to-line for a 3-wire (delta) service or line-to-neutral for a 4-wire (wye) service. -1 if main input voltage is not being measured.

isxModularPduAlarmStatus.name: isxModularPduAlarmStatus
isxModularPduAlarmStatus.description: The overall status (worst case) of this PDU.

isxModularPduTransformerTempStatus.name: isxModularPduTransformerTempStatus
isxModularPduTransformerTempStatus.description: Indicates if the PDU isolation transformer is over temperature.

isxModularPduFanStatus.name: isxModularPduFanStatus
isxModularPduFanStatus.description: Indicates if one or more of the PDU's cooling fans have failed.

uioSensorStatusTableSize.name: uioSensorStatusTableSize
uioSensorStatusTableSize.description: The number of entries in the uioSensorStatusTable.

uioSensorStatusTable.name: uioSensorStatusTable
uioSensorStatusTable.description: Allows for getting sensor status information.

uioSensorStatusEntry.name: uioSensorStatusEntry
uioSensorStatusEntry.description: The unit from which to get data.

uioSensorStatusPortID.name: uioSensorStatusPortID
uioSensorStatusPortID.description: The ID of the port to which the sensor is attached.

uioSensorStatusTemperatureDegF.name: uioSensorStatusTemperatureDegF
uioSensorStatusTemperatureDegF.description: The sensor's current temperature reading in degrees Fahrenheit. -1 indicates an invalid reading due to lost communications.

uioSensorStatusTemperatureDegC.name: uioSensorStatusTemperatureDegC
uioSensorStatusTemperatureDegC.description: The sensor's current temperature reading in degrees Celsius. -1 indicates an invalid reading due to lost communications.

uioSensorStatusHumidity.name: uioSensorStatusHumidity
uioSensorStatusHumidity.description: The sensor's current humidity reading in percent relative humidity. -1 indicates an invalid reading due to either a sensor that doesn't read humidity or lost communications.

uioSensorStatusViolationStatus.name: uioSensorStatusViolationStatus
uioSensorStatusViolationStatus.description: The violation status of the sensor. This integer should be interpreted as a bit map, with each bit representing the presence or absence of the specific alarm conditions listed below. The bit will be '1' if the condition is present, and '0' if the condition is not present. Bit Hex. Value Description 1 0x0001 Maximum temperature exceeded. 2 0x0002 High temperature exceeded. 3 0x0004 Low temperature exceeded. 4 0x0008 Minimum temperature exceeded. 5 0x0010 Short-term increasing temperature rate exceeded (Not used). 6 0x0020 Short-term decreasing temperature rate exceeded (Not used). 7 0x0040 Long-term increasing temperature rate exceeded (Not used). 8 0x0080 Long-term decreasing temperature rate exceeded (Not used). 9 0x0100 Maximum humidity exceeded. 10 0x0200 High humidity exceeded. 11 0x0400 Low humidity exceeded. 12 0x0800 Minimum humidity exceeded.

uioSensorStatusAlarmStatus.name: uioSensorStatusAlarmStatus
uioSensorStatusAlarmStatus.description: The alarm status of the sensor.

uioSensorStatusCommStatus.name: uioSensorStatusCommStatus
uioSensorStatusCommStatus.description: The communications status of the sensor.

uioSensorConfigTableSize.name: uioSensorConfigTableSize
uioSensorConfigTableSize.description: The number of entries in the uioSensorConfigTable.

uioSensorConfigEntry.name: uioSensorConfigEntry
uioSensorConfigEntry.description: The sensor from which to get configuration.

uioSensorConfigPortID.name: uioSensorConfigPortID
uioSensorConfigPortID.description: The ID of the port to which the sensor is attached.

uioSensorConfigMinTemperatureThreshold.name: uioSensorConfigMinTemperatureThreshold
uioSensorConfigMinTemperatureThreshold.description: The minimum (critical) temperature alarm threshold for the probe in degrees C. Must be lower than the low threshold to ensure proper sensor alarm behavior.

uioSensorConfigLowTemperatureThreshold.name: uioSensorConfigLowTemperatureThreshold
uioSensorConfigLowTemperatureThreshold.description: The low (warning) temperature alarm threshold for the probe in degrees C. Must be higher than the minimum threshold and lower than the high threshold to ensure proper sensor alarm behavior.

uioSensorConfigHighTemperatureThreshold.name: uioSensorConfigHighTemperatureThreshold
uioSensorConfigHighTemperatureThreshold.description: The high (warning) temperature alarm threshold for the probe in degrees C. Must be lower than the maximum threshold and higher than the low threshold to ensure proper sensor alarm behavior.

uioSensorConfigMaxTemperatureThreshold.name: uioSensorConfigMaxTemperatureThreshold
uioSensorConfigMaxTemperatureThreshold.description: The maximum (critical) temperature alarm threshold for the probe in degrees C. Must be higher than the high threshold to ensure proper sensor alarm behavior.

uioSensorConfigTemperatureHysteresis.name: uioSensorConfigTemperatureHysteresis
uioSensorConfigTemperatureHysteresis.description: The number of degrees C beyond the temperature thresholds at which an active temperature alarm will be cleared. This value applies to all temperature thresholds.

uioSensorConfigMinTemperatureEnable.name: uioSensorConfigMinTemperatureEnable
uioSensorConfigMinTemperatureEnable.description: The minimum temperature alarm enable/disable for the sensor. 1 - disabled 2 - enabled

uioSensorConfigLowTemperatureEnable.name: uioSensorConfigLowTemperatureEnable
uioSensorConfigLowTemperatureEnable.description: The low temperature alarm enable/disable for the sensor. 1 - disabled 2 - enabled

uioSensorConfigHighTemperatureEnable.name: uioSensorConfigHighTemperatureEnable
uioSensorConfigHighTemperatureEnable.description: The high temperature alarm enable/disable for the sensor. 1 - disabled 2 - enabled

uioSensorConfigMaxTemperatureEnable.name: uioSensorConfigMaxTemperatureEnable
uioSensorConfigMaxTemperatureEnable.description: The maximum temperature alarm enable/disable for the sensor. 1 - disabled 2 - enabled

uioSensorConfigMinHumidityThreshold.name: uioSensorConfigMinHumidityThreshold
uioSensorConfigMinHumidityThreshold.description: The minimum (critical) humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity. Must be lower than the low threshold to ensure proper sensor alarm behavior. -1 if the sensor doesn't read humidity.

uioSensorConfigLowHumidityThreshold.name: uioSensorConfigLowHumidityThreshold
uioSensorConfigLowHumidityThreshold.description: The low (warning) humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity. Must be higher than the minimum threshold and lower than the high threshold to ensure proper sensor alarm behavior. -1 if the sensor doesn't read humidity.

uioSensorConfigHighHumidityThreshold.name: uioSensorConfigHighHumidityThreshold
uioSensorConfigHighHumidityThreshold.description: The high (warning) humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity. Must be lower than the maximum threshold and higher than the low threshold to ensure proper sensor alarm behavior. -1 if the sensor doesn't read humidity.

uioSensorConfigMaxHumidityThreshold.name: uioSensorConfigMaxHumidityThreshold
uioSensorConfigMaxHumidityThreshold.description: The maximum (critical) humidity alarm threshold for the probe in percent relative humidity. Must be higher than the high threshold to ensure proper sensor alarm behavior. -1 if the sensor doesn't read humidity.

uioSensorConfigHumidityHysteresis.name: uioSensorConfigHumidityHysteresis
uioSensorConfigHumidityHysteresis.description: The number of percent relative humidity beyond the humidity thresholds at which an active humidity alarm will be cleared. This value applies to all humidity thresholds. -1 if the sensor doesn't read humidity.

uioSensorConfigMinHumidityEnable.name: uioSensorConfigMinHumidityEnable
uioSensorConfigMinHumidityEnable.description: The minimum humidity alarm enable/disable for the sensor. 1 - disabled (always set if the sensor doesn't read humidity) 2 - enabled

uioSensorConfigLowHumidityEnable.name: uioSensorConfigLowHumidityEnable
uioSensorConfigLowHumidityEnable.description: The low humidity alarm enable/disable for the sensor. 1 - disabled (always set if the sensor doesn't read humidity) 2 - enabled

uioSensorConfigHighHumidityEnable.name: uioSensorConfigHighHumidityEnable
uioSensorConfigHighHumidityEnable.description: The high humidity alarm enable/disable for the sensor. 1 - disabled (always set if the sensor doesn't read humidity) 2 - enabled

uioSensorConfigMaxHumidityEnable.name: uioSensorConfigMaxHumidityEnable
uioSensorConfigMaxHumidityEnable.description: The maximum humidity alarm enable/disable for the sensor. 1 - disabled (always set if the sensor doesn't read humidity) 2 - enabled
