communicationLost.name: communicationLost
communicationLost.description: SEVERE: Communication to the UPS has been lost. Steps to reestablish communication are in progress.

upsOverload.name: upsOverload
upsOverload.description: SEVERE: The UPS has sensed a load greater than 100 percent of its rated capacity.

upsDiagnosticsFailed.name: upsDiagnosticsFailed
upsDiagnosticsFailed.description: SEVERE: The UPS failed its internal diagnostic self-test.

upsDischarged.name: upsDischarged
upsDischarged.description: SEVERE: The UPS batteries are discharged; if utility power fails an immediate low battery condition will exist. Sufficient runtime for necessary action cannot be guaranteed.

upsOnBattery.name: upsOnBattery
upsOnBattery.description: WARNING: The UPS has switched to battery backup power.

smartBoostOn.name: smartBoostOn
smartBoostOn.description: WARNING: The UPS has enabled SmartBoost(TM).

lowBattery.name: lowBattery
lowBattery.description: SEVERE: The UPS batteries are low and will soon be exhausted. If utility power is not restored the UPS will put itself to 'sleep' and immediately cut power to the load.

communicationEstablished.name: communicationEstablished
communicationEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: Communication with the UPS has been established.

powerRestored.name: powerRestored
powerRestored.description: INFORMATIONAL: Utility power has been restored.

upsDiagnosticsPassed.name: upsDiagnosticsPassed
upsDiagnosticsPassed.description: INFORMATIONAL: The UPS passed its internal self-test.

returnFromLowBattery.name: returnFromLowBattery
returnFromLowBattery.description: INFORMATIONAL: The UPS has returned from a low battery condition.

upsTurnedOff.name: upsTurnedOff
upsTurnedOff.description: WARNING: The UPS has been turned 'off' by the management station.

upsSleeping.name: upsSleeping
upsSleeping.description: WARNING: The UPS is entering 'sleep' mode. Power to the load will be cut off.

upsWokeUp.name: upsWokeUp
upsWokeUp.description: INFORMATION: The UPS has returned from 'sleep' mode. Power to the load has been restored.

upsRebootStarted.name: upsRebootStarted
upsRebootStarted.description: WARNING: The UPS has started its reboot sequence. The UPS will reboot itself at this time.

upsDipSwitchChanged.name: upsDipSwitchChanged
upsDipSwitchChanged.description: WARNING: The dip switch settings on the UPS have been changed, possibly altering UPS performance.

upsBatteryNeedsReplacement.name: upsBatteryNeedsReplacement
upsBatteryNeedsReplacement.description: SEVERE: The batteries of the UPS need immediate replacement.

contactFault.name: contactFault
contactFault.description: SEVERE: One of the contacts on the Environmental Monitor has changed from its default position. The first variable is the contact number that is faulted.

contactFaultResolved.name: contactFaultResolved
contactFaultResolved.description: INFORMATIONAL: A fault on one of the Environmental Monitor contacts has been resolved. The first variable is the contact number that has been resolved.

hardwareFailureBypass.name: hardwareFailureBypass
hardwareFailureBypass.description: SEVERE: UPS on bypass due to internal fault

softwareBypass.name: softwareBypass
softwareBypass.description: WARNING: UPS on bypass - user set via software or panel

switchedBypass.name: switchedBypass
switchedBypass.description: WARNING: UPS on bypass - initiated by user

returnFromBypass.name: returnFromBypass
returnFromBypass.description: INFORMATIONAL: UPS has returned from bypass

bypassPowerSupplyFailure.name: bypassPowerSupplyFailure
bypassPowerSupplyFailure.description: SEVERE: Base module bypass power supply needs repair

baseFanFailure.name: baseFanFailure
baseFanFailure.description: SEVERE: Base module fan needs repair

batteryPackCommLost.name: batteryPackCommLost
batteryPackCommLost.description: SEVERE: Check installation of external battery packs signal cable

batteryPackCommEstablished.name: batteryPackCommEstablished
batteryPackCommEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: UPS is communicating with the external battery packs.

calibrationStart.name: calibrationStart
calibrationStart.description: INFORMATIONAL: A battery calibration test has been initiated on the UPS.

restartAgent.name: restartAgent
restartAgent.description: INFORMATIONAL: Agent restarting as commanded by manager.

upsTurnedOn.name: upsTurnedOn
upsTurnedOn.description: INFORMATIONAL: A UPS is turned on.

smartAvrReducing.name: smartAvrReducing
smartAvrReducing.description: WARNING: The UPS is reducing the line voltage via SmartTrim(TM).

codeAuthenticationDone.name: codeAuthenticationDone
codeAuthenticationDone.description: INFORMATIONAL: Authentication on agent code image is done.

upsOverloadCleared.name: upsOverloadCleared
upsOverloadCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The overload condition has been cleared.

smartBoostOff.name: smartBoostOff
smartBoostOff.description: INFORMATIONAL: The UPS has returned from SmartBoost(TM).

smartAvrReducingOff.name: smartAvrReducingOff
smartAvrReducingOff.description: INFORMATIONAL: The UPS has returned from SmartTrim(TM).

upsBatteryReplaced.name: upsBatteryReplaced
upsBatteryReplaced.description: INFORMATIONAL: A bad battery fault has been cleared.

calibrationEnd.name: calibrationEnd
calibrationEnd.description: INFORMATIONAL: The UPS has finished calibrating.

dischargeCleared.name: dischargeCleared
dischargeCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A UPS discharge condition has been cleared.

gracefulShutdown.name: gracefulShutdown
gracefulShutdown.description: INFORMATIONAL: A graceful shutdown has been initiated.

outletOn.name: outletOn
outletOn.description: WARNING: The specified PDU outlet has turned on. If sPDUOutletControlIndex equals zero, then all outlets have turned on.

outletOff.name: outletOff
outletOff.description: WARNING: The specified PDU outlet has turned off. If sPDUOutletControlIndex equals zero, then all outlets have turned off.

outletReboot.name: outletReboot
outletReboot.description: WARNING: The specified PDU outlet has rebooted. If sPDUOutletControlIndex equals zero, then all outlets have rebooted.

configChangeSNMP.name: configChangeSNMP
configChangeSNMP.description: WARNING: The SNMP configuration has been changed.

configChangeOutlet.name: configChangeOutlet
configChangeOutlet.description: WARNING: The specified PDU outlet has changed configuration. If sPDUOutletConfigIndex equals zero, then the Master outlet has changed configuration.

accessViolationConsole.name: accessViolationConsole
accessViolationConsole.description: WARNING: Someone has attempted to login via the console with the incorrect password.

accessViolationHTTP.name: accessViolationHTTP
accessViolationHTTP.description: WARNING: Someone has attempted to login via HTTP with the incorrect password.

passwordChange.name: passwordChange
passwordChange.description: WARNING: The password for the device has been changed.

badVoltage.name: badVoltage
badVoltage.description: WARNING: The output voltage is not within acceptable range.

badVoltageCleared.name: badVoltageCleared
badVoltageCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The output voltage has returned to an acceptable level.

chargerFailure.name: chargerFailure
chargerFailure.description: WARNING: The battery charger has failed.

chargerFailureCleared.name: chargerFailureCleared
chargerFailureCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The battery charger failure condition has been cleared.

batteryOverTemperature.name: batteryOverTemperature
batteryOverTemperature.description: WARNING: The battery temperature threshold has been violated.

batteryOverTemperatureCleared.name: batteryOverTemperatureCleared
batteryOverTemperatureCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The battery over temperature has been cleared.

smartRelayFault.name: smartRelayFault
smartRelayFault.description: WARNING: SmartBoost(TM) or SmartTrim(TM) relay fault.

smartRelayFaultCleared.name: smartRelayFaultCleared
smartRelayFaultCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: SmartBoost(TM) or SmartTrim(TM) relay fault has been cleared.

humidityThresholdViolation1.name: humidityThresholdViolation1
humidityThresholdViolation1.description: SEVERE: Probe 1 humidity threshold violated. The first variable is the current humidity.

humidityThresholdViolationCleared1.name: humidityThresholdViolationCleared1
humidityThresholdViolationCleared1.description: INFORMATIONAL: An Environmental Monitor humidity threshold violation has been cleared on probe 1.

temperatureThresholdViolation1.name: temperatureThresholdViolation1
temperatureThresholdViolation1.description: SEVERE: An Environmental Monitor temperature threshold has been violated on probe 1. The first variable is the current temperature.

temperatureThresholdViolationCleared1.name: temperatureThresholdViolationCleared1
temperatureThresholdViolationCleared1.description: INFORMATIONAL: An Environmental Monitor temperature threshold violation has been cleared on probe 1.

humidityThresholdViolation2.name: humidityThresholdViolation2
humidityThresholdViolation2.description: SEVERE: An Environmental Monitor humidity threshold has been violated on probe 2. The first variable is the current humidity.

humidityThresholdViolationCleared2.name: humidityThresholdViolationCleared2
humidityThresholdViolationCleared2.description: INFORMATIONAL: An Environmental Monitor humidity threshold violation has been cleared on probe 2.

temperatureThresholdViolation2.name: temperatureThresholdViolation2
temperatureThresholdViolation2.description: SEVERE: An Environmental Monitor temperature threshold has been violated on probe 2. The first variable is the current temperature.

temperatureThresholdViolationCleared2.name: temperatureThresholdViolationCleared2
temperatureThresholdViolationCleared2.description: INFORMATIONAL: An Environmental Monitor temperature threshold violation has been cleared on probe 2.

mupsCommunicationEstablished.name: mupsCommunicationEstablished
mupsCommunicationEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: Communication with the Environmental Monitor has been established.

mupsCommunicationLost.name: mupsCommunicationLost
mupsCommunicationLost.description: SEVERE: Communication to the Environmental Monitor has been lost. Steps to reestablish communication are in progress.

batteryIncrease.name: batteryIncrease
batteryIncrease.description: INFORMATIONAL: The number of batteries has increased.

batteryDecrease.name: batteryDecrease
batteryDecrease.description: INFORMATIONAL: The number of batteries has decreased.

powerModuleIncrease.name: powerModuleIncrease
powerModuleIncrease.description: INFORMATIONAL: The number of power modules has increased.

powerModuleDecrease.name: powerModuleDecrease
powerModuleDecrease.description: INFORMATIONAL: The number of power modules has decreased.

intelligenceModuleInserted.name: intelligenceModuleInserted
intelligenceModuleInserted.description: INFORMATIONAL: An intelligence module has been inserted.

intelligenceModuleRemoved.name: intelligenceModuleRemoved
intelligenceModuleRemoved.description: INFORMATIONAL: An intelligence module has been removed.

rintelligenceModuleInserted.name: rintelligenceModuleInserted
rintelligenceModuleInserted.description: INFORMATIONAL: A redundant intelligence module has been inserted.

rintelligenceModuleRemoved.name: rintelligenceModuleRemoved
rintelligenceModuleRemoved.description: INFORMATIONAL: A redundant intelligence module has been removed.

extBatteryFrameIncease.name: extBatteryFrameIncease
extBatteryFrameIncease.description: INFORMATIONAL: An external battery frame has been added.

extBatteryFrameDecrease.name: extBatteryFrameDecrease
extBatteryFrameDecrease.description: INFORMATIONAL: An external battery frame has been removed.

abnormalCondition.name: abnormalCondition
abnormalCondition.description: SEVERE: An abnormal condition has been detected. The first variable is the fault condition.

abnormalConditionCleared.name: abnormalConditionCleared
abnormalConditionCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: An abnormal condition has been cleared. The first variable is the fault condition.

deviceStatusChange.name: deviceStatusChange
deviceStatusChange.description: INFORMATIONAL: The status of the device being monitored has changed.

noBatteries.name: noBatteries
noBatteries.description: WARNING: The UPS has no batteries attached.

noBatteriesCleared.name: noBatteriesCleared
noBatteriesCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The UPS's batteries have been attached.

userAdded.name: userAdded
userAdded.description: INFORMATIONAL: A new user has been added.

userDeleted.name: userDeleted
userDeleted.description: INFORMATIONAL: A user has been deleted.

userModified.name: userModified
userModified.description: INFORMATIONAL: A user has been modified.

msvmCommunicationEstablished.name: msvmCommunicationEstablished
msvmCommunicationEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: Communications with the MasterSwitch VM has been established.

msvmCommunicationLost.name: msvmCommunicationLost
msvmCommunicationLost.description: SEVERE: Communications with the MasterSwitch VM has been lost.

msvmOverload.name: msvmOverload
msvmOverload.description: SEVERE: The MasterSwitch VM in an overload condition.

msvmOverloadCleared.name: msvmOverloadCleared
msvmOverloadCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The overload condition on the MasterSwitch VM has been cleared.

msvmOutletOn.name: msvmOutletOn
msvmOutletOn.description: INFORMATIONAL: An outlet on the MasterSwitch VM has turned on.

msvmOutletOff.name: msvmOutletOff
msvmOutletOff.description: INFORMATIONAL: An outlet on the MasterSwitch VM has turned off.

msvmDeviceConfigChange.name: msvmDeviceConfigChange
msvmDeviceConfigChange.description: INFORMATIONAL: A device configuration change has been made on a MasterSwitch VM.

msvmOutletConfigChange.name: msvmOutletConfigChange
msvmOutletConfigChange.description: INFORMATIONAL: An outlet configuration change has been made on a MasterSwitch VM.

msvmLowLoad.name: msvmLowLoad
msvmLowLoad.description: INFORMATIONAL: The MasterSwitch VM has violated the low load threshold.

msvmLowLoadCleared.name: msvmLowLoadCleared
msvmLowLoadCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The low load condition on the MasterSwitch VM has been cleared.

msvmNearOverload.name: msvmNearOverload
msvmNearOverload.description: SEVERE: The MasterSwitch VM is approaching an overload condition.

msvmNearOverloadCleared.name: msvmNearOverloadCleared
msvmNearOverloadCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The near overload condition on the MasterSwitch VM has been cleared.

msvmPowerSupplyStatusChange.name: msvmPowerSupplyStatusChange
msvmPowerSupplyStatusChange.description: WARNING: The power supply status of the MasterSwitch VM has changed.

mspCommunicationEstablished.name: mspCommunicationEstablished
mspCommunicationEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: Communications with the MasterSwitch plus has been established.

mspCommunicationLost.name: mspCommunicationLost
mspCommunicationLost.description: SEVERE: Communications with the MasterSwitch plus has been lost.

mspOutletOn.name: mspOutletOn
mspOutletOn.description: INFORMATIONAL: An outlet on the MasterSwitch plus has turned on.

mspOutletOff.name: mspOutletOff
mspOutletOff.description: INFORMATIONAL: An outlet on the MasterSwitch plus has turned off.

mspDeviceConfigChange.name: mspDeviceConfigChange
mspDeviceConfigChange.description: INFORMATIONAL: A device configuration change has been made on a MasterSwitch plus.

mspOutletConfigChange.name: mspOutletConfigChange
mspOutletConfigChange.description: INFORMATIONAL: An outlet configuration change has been made on a MasterSwitch plus.

rsSourceSwitched.name: rsSourceSwitched
rsSourceSwitched.description: INFORMATIONAL: The Redundant Switch has switched source. The first variable is an integer representing the current source: 0=A, 1=B. The second variable is the 32-character name of the current source. The third variable is an integer representing the transfer cause: 0=No Transfers Recorded, 1=Due to user action or preferred switching, 3=Due to line notch or spike, 5=Due to low line voltage, 7=Transfer due to high line voltage, 9=Transfer due to frequency out of range. The fourth variable is a character string listing the transfer cause.

rsLostRedundancy.name: rsLostRedundancy
rsLostRedundancy.description: SEVERE: The Redundant Switch has lost redundancy. The first variable is an integer representing the source which is no longer available: 0=A, 1=B. The second variable is the 32-character name of the source which is no longer available.

rsRedundancyRestored.name: rsRedundancyRestored
rsRedundancyRestored.description: INFORMATIONAL: Redundancy has been restored to the Redundant Switch . The first variable is an integer representing the source which has been restored: 0=A, 1=B. The second variable is the 32-character name of the source which has been restored.

rsConfigChange.name: rsConfigChange
rsConfigChange.description: INFORMATIONAL: A configuration change has been made on a Redundant Switch.

rsCommunicationEstablished.name: rsCommunicationEstablished
rsCommunicationEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: Communications with the Redundant Switch has been established.

rsCommunicationLost.name: rsCommunicationLost
rsCommunicationLost.description: SEVERE: Communications with the Redundant Switch has been lost.

dcCommunicationEstablished.name: dcCommunicationEstablished
dcCommunicationEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: Communications with the DC power plant has been established.

dcCommunicationLost.name: dcCommunicationLost
dcCommunicationLost.description: SEVERE: Communications with the DC power plant has been lost.

dcPINChanged.name: dcPINChanged
dcPINChanged.description: INFORMATIONAL: The active PIN on the DC controller has been changed.

dcMajorAlarm.name: dcMajorAlarm
dcMajorAlarm.description: SEVERE: A Major alarm is active in the DC power plant.

dcMajorAlarmCleared.name: dcMajorAlarmCleared
dcMajorAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A Major alarm is no longer active in the DC power plant.

dcMinorAlarm.name: dcMinorAlarm
dcMinorAlarm.description: WARNING: A Minor alarm is active in the DC power plant.

dcMinorAlarmCleared.name: dcMinorAlarmCleared
dcMinorAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A Minor alarm is no longer active in the DC power plant.

dcOutputRelayOn.name: dcOutputRelayOn
dcOutputRelayOn.description: WARNING: An output relay for the powerplant has been activated (state changed to on). The first variable is an integer representing the output relay number that has gone on. The second variable is the 16-character name of the output relay.

dcOutputRelayOff.name: dcOutputRelayOff
dcOutputRelayOff.description: INFORMATIONAL: An output relay for the powerplant has been deactivated (state changed to off). The first variable is an integer representing the output relay number that has gone off. The second variable is the 16-character name of the output relay.

dcInputRelayOn.name: dcInputRelayOn
dcInputRelayOn.description: WARNING: An input relay for the powerplant has been activated (state changed to on). The first variable is an integer representing the input relay number that has gone on. The second variable is the 16-character name of the input relay.

dcInputRelayOff.name: dcInputRelayOff
dcInputRelayOff.description: INFORMATIONAL: An input relay for the powerplant has been deactivated (state changed to off). The first variable is an integer representing the input relay number that has gone off. The second variable is the 16-character name of the input relay.

logicPowerSuppliesIncreased.name: logicPowerSuppliesIncreased
logicPowerSuppliesIncreased.description: INFORMATIONAL: The number of system power supplies has increased.

logicPowerSuppliesDecreased.name: logicPowerSuppliesDecreased
logicPowerSuppliesDecreased.description: INFORMATIONAL: The number of system power supplies has decreased.

atsSourceSwitched.name: atsSourceSwitched
atsSourceSwitched.description: INFORMATIONAL: The Automatic Transfer Switch has switched source. The first variable is an integer representing the current source: 0=A, 1=B. The second variable is the 32-character name of the current source.

atsLostRedundancy.name: atsLostRedundancy
atsLostRedundancy.description: SEVERE: The Automatic Transfer Switch has lost redundancy. The first variable is an integer representing the source which is no longer available: 0=A, 1=B. The second variable is the 32-character name of the source which is no longer available.

atsRedundancyRestored.name: atsRedundancyRestored
atsRedundancyRestored.description: INFORMATIONAL: Redundancy has been restored to the Automatic Transfer Switch . The first variable is an integer representing the source which has been restored: 0=A, 1=B. The second variable is the 32-character name of the source which has been restored.

atsConfigChange.name: atsConfigChange
atsConfigChange.description: INFORMATIONAL: A configuration change has been made on the Automatic Transfer Switch. The first variable is an integer representing the configuration setting which changed: 0=Transfer Voltage Range, 1=Sensitivity, 2=Preferred Source 3=Front Panel Lockout, 4=Current Limit, 5=Reset XA Processor, 6=Reset to defaults, 7=Product Name, 8=Nominal Voltage, 9=Nominal Line Frequency, 10=Narrow VRMS, 11=Medium VRMS, 12=Wide VRMS,13=Frequency Deviation, 14=ColdStart ATS, 15=Events Count Cleared, 16=Phase or Bank Threshold.

atsCommunicationEstablished.name: atsCommunicationEstablished
atsCommunicationEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: Communications with the Automatic Transfer Switch has been established.

atsCommunicationLost.name: atsCommunicationLost
atsCommunicationLost.description: SEVERE: Communications with the Automatic Transfer Switch has been lost.

atsOverCurrent.name: atsOverCurrent
atsOverCurrent.description: SEVERE: Output Current has exceeded threshold. This is same as atsOverload Trap for phase or total in case banked units

atsOverCurrentCleared.name: atsOverCurrentCleared
atsOverCurrentCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Output Current has returned below threshold.This is same as atsOverloadCleared Trap for phase or total in case banked units

atsPowerSupplyFailure.name: atsPowerSupplyFailure
atsPowerSupplyFailure.description: SEVERE: The Automatic Transfer Switch Power Supply has failed. The first variable is an integer representing the Power Supply which has failed: 0 = Source A 24V, 1 = 12V, 2 = 5V, 3 = Source B 24V.

atsPowerSupplyFailureCleared.name: atsPowerSupplyFailureCleared
atsPowerSupplyFailureCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The Automatic Transfer Power Supply Failure Cleared. The first variable is an integer representing the Power Supply which has cleared: 0 = Source A 24V, 1 = 12V, 2 = 5V, 3 = Source B 24V.

dcMainsFailAlarm.name: dcMainsFailAlarm
dcMainsFailAlarm.description: WARNING: A Mains Fail alarm is active in the DC power plant.

dcMainsFailAlarmCleared.name: dcMainsFailAlarmCleared
dcMainsFailAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Mains Fail alarm is no longer active in the DC power plant.

dcFanFailAlarm.name: dcFanFailAlarm
dcFanFailAlarm.description: WARNING: A Fan Fail alarm is active in the DC power plant.

dcFanFailAlarmCleared.name: dcFanFailAlarmCleared
dcFanFailAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A Fan Fail alarm is no longer active in the DC power plant.

dcRectifierOvertempAlarm.name: dcRectifierOvertempAlarm
dcRectifierOvertempAlarm.description: WARNING: Rect. Overtemp alarm is active in the power plant.

dcRectifierOvertempAlarmCleared.name: dcRectifierOvertempAlarmCleared
dcRectifierOvertempAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Rect. Overtemp alarm is no longer active in the power plant.

dcCurrentLimitAlarm.name: dcCurrentLimitAlarm
dcCurrentLimitAlarm.description: WARNING: A Current Limit alarm is active in the power plant.

dcCurrentLimitAlarmCleared.name: dcCurrentLimitAlarmCleared
dcCurrentLimitAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Current Limit alarm is no longer active in the power plant.

dcRectifierFailAlarm.name: dcRectifierFailAlarm
dcRectifierFailAlarm.description: WARNING: A Rect. Fail alarm is active in the power plant.

dcRectifierFailAlarmCleared.name: dcRectifierFailAlarmCleared
dcRectifierFailAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Rect. Fail alarm is no longer active in the power plant.

dcMultRectFailAlarm.name: dcMultRectFailAlarm
dcMultRectFailAlarm.description: WARNING: Multiple Rect. Fail alarm is active in the powerplant.

dcMultRectFailAlarmCleared.name: dcMultRectFailAlarmCleared
dcMultRectFailAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Multiple Rect Fail alarm is no longer active in the powerplant.

dcBatteryBreakerAlarm.name: dcBatteryBreakerAlarm
dcBatteryBreakerAlarm.description: WARNING: Batt. Breaker alarm is active in the power plant.

dcBatteryBreakerAlarmCleared.name: dcBatteryBreakerAlarmCleared
dcBatteryBreakerAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Batt. Breaker alarm is no longer active in the power plant.

dcRectifierOVPAlarm.name: dcRectifierOVPAlarm
dcRectifierOVPAlarm.description: WARNING: A Rect. OVP alarm is active in the power plant.

dcRectifierOVPAlarmCleared.name: dcRectifierOVPAlarmCleared
dcRectifierOVPAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A Rect. OVP alarm is no longer active in the power plant.

dcLVDImminentAlarm.name: dcLVDImminentAlarm
dcLVDImminentAlarm.description: WARNING: A LVD Imminent alarm is active in the powerplant.

dcLVDImminentAlarmCleared.name: dcLVDImminentAlarmCleared
dcLVDImminentAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A LVD Imminent alarm is no longer active in the powerplant.

dcFuseCBAlarm.name: dcFuseCBAlarm
dcFuseCBAlarm.description: WARNING: A Fuse/CB alarm is active in the DC power plant.

dcFuseCBAlarmCleared.name: dcFuseCBAlarmCleared
dcFuseCBAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A Fuse/CB alarm is no longer active in the DC power plant.

dcBatteryTestFail.name: dcBatteryTestFail
dcBatteryTestFail.description: WARNING: A Battery Test failed in the DC power plant.

dcTemperatureAlarm.name: dcTemperatureAlarm
dcTemperatureAlarm.description: WARNING: A Temperature is active in the power plant.

dcTemperatureAlarmCleared.name: dcTemperatureAlarmCleared
dcTemperatureAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A Temperature alarm is no longer active in the power plant.

dcHumidityAlarm.name: dcHumidityAlarm
dcHumidityAlarm.description: WARNING: A Humidity alarm is active in the DC power plant.

dcHumidityAlarmCleared.name: dcHumidityAlarmCleared
dcHumidityAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A Humidity alarm is no longer active in the DC power plant.

dcBBCommunicationEstablished.name: dcBBCommunicationEstablished
dcBBCommunicationEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: Power plant bridging board communications established.

dcBBCommunicationLost.name: dcBBCommunicationLost
dcBBCommunicationLost.description: SEVERE: Power plant bridging board communications lost.

iemHighTempThresholdViolation.name: iemHighTempThresholdViolation
iemHighTempThresholdViolation.description: SEVERE: High temperature threshold violated on Integrated Environmental Monitor probe. The first variable is the current temperature. The second variable is the temperature scale. The third variable is the probe number. The fourth variable is the probe name.

iemHighTempThresholdViolationCleared.name: iemHighTempThresholdViolationCleared
iemHighTempThresholdViolationCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: High temperature threshold violated on Integrated Environmental Monitor probe has been cleared. The first variable is the probe number. The second variable is the probe name.

iemLowTempThresholdViolation.name: iemLowTempThresholdViolation
iemLowTempThresholdViolation.description: SEVERE: Low temperature threshold violated on integrated probe. The first variable is the current temperature. The second variable is the temperature scale. The third variable is the probe number. The fourth variable is the probe name.

iemLowTempThresholdViolationCleared.name: iemLowTempThresholdViolationCleared
iemLowTempThresholdViolationCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Low temperature threshold violated on integrated probe has been cleared. The first variable is the probe number. The second variable is the probe name.

iemHighHumidThresholdViolation.name: iemHighHumidThresholdViolation
iemHighHumidThresholdViolation.description: SEVERE: High humidity threshold violated on integrated probe. The first variable is the current humidity. The second variable is the probe number. The third variable is the probe name.

iemHighHumidThresholdViolationCleared.name: iemHighHumidThresholdViolationCleared
iemHighHumidThresholdViolationCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: High humidity threshold violated on integrated probe cleared. The first variable is the probe number. The second variable is the probe name.

iemLowHumidThresholdViolation.name: iemLowHumidThresholdViolation
iemLowHumidThresholdViolation.description: SEVERE: Low humidity threshold violated on integrated probe. The first variable is the current humidity. The second variable is the probe number. The third variable is the probe name.

iemLowHumidThresholdViolationCleared.name: iemLowHumidThresholdViolationCleared
iemLowHumidThresholdViolationCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Low humidity threshold violated on integrated probe cleared. The first variable is the probe number. The second variable is the probe name.

iemProbeDisconnected.name: iemProbeDisconnected
iemProbeDisconnected.description: WARNING: The temperature/humidity probe on the Integrated Environmental Monitor has been disconnected. This trap is generated when a probe that has been in communication with the Environmental Monitor has been disconnected or can no longer communicate.

iemProbeConnected.name: iemProbeConnected
iemProbeConnected.description: INFORMATIONAL: The temperature/humidity probe on the Integrated Environmental Monitor has been connected. This trap is generated when the Environmental Monitor establishes communication with a probe that had previously not been connected.

iemContactFault.name: iemContactFault
iemContactFault.description: SEVERE: There is a contact fault on the Integrated Environmental Monitor. The first argument is the number of the contact. The second argument is the name of the contact.

iemContactFaultCleared.name: iemContactFaultCleared
iemContactFaultCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The contact fault on the Integrated Environmental Monitor has been cleared. The first argument is the number of the contact. The second argument is the name of the contact.

iemRelayFault.name: iemRelayFault
iemRelayFault.description: SEVERE: The output relay on the Integrated Environmental Monitor has switched to the fault state. The first argument is the number of the output relay. The second argument is the name of the output relay. The third argument is the event that caused the fault.

iemRelayFaultCleared.name: iemRelayFaultCleared
iemRelayFaultCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The fault condition on the output relay on the Integrated Environmental Monitor has cleared. The first argument is the number of the output relay. The second argument is the name of the output relay.

bmBatManCommEstab.name: bmBatManCommEstab
bmBatManCommEstab.description: INFORMATIONAL: Serial Communications Established with Battery Manager.

bmBatManCommLost.name: bmBatManCommLost
bmBatManCommLost.description: SEVERE: Serial Communications Lost with Battery Manager.

bmBatManKneeAlarm.name: bmBatManKneeAlarm
bmBatManKneeAlarm.description: SEVERE: Battery Voltage Knee Threshold Alarm Detected.

bmBatManKneeAlarmCleared.name: bmBatManKneeAlarmCleared

xATSOutputCurrentHighAlarmCleared.name: xATSOutputCurrentHighAlarmCleared
xATSOutputCurrentHighAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The three-phase output load current of the device is back within the specified limits. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the phase (1=L1, 2=L2, 3=L3). The fourth argument is the measured current in Amps.

xATSOutputFrequencyAlarm.name: xATSOutputFrequencyAlarm
xATSOutputFrequencyAlarm.description: SEVERE: The devices output frequency is outside the specified limits. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the frequency deviation from the nominal in tenths of Hertz. The fourth argument is the frequency deviation threshold in tenths of Hertz, from which the alarm was generated.

xATSOutputFrequencyAlarmCleared.name: xATSOutputFrequencyAlarmCleared
xATSOutputFrequencyAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The devices output frequency is back within the specified limits. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSInternalCommError.name: xATSInternalCommError
xATSInternalCommError.description: SEVERE: There is an internal communication error in the device. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSInternalCommErrorCleared.name: xATSInternalCommErrorCleared
xATSInternalCommErrorCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Internal communication has been restored. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSDataCommMismatchError.name: xATSDataCommMismatchError
xATSDataCommMismatchError.description: SEVERE: A data incompatibility exists within the device. This is typically the result of mismatches between firmware revisions of the transfer switch controller and the Network Management interface. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSDataCommMismatchErrorCleared.name: xATSDataCommMismatchErrorCleared
xATSDataCommMismatchErrorCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The internal data incompatibility has been resolved. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGenCommLost.name: xATSGenCommLost
xATSGenCommLost.description: WARNING: The XATS cannot communicate with the generator. This will make unavailable all the xATSGenerator OIDs. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGenCommEstablished.name: xATSGenCommEstablished
xATSGenCommEstablished.description: INFORMATIONAL: The XATS has established communication with the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSNeutralPosition.name: xATSNeutralPosition
xATSNeutralPosition.description: WARNING: XATS has transferred to neutral position. In this position neither Source 1 nor Source 2 is selected, and the XATS will have no output voltage. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the mode in which the switch is operating (1=Auto, 2=Not-in-Auto, Abnormal Condition 3=Not-in-Auto, manual).

xATSSwitchTransferEvent.name: xATSSwitchTransferEvent
xATSSwitchTransferEvent.description: INFORMATIONAL: XATS has transferred from one source to the other. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the mode in which the switch is operating. (1=Auto, 2=Not-in-Auto, Abnormal Condition 3=Not-in-Auto, manual). The fourth argument is the input source selected (1=Source 1, 2=Source 2). The fifth argument is type of transfer that took place. (1=Closed, 2=Open, 3=Unknown)

xATSInternalATSFault.name: xATSInternalATSFault
xATSInternalATSFault.description: SEVERE: An internal XATS fault has been detected. The XATS may have forced itself to not-in-auto mode (abnormal condition), as indicated by the xATSSwitchStatusAutoSwitchOperationalMode OID. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument indicates the detected fault. 1=Cannot Close S1 2=Cannot Close S2 3=Cannot Open S1 4=Cannot Open S2 5=Cannot Trip Open S1 6=Cannot Trip Open S2 7=Start Contact Failure 8=Voltage Sensing Failure

xATSInternalATSFaultCleared.name: xATSInternalATSFaultCleared
xATSInternalATSFaultCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected internal XATS fault has been cleared. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument indicates the detected fault. 1=Cannot Close S1 2=Cannot Close S2 3=Cannot Open S1 4=Cannot Open S2 5=Cannot Trip Open S1 6=Cannot Trip Open S2 7=Start Contact Failure 8=Voltage Sensing Failure

xATSEngineStartAsserted.name: xATSEngineStartAsserted
xATSEngineStartAsserted.description: INFORMATIONAL: The XATS has asserted the Engine Start contact. This should result in the generator producing output voltage. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument indicates the reason that the start signal was asserted 1=Unknown, 2=S1 Low Voltage, 3=S1 High Voltage, 4=S1 Line Imbalance, 5=S1 Freq Range, 6=S1 Bad Rotation.

xATSEngineStopAsserted.name: xATSEngineStopAsserted
xATSEngineStopAsserted.description: INFORMATIONAL: The XATS has de-asserted the Engine Start contact. This should result in the generator shutting down, and producing no output voltage. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSStartFailure.name: xATSStartFailure
xATSStartFailure.description: SEVERE: The generator failed to start. After assertion of the Engine Start signal, the quality of Source 2 was not seen as good. This alarm can be cleared using the xATSSwitchStatusClearLatchedAlarms OID. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument indicates the line quality at S2 1=Unknown, 2=S2 Low Voltage, 3=S2 High Voltage, 4=S2 Line Imbalance, 4=S2 Freq Range, 5=S2 Bad Rotation.

xATSStopFailure.name: xATSStopFailure
xATSStopFailure.description: WARNING: The generator failed to stop. After de-assertion of the Engine Start signal, the quality of Source 2 continued to be seen as good. This alarm can be cleared using the xATSSwitchStatusClearLatchedAlarms OID. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSNotInAutomaticMode.name: xATSNotInAutomaticMode
xATSNotInAutomaticMode.description: SEVERE: Automatic Transfer Switch is not in automatic mode. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The xATSSwitchStatusAutoSwitchStatus OID and the xATSSwitchStatusAutoSwitchOperationalMode OID can provide more information about the state of the XATS.

xATSNotInAutomaticModeCleared.name: xATSNotInAutomaticModeCleared
xATSNotInAutomaticModeCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Automatic Transfer Switch is in automatic mode. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSEpoTripped.name: xATSEpoTripped
xATSEpoTripped.description: SEVERE: The device's Emergency Power Off (EPO) circuit is tripped. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSEpoReset.name: xATSEpoReset
xATSEpoReset.description: INFORMATIONAL: The device's Emergency Power Off (EPO) circuit has been reset to the armed position. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSEpoTestMode.name: xATSEpoTestMode
xATSEpoTestMode.description: WARNING: The device's Emergency Power Off (EPO) circuit has been switched back to the test position. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSEpoArmed.name: xATSEpoArmed
xATSEpoArmed.description: INFORMATIONAL: The device's Emergency Power Off (EPO) circuit has been switched back to the armed position. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSTestInitiated.name: xATSTestInitiated
xATSTestInitiated.description: INFORMATIONAL: A scheduled test has been initiated. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the type of test initiated (1=scheduled, 2=manual).

xATSTestCanceled.name: xATSTestCanceled
xATSTestCanceled.description: INFORMATIONAL: The scheduled test has been canceled The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the type of test initiated (1=scheduled, 2=manual).

xATSTestFailed.name: xATSTestFailed
xATSTestFailed.description: SEVERE: The initiated test has failed. This alarm can be cleared using the xATSSwitchStatusClearLatchedAlarms OID. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSTestPassed.name: xATSTestPassed
xATSTestPassed.description: INFORMATIONAL: The initiated test has passed switched back to the armed position. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSInputContactStateAbnormal.name: xATSInputContactStateAbnormal
xATSInputContactStateAbnormal.description: SEVERE: A user input contact on the device has changed to its abnormal state. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the input contact number. The fourth argument is the input contact name. The fifth argument is the input contact state (1=OPEN, 2=CLOSED). The sixth argument is the configured normal input contact state (1=OPEN, 2=CLOSED).

xATSInputContactStateNormal.name: xATSInputContactStateNormal
xATSInputContactStateNormal.description: INFORMATIONAL: A user input contact on the device has changed to its normal state. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the input contact number. The fourth argument is the input contact name. The fifth argument is the input contact state (1=OPEN, 2=CLOSED). The sixth argument is the configured normal input contact state (1=OPEN, 2=CLOSED).

xATSRemoteStartContactMismatch.name: xATSRemoteStartContactMismatch
xATSRemoteStartContactMismatch.description: SEVERE: The state of the generator's Remote Start input and the ATS's Engine Start output do not match. This indicates something wrong in the Engine Start wiring, which must be corrected. This condition will prevent the generator from being started when needed. (See also: xATSGeneratorStatusRemoteStart and xATSSwitchStatusEngineStartSignal OIDs) The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSRemoteStartContactMismatchCleared.name: xATSRemoteStartContactMismatchCleared
xATSRemoteStartContactMismatchCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Mismatch in the state of the generator's Remote Start input and the ATS's Engine Start output as been resolved. This indicates something wrong in the Engine Start wiring, which must be corrected. This condition will prevent the generator from being started when needed. (See also: xATSGeneratorStatusRemoteStart and xATSSwitchStatusEngineStartSignal OIDs) The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSDoorOpenAlarm.name: xATSDoorOpenAlarm
xATSDoorOpenAlarm.description: WARNING: The XATS exterior panel door is open. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSDoorOpenAlarmCleared.name: xATSDoorOpenAlarmCleared
xATSDoorOpenAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The external door to the device is closed. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSDCBackupAlarm.name: xATSDCBackupAlarm
xATSDCBackupAlarm.description: WARNING: The XATS's DC backup has been lost. The XATS will lose power on Source 1 failure, causing the Engine Start signal to be asserted. The XATS will then restart from Source 2. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSDCBackupAlarmCleared.name: xATSDCBackupAlarmCleared
xATSDCBackupAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: DC backup alarm has been cleared in the device. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGeneratorLowCoolantLevelAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorLowCoolantLevelAlarm
xATSGeneratorLowCoolantLevelAlarm.description: SEVERE: Low coolant level has been detected in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowCoolantLevelAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorLowCoolantLevelAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorLowCoolantLevelAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected low coolant level has been cleared in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowCoolantLevelAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowCoolantLevelAlarm
xATSGeneratorVeryLowCoolantLevelAlarm.description: SEVERE: Very low coolant level has been detected in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowCoolantLevelAlarmCle.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowCoolantLevelAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorVeryLowCoolantLevelAlarmCle.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected Very low coolant level has been cleared in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorHighCoolantTempAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorHighCoolantTempAlarm
xATSGeneratorHighCoolantTempAlarm.description: SEVERE: High coolant temperature has been detected in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorHighCoolantTempAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorHighCoolantTempAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorHighCoolantTempAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected high coolant temperature has been cleared in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorVeryHighCoolantTempAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorVeryHighCoolantTempAlarm
xATSGeneratorVeryHighCoolantTempAlarm.description: SEVERE: Very high coolant temperature has been detected in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorVeryHighCoolantTempAlarmCle.name: xATSGeneratorVeryHighCoolantTempAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorVeryHighCoolantTempAlarmCle.description: INFORMATIONAL: The Very high coolant temperature condition has been cleared in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowCoolantTempAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorLowCoolantTempAlarm
xATSGeneratorLowCoolantTempAlarm.description: WARNING: Low coolant temperature has been detected in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowCoolantTempAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorLowCoolantTempAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorLowCoolantTempAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The low coolant temperature condition has been cleared in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowOilLevelAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorLowOilLevelAlarm
xATSGeneratorLowOilLevelAlarm.description: SEVERE: Low oil level has been detected in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowOilLevelAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorLowOilLevelAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorLowOilLevelAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Low oil level alarm has been cleared in the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltDuringCrankAl.name: xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltDuringCrankAlarm
xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltDuringCrankAl.description: SEVERE: The generator's battery voltage has been detected as low while cranking the engine. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltDuringCrankAl.name: xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltDuringCrankAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltDuringCrankAl.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator's low battery voltage while cranking condition has been cleared. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowBatteryVoltDuringCra.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowBatteryVoltDuringCrankAlarm
xATSGeneratorVeryLowBatteryVoltDuringCra.description: SEVERE: The generator's battery voltage has been detected as very low while cranking the engine. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowBatteryVoltDuringCra.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowBatteryVoltDuringCrankAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorVeryLowBatteryVoltDuringCra.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator's high battery voltage while cranking condition has been cleared. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorEStop.name: xATSGeneratorEStop
xATSGeneratorEStop.description: SEVERE: The generator's emergency stop input has been activated. After the emergency stop signal has been removed, the E-Stop condition must be cleared before the generator can be started again. E-Stop conditions can only be cleared via the generator front panel. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code. The fourth argument is the type of E-Stop (1=LOCAL, 2=REMOTE).

xATSGeneratorEStopCleared.name: xATSGeneratorEStopCleared
xATSGeneratorEStopCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator's emergency stop condition has been cleared. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code. The fourth argument is the type of E-Stop (1=LOCAL, 2=REMOTE).

xATSGeneratorHighBatteryVolt.name: xATSGeneratorHighBatteryVolt
xATSGeneratorHighBatteryVolt.description: WARNING: The generator's battery voltage has been detected as high. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorHighBatteryVoltCleared.name: xATSGeneratorHighBatteryVoltCleared
xATSGeneratorHighBatteryVoltCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected high battery voltage has been cleared, on the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVolt.name: xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVolt
xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVolt.description: SEVERE: The generator's battery voltage has been detected as low. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltCleared.name: xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltCleared
xATSGeneratorLowBatteryVoltCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected low battery voltage has been cleared, on the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorControlSwitchNotAuto.name: xATSGeneratorControlSwitchNotAuto
xATSGeneratorControlSwitchNotAuto.description: SEVERE: The control switch on the generator is not in auto position. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorControlSwitchNotAutoCleared.name: xATSGeneratorControlSwitchNotAutoCleared
xATSGeneratorControlSwitchNotAutoCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The control switch on the generator is in auto position. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowOilPressure.name: xATSGeneratorLowOilPressure
xATSGeneratorLowOilPressure.description: SEVERE: The generator's oil pressure has been detected as low. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowOilPressureCleared.name: xATSGeneratorLowOilPressureCleared
xATSGeneratorLowOilPressureCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected low oil pressure has been cleared, on the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowOilPressure.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowOilPressure
xATSGeneratorVeryLowOilPressure.description: SEVERE: The generator's oil pressure has been detected as very low. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowOilPressureCleared.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowOilPressureCleared
xATSGeneratorVeryLowOilPressureCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected v.low oil pressure has been cleared, on the generator. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorOverload.name: xATSGeneratorOverload
xATSGeneratorOverload.description: SEVERE: The generator is overloaded. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorOverloadCleared.name: xATSGeneratorOverloadCleared
xATSGeneratorOverloadCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator is running within loading limits. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowACVEvent.name: xATSGeneratorLowACVEvent
xATSGeneratorLowACVEvent.description: SEVERE: The generator AC voltage is outside the acceptable bounds. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowACVEventCleared.name: xATSGeneratorLowACVEventCleared
xATSGeneratorLowACVEventCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator AC voltage is within normal bounds. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorHighACVEvent.name: xATSGeneratorHighACVEvent
xATSGeneratorHighACVEvent.description: SEVERE: The generator AC voltage is outside the acceptable bounds. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorHighACVEventCleared.name: xATSGeneratorHighACVEventCleared
xATSGeneratorHighACVEventCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator AC voltage is within normal bounds. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorOverspeed.name: xATSGeneratorOverspeed
xATSGeneratorOverspeed.description: SEVERE: The generator is running over the acceptable RPM. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorOverspeedCleared.name: xATSGeneratorOverspeedCleared
xATSGeneratorOverspeedCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator overspeed shutdown has been cleared. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorEngineCold.name: xATSGeneratorEngineCold
xATSGeneratorEngineCold.description: SEVERE: The generator engine is cold, may not start. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorEngineColdCleared.name: xATSGeneratorEngineColdCleared
xATSGeneratorEngineColdCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The engine is not cold to start. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorOutputBreakerOpen.name: xATSGeneratorOutputBreakerOpen
xATSGeneratorOutputBreakerOpen.description: SEVERE: The generators output breaker has been detected as open. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorOutputBreakerOpenCleared.name: xATSGeneratorOutputBreakerOpenCleared
xATSGeneratorOutputBreakerOpenCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The engine is not cold to start. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorLowFuelLevelAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorLowFuelLevelAlarm
xATSGeneratorLowFuelLevelAlarm.description: WARNING: The tank fuel level is below the limits specified in the xATSGeneratorFuelSystemLowFuelLevelThreshold OID. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the measured fuel level in percent of full.

xATSGeneratorLowFuelLevelAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorLowFuelLevelAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorLowFuelLevelAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The tank fuel level is back above the specified limit. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowFuelLevelAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowFuelLevelAlarm
xATSGeneratorVeryLowFuelLevelAlarm.description: SEVERE: The tank fuel level is below the low threshold limits. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the measured tank fuel level in percent of full.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowFuelLevelAlarmCleare.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowFuelLevelAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorVeryLowFuelLevelAlarmCleare.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected low tank level has been cleared in the device. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGeneratorLowRunTimeAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorLowRunTimeAlarm
xATSGeneratorLowRunTimeAlarm.description: WARNING: The estimated runtime is below the limits specified. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the estimated runtime in hours.

xATSGeneratorLowRunTimeAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorLowRunTimeAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorLowRunTimeAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected low runtime has been cleared in the device. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowRunTimeAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowRunTimeAlarm
xATSGeneratorVeryLowRunTimeAlarm.description: SEVERE: The estimated runtime is below the limits specified in the xATSGeneratorFuelSystemVeryLowRunTimeThreshold OID. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the estimated runtime in hours.

xATSGeneratorVeryLowRunTimeAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorVeryLowRunTimeAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorVeryLowRunTimeAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The detected low runtime has been cleared in the device. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGeneratorServiceDueAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorServiceDueAlarm
xATSGeneratorServiceDueAlarm.description: WARNING: The generator is due for scheduled service. Generation of this alarm is based on calendar days since and/or actual generator run-hours since last service. This alarm is cleared using the xATSGeneratorServiceResetRecord OID. (See also: xATSGeneratorServiceCalendarIntervalThreshold and xATSGeneratorServiceRunHoursThreshold OIDs) The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGeneratorServiceDueAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorServiceDueAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorServiceDueAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator's service registers have been reset. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGeneratorShutdown.name: xATSGeneratorShutdown
xATSGeneratorShutdown.description: SEVERE: The generator is shutdown. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorShutdownCleared.name: xATSGeneratorShutdownCleared
xATSGeneratorShutdownCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The generator shutdown alarm is cleared. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorBatteryCharger.name: xATSGeneratorBatteryCharger
xATSGeneratorBatteryCharger.description: SEVERE: The generator battery charger is nonfunctional. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorBatteryChargerCleared.name: xATSGeneratorBatteryChargerCleared
xATSGeneratorBatteryChargerCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Fault in the generator battery charger is cleared. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorGenericEvent.name: xATSGeneratorGenericEvent
xATSGeneratorGenericEvent.description: WARNING: Any generic generator event. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorGenericEventCleared.name: xATSGeneratorGenericEventCleared
xATSGeneratorGenericEventCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Generated generic generator event is cleared. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xPDUInternalCommErrorCleared.name: xPDUInternalCommErrorCleared
xPDUInternalCommErrorCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Internal communication has been restored. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xPDUSystemStateAlarm.name: xPDUSystemStateAlarm
xPDUSystemStateAlarm.description: SEVERE: The PDU's breakers (Q1, Q2 & Q3) are in a configuration that might lead to system unavailability. it may signify a temporary condition, when the breakers are placed in an atypical manner as the user transitions to (UPS OPERATION or MAINTENANCE BYPASS) The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the type of state change (1=NO UPS INPUT, 2=NO PANEL FEED, 3=ATYPICAL BYPASS MODE). note: The NO_PANEL_FEED alarm is applicable only for PDUs with system bypass.

xPDUSystemStateAlarmCleared.name: xPDUSystemStateAlarmCleared
xPDUSystemStateAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The PDU's breakers (Q1, Q2 & Q3) are set in a configuration that is a non-alarm state. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the type of state change (1=NO UPS INPUT, 2=NO PANEL FEED, 3=ATYPICAL BYPASS MODE). note: The NO_PANEL_FEED alarm is applicable only for PDUs with system bypass.

xPDUEpoTestMode.name: xPDUEpoTestMode
xPDUEpoTestMode.description: WARNING: The device's Emergency Power Off (EPO) circuit has been switched back to the test position. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xPDUEpoArmed.name: xPDUEpoArmed
xPDUEpoArmed.description: INFORMATIONAL: The device's Emergency Power Off (EPO) circuit has been switched back to the armed position. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xPDUFuseBlownAlarm.name: xPDUFuseBlownAlarm
xPDUFuseBlownAlarm.description: SEVERE: One or more fuses in this PDU have been detected as open. These fuses are in the feed to the UPS associated with this PDU. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the phase (1=L1, 2=L2, 3=L3).

xPDUFuseBlownAlarmCleared.name: xPDUFuseBlownAlarmCleared
xPDUFuseBlownAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A previous check fuse alarm in this PDU has cleared. These fuses are in the feed to the UPS associated with this PDU. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the phase (1=L1, 2=L2, 3=L3).

xPDUBreakerPositionAlarm.name: xPDUBreakerPositionAlarm
xPDUBreakerPositionAlarm.description: SEVERE: A PDU breaker is in a state that compromises system availability. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the breaker (1=MAIN INPUT, 2=BYPASS INPUT, 3=CROSS TIE, 4=OUTPUT). note: The OUTPUT breaker position alarm is applicable only for PDUs with no system bypass. The fourth argument is the breaker position (1=OPEN, 2=CLOSED).

xPDUBreakerPositionAlarmCleared.name: xPDUBreakerPositionAlarmCleared
xPDUBreakerPositionAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: A PDU breaker is no longer in a state that compromises system availability. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the breaker (1=MAIN INPUT, 2=BYPASS INPUT, 3=CROSS TIE, 4=OUTPUT). note: The OUTPUT breaker position alarm cleared is applicable only for PDUs with no system bypass.

xPDUBreakerChangeEvent.name: xPDUBreakerChangeEvent
xPDUBreakerChangeEvent.description: INFORMATIONAL: A system breaker or switch within the device has changed state. They are generated when any of the Q1, Q2 or Q3 breakers have changed states. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the breaker that has changed (1=UPS FEED (Q1), 2=UPS OUTPUT(Q2), 3=MAINTENANCE BYPASS (Q3). The fourth argument is the state of the breaker that has changed (1=OPEN, 2=CLOSED). The fifth argument is a 8-bit field representing the state of all breakers in the system, when any of one of the Q1, Q2 or Q3 breakers have changed state. The bit map is represented in the following manner (b7, b6 ... b0) b0 - UPS FEED (Q1) b1 - MAINTENANCE BYPASS (Q3) b2 - UPS OUTPUT (Q2) b3 - MAIN INPUT b4 - BYPASS INPUT b5 - CROSS-TIE OUTPUT Example: value of 60 (0x3C) indicates that the CROSS_TIE, BYPASS and MAIN INPUT, and Q2 breakers are CLOSED and Q3, Q1 breakers are OPEN.

xPDUDataCommMismatchError.name: xPDUDataCommMismatchError
xPDUDataCommMismatchError.description: SEVERE: A data incompatibility exists within the device. This is typically the result of mismatches between firmware revisions of the transfer switch controller and the Network Management interface. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xPDUDataCommMismatchErrorCleared.name: xPDUDataCommMismatchErrorCleared
xPDUDataCommMismatchErrorCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The internal data incompatibility has been resolved. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xPDUSystemInMaintenanceBypassMode.name: xPDUSystemInMaintenanceBypassMode
xPDUSystemInMaintenanceBypassMode.description: WARNING: The PDU state has changed to maintenance bypass mode. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xPDUSystemInUPSOperationalMode.name: xPDUSystemInUPSOperationalMode
xPDUSystemInUPSOperationalMode.description: INFORMATIONAL: The PDU state has changed to UPS operational mode. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xATSGeneratorFuelTankRuptureAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorFuelTankRuptureAlarm
xATSGeneratorFuelTankRuptureAlarm.description: WARNING: Detected a rupture in the inner wall of the generator fuel tank. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorFuelTankRuptureAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorFuelTankRuptureAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorFuelTankRuptureAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The rupture in the inner wall of the generator is not detected. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorGroundFaultAlarm.name: xATSGeneratorGroundFaultAlarm
xATSGeneratorGroundFaultAlarm.description: SEVERE: Generator ground fault alarm. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSGeneratorGroundFaultAlarmCleared.name: xATSGeneratorGroundFaultAlarmCleared
xATSGeneratorGroundFaultAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Generator ground fault alarm cleared. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the OEM's fault/event code.

xATSOutputLoadPoweredByGeneratorAlarm.name: xATSOutputLoadPoweredByGeneratorAlarm
xATSOutputLoadPoweredByGeneratorAlarm.description: WARNING: The system load on the output of the ATS is being powered by source 2 (generator). The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument indicates if the load is powered by the generator, when 'load testing' the generator (1 = LIVE, 2 = TEST).

xATSOutputLoadPoweredByGeneratorAlarmCle.name: xATSOutputLoadPoweredByGeneratorAlarmCleared
xATSOutputLoadPoweredByGeneratorAlarmCle.description: INFORMATIONAL: The system load on the output of the ATS is no longer being powered by source 2 (generator). The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name.

xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferStar.name: xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferStart
xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferStar.description: INFORMATIONAL: Start controller firmware transfer in the device. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host model name that initiated the transfer. The third argument is the name of the file that is transferred. The fourth argument is the updated revision of the file, if available The fifth argument is the reason for the update, if available (1=User request, 2=Automatic upgrade by NMC, 3=Unknown).

xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferComp.name: xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferComplete
xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferComp.description: INFORMATIONAL: Transfer of controller firmware was completed in the device. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device model name that completed the transfer. The third argument is the name of the file that was transferred. The fourth argument is the revision of the file that was transferred, if available.

xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferFail.name: xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferFailed
xAPCControllerFirmwareUpdateTransferFail.description: SEVERE: Transfer of controller firmware failed. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device model name that failed to transfer. The third argument is the name of the file that failed the transfer, if available. The fourth argument is the reason for failure.

upsPfcInputRelayFailure.name: upsPfcInputRelayFailure
upsPfcInputRelayFailure.description: WARNING: The PFC (Power Factor Correction) input relay failure exists.

upsPfcInputRelayFailureCleared.name: upsPfcInputRelayFailureCleared
upsPfcInputRelayFailureCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The PFC (Power Factor Correction) input relay failure cleared.

upsInverterOverTemperature.name: upsInverterOverTemperature
upsInverterOverTemperature.description: WARNING: The inverter over temperature condition exists.

upsInverterOverTemperatureCleared.name: upsInverterOverTemperatureCleared
upsInverterOverTemperatureCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The inverter over temperature condition cleared.

upsBatteryOverVoltage.name: upsBatteryOverVoltage
upsBatteryOverVoltage.description: WARNING: The battery over voltage condition exists.

upsBatteryOverVoltageCleared.name: upsBatteryOverVoltageCleared
upsBatteryOverVoltageCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The battery over voltage condition cleared.

aruFanRuntimeAlarm.name: aruFanRuntimeAlarm
aruFanRuntimeAlarm.description: WARNING: The total running hours for a fan has exceeded the run hour threshold. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the ARU number. The fourth argument is the ARU name. The fifth argument indicates which fan in the ARU.

aruFanRuntimeAlarmCleared.name: aruFanRuntimeAlarmCleared
aruFanRuntimeAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: The total running hours for a fan is no longer above the fan runhour threshold. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the ARU number. The fourth argument is the ARU name. The fifth argument indicates which fan in the ARU.

aruFanPoorPerformanceAlarm.name: aruFanPoorPerformanceAlarm
aruFanPoorPerformanceAlarm.description: WARNING: Poor fan performance has been detected in the ARU, indicating that the fan may be close to failing. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the ARU number. The fourth argument is the ARU name. The fifth argument indicates which fan in the ARU.

aruFanPoorPerformanceAlarmCleared.name: aruFanPoorPerformanceAlarmCleared
aruFanPoorPerformanceAlarmCleared.description: INFORMATIONAL: Fan performance is no longer degraded. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is the ARU number. The fourth argument is the ARU name. The fifth argument indicates which fan in the ARU.

aruRedundantPowerLostAlarm.name: aruRedundantPowerLostAlarm

aruRedundantPowerLostAlarmCleared.name: aruRedundantPowerLostAlarmCleared

apcDeviceConfigChange.name: apcDeviceConfigChange

apcOutletStateAbnormal.name: apcOutletStateAbnormal

The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is a secondary device id number. The fourth argument is the outlet number. The fifth argument is the outlet name. The sixth argument is the current outlet state (1=ON, 2=OFF). The seventh argument is the configured normal outlet state (1=ON, 2=OFF).

The sixth argument is the current output relay state (1=CLOSED, 2=OPEN). The seventh argument is the configured normal output relay state (1=CLOSED, 2=OPEN).

This can be caused by improper devices being connected to device ports or Alink Current limit detection. The first argument is the host device serial number. The second argument is the host device name. The third argument is a secondary device id number. The fourth argument is a hardware specific state code.

The third argument is the ISXC alarm code. The fourth argument is the unique ISXC device ID. The fifth argument is the ISXC device label as a UTF8 string. The sixth argument is the ISXC parent host. The seventh argument is the ISXC device type as a UTF8 string. The eighth argument is the device serial number. The ninth argument is the device model number. The tenth argument is the device host. The eleventh argument is the device location as a UTF8 string. The twelfth argument is the device contact as a UTF8 string. The thirteenth argument is the unique ISXC sensor ID. The fourteenth argument is the ISXC sensor label as a UTF8 string. The fifteenth argument is the sensor value as a UTF8 string. The sixteenth argument is the ISXC alarm start time. The seventeenth argument is the ISXC alarm resolution time. The eighteenth argument is the description as a UTF8 string.

upsOnBatteryDueToFault.name: upsOnBatteryDueToFault
upsOnBatteryDueToFault.description: SEVERE: The UPS is on battery due to an error. Symmetra UPSes: Intelligence module has reported being in self-test for too long. When this happens, the UPS is not usually in self-test, but the batteries are draining slowly. If left uncorrected, the batteries will become depleted and the UPS will not be able to turn on. If UPS has at least N+1 redundancy, check power modules one by one to determine which keeps the UPS in self-test. Once identified, replace the module.
